These two Government Camp vacation rentals are located on the same lot in the beautiful forest of Mt Hood and, with a combined total of seven bedrooms, can accommodate up to 30. They're perfect for hosting a large gathering in a scenic and comfortable setting.

The Big Bear Cabin will fit your large group comfortably in its 2,500 square feet and three floors.  On the main floor you will find an expansive living and dining area, complete with an extra large dining table that fits 18 guests, comfy leather couches and recliners, and a flat screen TV with a DVD player. A beautiful master bedroom sits on the main floor as well and includes a queen sized bed with its own private bathroom.

Upstairs a large bedroom holds a queen bed and four twins to sleep up to six guests and comes with a flat screen TV for entertainment.

Downstairs are two more bedrooms; the first hosting two sets of bunk beds and a queen sized bed, and the second room containing a queen and another set of twin-over-twin bunks as well.

The Little Bear Cabin vacation rental is the smaller of the Bear cabins, but can still accommodate up to 12 guests.

It is the perfect place to gather everyone together after a day of enjoying all that Mt. Hood has to offer and relax in the cozy living room that comes complete with a wall mounted flat screen TV and entertainment center. There is also wireless internet throughout the houses so you can work and play while you are away.

An open and upscale kitchen with granite counter tops and stainless steel appliances coaxes out your inner chef and includes plenty of seating around the island.

The master bedroom can be found on the top floor and includes a queen sized bed with a private bathroom and an open loft that houses an additional queen mattress. A large bathroom splits the hall between this room and the second upstairs bedroom, which includes two sets of bunk beds and a queen bed.

The third bedroom is on the main floor and contains another set of bunk beds and queen bed as well. Pets are welcome here and if you do bring your dogs along, it's just a $10 per day, per pet fee, with a $40 minimum fee required.

These charming and spacious Mt. Hood vacation rental cabins are located close to the base of Glade Trail, which is connected to Timberline Ski Area and a favorite with snowboarders, skiers, and those who like to snowshoe. In summertime, take in the sounds of beautiful Camp Creek that runs between Big and Little Bear cabins while soaking in the shared hot tub.

