We rented this house for a long guys' weekend. This house worked wonderfully in that there were beds for everyone (11 of us) and there was plenty of room to spreadout and not constantly be stepping on each other. The house was clean and tidy, though perhaps overpopulated with tchotchkes and life's detritus - there are tons of books and nick-knacks in every drawer, cupboard, and shelf (we found a book from the 1920s with a program from a 1926 Cincinnati Orchestra performance tucked in the front).

One area of concern we did have was with the cable service; there was a big football game on and we checked ahead of time to confirm the house had the basic cable service which included the channel we needed. Unfortunately, we didn't think to specifically ask whether the house also had a cable box. They don't. That meant only the analog channels offered within the basic cable package were available (and some of those, like ABC and CBS, were almost unwatchable); none of the digital channels, including Pac-12 Network were available. To their credit, the management company really impressed with their efforts to understand the problem and follow up with the homeowner and then with us. They couldn't actually fix it for us, but they tried, and I have no doubt if they could have, they would have.

The house has *tons* of dishes; there was never a shortage of silverware, plates, bowls, glassware, etc. They could have handled a small army.

One thing we noticed was that almost every room in the house has one or more mystery light switches. Seriously, in the "dining" room right next to the kitchen (where the TV is), I think there were 6 light switches in one long bank and not a single one of them seemed to do anything. It didn't help that there were many burned out light bulbs or that they used lots of regular bulbs in three way lamps.

The website said the house could accommodate 8 cars; the email and signage within the home all specify a hard limit of 5. Obviously that creates challenges if you planned on 8 but are then limited to 5; we squeezed more cars on the driveway and it worked, but it was an unpleasant surprise.

Hopefully the homeowners invest a little in the sprucing up the place, buying some decent TVs (this house has at least 3 CRT TVs) and renting a cable box, and maybe clearing out some of the clutter, but the house was big and clean and met all of our needs. All in all, we would definitely come back.

