Multorpor: While the name sounds other-worldly, it's actually very close to home - about an hour and a half from Portland. When you stay at this roomy, smartly appointed and spacious Government Camp vacation rental lodge with six bedrooms and room for 15, you'll be right there!

Just footsteps to Skibowl in historic and scenic Government Camp, you'll also be a short ride to Mount Hood Meadows, storied Timberline Lodge, and other ski areas.  It's the perfect place for that family reunion or business getaway. And Government Camp isn't just for winter. In summer, there are about 25 hiking trails of varying difficulty in the area, not to mention the fishing and rafting on the Sandy and great golfing up the road in Welches, about twenty minutes away.

The living room is enormous, with comfy leather chairs. And while you're relaxing, it might be hard for your eyes to choose between the forest view through the floor-to-ceiling windows, or the fire in the uniquely designed gas fireplace. With 4500 square feet of living space, six bedrooms and three bathrooms, there's plenty of room to bunk down. Lots of fun things too! Kids of all ages will love the play station. There's a BIG flat screen TV with cable and a DVD player for those movies you brought along. Shuffle the deck and enjoy a friendly game of cards at the game table. If you need to check your e-mail before you go out and play, this lodge has WiFi throughout.

A big group needs a big kitchen, and this lodge has it. With tons of cabinets and lots of counter space, there's ample room - from prep to presentation - to feed that hungry clan.

In addition to five big bedrooms with ample storage space, there are bunk beds in the lower level as well. Settle in with a book and lounge on the soft couch and chairs.

Government Camp is just a short walk away. You can pick up some things at the general store, enjoy a cup of coffee or a meal at one of the eateries, buy some equipment at one of the outfitters, arrange your day of skiing at Skibowl, or hop on the shuttle to Mount Hound Meadows. Government Camp is full of history. Timberline Lodge, Barlow Trail, Glade Trail and other places have unique histories you can learn about at the Mount Hood Cultural Center.

Get your family, friends, or coworkers together for an unforgettable getaway in this Mt. Hood vacation rental.

