Immerse yourself in history and comfort at this gorgeous 1940s-era, riverview, three-bedroom Welches vacation rental. Near ski resorts and hiking trails, right on the edge of the Mt. Hood National Forest, you'll spend your time here relaxing on the deck, soaking in the private hot tub, gathering around the massive floor-to-ceiling, rock-faced fireplace, and breathing in the fresh mountain air. This Papa Bear Cabin is even pet-friendly, so up to four of your furry family members can join you on an unforgettable Mt. Hood getaway.

The inside of this stylish Welches bungalow will remind you of a mountain lodge - with its tall ceilings, wood paneling and beams, gorgeous hardwood floors, and comfortable furniture. While the snow falls down outside, put another log on the fire, and settle back on the sofa right under the antler chandelier for an evening of chatting, reading, or watching TV. There's cable, WiFi, a DVD player, and a VCR, as well as a collection of VHS tapes to choose from.

Deck access is right through either set of the living room's French doors. Out here, you'll find a hot tub, a gas grill, and a beautiful view of the Salmon River. The water is so close, you can even dip your toes in right from the edge of the property.

This main level is spacious and open, with a china hutch, dining table, and small work area right by a black iron spiral staircase. The country-style full kitchen has an eat-in breakfast counter, stovetop/range, refrigerator, dishwasher, and microwave. Smaller gadgets include a coffee grinder and toaster, so quick breakfasts before a hike are easy to prepare.

Right near the work station is a plaid-themed full bathroom with a pedestal sink and a walk-in shower. And on this level, you'll also find the first bedroom with a queen bed, brass bed frame, and a rustic, mountain cabin decor. This room also has a stacked washer and dryer, so there's no need to overpack when you stay here.

Up the spiral staircase, are the two additional bedrooms - one with a full and a twin bed, as well as another room with two twin beds. And in the upstair bathroom, you'll have a beautiful clawfoot tub for soaking - there's even a large skylight in the slanted ceiling for a tree-lined view. All bedrooms have their own TVs. In addition, a sofabed provides and extra sleeping space, so that up to seven guests can stay here at the Papa Bear Cabin. Up to four dogs are also welcome with a $10 per day, per pet fee ($40 minimum per stay).

This Welches vacation cabin is close to hiking and biking trails, river access, golfing at The Resort at the Mountains, and numerous restaurants for those evenings that you don't feel like cooking. Right along the Mt. Hood Scenic Byway there's the highly-rated Rendezvous Grill for specials like Wine Down Wednesdays, El Burro Locco for wild boar tacos, and the ZigZag Inn - be sure to try a pizza there!

In winter, you're only 13 miles from Mt. Hood Skibowl, 19 miles from Timberline Lodge, and 22 miles from Mt. Hood Meadows, so you'll want to be sure to bring your skis and snowboards! And even closer to your mountain getaway, you can enjoy cross-country skiing, snowboarding, and even snowmobiling in the Mt. Hood National Forest.

This Papa Bear Cabin in Welches is the quintessential Mt. Hood / Hood River vacation rental! Year-round, you'll enjoy classic mountain lodge ambiance, your own private hot tub with forest views, and a great location near all the area's best attractions.

