Nestled in the rolling hills with awesome views of Mt. Hood, this getaway is secluded and comfortable! You'll have close access to fabulous outdoor activities like skiing, hiking, mountain biking, and kayaking, plus the town of Parkdale is quaint and charming, and less than three miles away.

All on one level with a laid-back interior, this home feels like your own private mountain cottage!

You'll feel welcomed as soon as you walk through the front door - the living room is spacious and open with soft blue couches, a flatscreen TV, and tons of natural light. Around the corner, the full kitchen is cozy with a six-person dining table, and all the amenities the chef could need to whip up a special meal, including a dishwasher! The views of Mt. Hood out the kitchen window don't hurt, either.

There are three bedrooms in this home, with the master located at the end of the hallway. The master is spacious with a queen-size bed, plenty of places to store your things, and a modern private bathroom.

The other two bedrooms are kid-friendly with brightly painted walls. One has twin bunk beds while the other has a twin-over-queen-size bed with an attached bathroom. With a full bathroom for each bedroom, there's tons of privacy and room for up to seven guests.

You'll fall in love with the backyard and patio here - the deck has its own covered seating area where you can relax, along with a gas grill for BBQ. The rolling hills and mountains provide a gorgeous backdrop, and for an additional fee, you can also bring  up to two dogs here. There's also WiFi and a private washer/dryer for your use.

This house has a fantastic yet rural location just under three miles from Parkdale and 26 miles from ski slopes! If you happen to come in the winter, this home would be a great ski base since Mt. Hood Meadows, Timberline Lodge, and SkiBowl are an easy drive from here. Spend your day on the slopes then drive down to the warmer temperatures in Parkdale!

There are also ample opportunities to get outside and explore the mountains. A lot of hiking trails and rivers populate this area, so it's easy to stretch your legs or cool off in some bright blue waters.

Parkdale provides a few restaurants and bars that have outrageously good views of the mountain, plus great food and beer! If you want to check out the Columbia River Gorge, Hood River is about 14 miles away, or if you're more into the city vibe, Portland is about 80 miles away.

You'll get sucked into life around here right away in this gorgeous Mt. Hood vacation rental!

