Relax and spread out in this amazing Government Camp vacation rental. Big Bear Cabin, a 2,800 square feet vacation rental with three floors, is located at the base of the mountain in the scenic mountain woods, and offers up to 18 people a chance to forget their worries and get lost in the woods - without losing out on modern convenience.

The Big Bear Lodge vacation rental is a traditional log home built with extra large logs for a unique look. On the main floor you will find an expansive living and dining area, complete with an extra large dining table that fits all 18 guests, comfy leather couches and recliners, and a flat screen TV with a DVD player. You and your guests will love admiring all the antiques hanging on the walls - old snowshoes, cross country skis, bobsleds, and even an old ski trail sign.

The expansive kitchen with granite countertops and modern appliances is a chef's dream - in fact, its size means that multiple cooks can be in the kitchen at once, prepping and cleaning up as a group! Enjoy fun gadgets like a coffee grinder and a blender, and a dishwasher for easy cleaning.

Sleep will be deep and comfortable here - no need to put anyone on the sofa. A beautiful master bedroom sits on the main floor as well and includes a queen sized bed with its own private bathroom, and pretty furnishings, including a bear statuette on top of the wardrobe!

Upstairs a large bedroom holds a queen bed and four twins to sleep up to six guests and comes with a flat screen TV for entertainment: a perfect place for young ones to spend their time watching their favorite TV shows or movies. There is also wireless Internet throughout the house so you can work and play while you are away!

Downstairs are two more bedrooms; the first hosting two sets of bunk beds and a queen sized bed, and the second room containing a queen and two more twin bunks as well, plus a card table and a second bear statuette. Downstairs is also a mud room perfect for stacking icy gear, and a laundry room to keep all your active wear fresh. This home is just the right size for a large family or ski team!

You're welcome to bring up to four dogs along, just remember the $10 per pet, per night fee, with a minimum of $40 per stay.

