When it's time to eat, head to the updated and sleekly-designed kitchen. There are granite countertops, a custom stone backsplash, and shiny, white appliances (including a dishwasher). Start the morning with chocolate chip pancakes before a hike through the Mt. Hood National Forest and end the day with a big bowl of popcorn in front of the fire. There's also a dining room table with seating for eight and a few extra spots at the breakfast bar for nights when you want to gather everyone around for a sit-down meal.

The spacious outdoor deck extends the full length of the house and includes a private hot tub surrounded by trees. End the evening with a luxurious soak and if the weather is rainy or snowing, extend the large umbrella and stay protected from the elements. On sunny afternoons, use the gas grill to cook up a feast and when it's done you don't even need to head inside for the meal - there's plenty of room on the deck for dining al fresco.

A bedroom on the main floor is bright and airy, with deck access right near the hot tub. This peaceful oasis has a king sized bed, large closet, and its own private bathroom. And up the carpeted stairs are the two additional bedrooms and a bonus room. There's a queen bedroom with matching furniture, including a bedside table and dresser, and an additional bedroom with twin over queen bunk beds.

The bonus room has two more twin beds (great for kids!) and an additional 42-inch flat screen TV. This is an ideal layout if you want to set the kids up in here with a movie or boardgames, while the adults congregate downstairs for cocktails and their own flick. This Mt. Hood condo will comfortably sleep up to nine guests (six adults), making it perfect for family getaways or couples with kids traveling together.

