The enormous galley kitchen is ready to feed the masses. Get your cooks together to plan out a family-style feast, then spread out over the countertops to work. Whether breakfast, lunch, dinner, or somewhere in between, this kitchen has all the tools you could need, including a dishwasher for easy cleaning. Dine out in the formal eating area, or out on the deck.

This five-bedroom, two and a half bathroom home comfortably sleeps up to 13 people. A small family may like to take the two downstairs bedrooms with a bathroom between them. The master suite has a king bed, a private fireplace, and a jetted tub for extra relaxation away from the crowd. The room across the way has two twins, perfect for children to share.

The second floor has a nice loft space, casual and comfy with European-style decor. This is another wonderful place for a small group to gather for a movie, a board game, or a chat over chips and salsa. Two bedrooms and one full bathroom are on this floor. Both bedrooms have queen beds with beautiful quilts; one has a skylight.

Put the younger members downstairs in the basement game room. There are seven beds total, including a trundle bed and two bunk beds. A foosball table will keep the group entertained. The laundry room and the half-bath are on this floor as well.

This is a wonderful home for a multi-generational group, from grandparents to young children. This home is also perfect for family reunions, holidays, and celebrations with friends.

