This adorable and pet-friendly Government Camp vacation rental has a balcony, close ski access, and views of the mountains!

With a convenient location down the street from downtown Government Camp and just a few miles from three ski areas, this is the perfect base for your Mt. Hood adventures! There are tons of things to do all year round in this incredible area, whether it's skiing, snowboarding, hiking, or camping! Plus, Government Camp and its neighboring mountain towns provide restaurants, bars, and little boutiques to explore.

With wood-beam walls and retro decorations, this home has its own cabin-in-the-woods feel!

As soon as you walk in, the red carpeting, beamed ceilings, and cozy fireplace will make you feel right at home! The living room has a comfortable couch, arm chairs, and a huge flatscreen TV where you can watch cable. Relax with a glass of red wine next to the fireplace, or have a cold beer with your crew after a day outdoors! The small kitchen offers a lot of cupboard space, a fridge, microwave, coffee maker, and a stovetop/oven.

Upstairs, two bedrooms provide cozy places to retreat at day's end! The master has a plush king-size bed, as well as a private balcony with views of the beautiful mountains. There are two twin-size beds in the other bedroom, as well as a half-bath on this level. With a sofa bed, this home can sleep up to six, and there's a full bathroom on the main level with a stand-up shower and fluffy towels for your convenience.

There's a mudroom downstairs where you can leave any wet gear or jackets to dry out, and the firepit out back means a fun night under the stars! For an additional fee, you can bring your dogs along too, and there's also WiFi so you can share your pictures with friends and family back home!

If you're a skiing or snowboarding enthusiast, this home has an incredible location. Right down the street from Government Camp, the ski areas of Timberline, Mt. Hood Meadows, and SkiBowl are all within an 11 mile radius. Spend your days out on the slopes chasing the powder, then head back to town for a cold brew at one of the bars!

This area is teeming with activities anytime of year, however, thanks to the gorgeous area surrounding Mt. Hood. There are tons of trails to hike, rivers to kayak, and lakes to swim in nearby!

For day trips, the Columbia River Gorge is about 40 miles away where you can find world-class windsurfing, kite boarding, and stand-up paddle boarding options, and the town of Hood River is an awesome place to relax and explore! If you're feeling more into the metropolis vibe, the city of Portland is less than 60 miles away, and there are many other charming mountain towns to visit along the way.

