Mountain views with activities for all

Nestled among the fairways of one of Oregon's most beautiful golf courses, this spacious three-bedroom condo is a perfect retreat for golfers, skiers, hikers, and spa-lovers alike!

Ideally located next to the lovely Resort at the Mountain on the western side of Mt. Hood, this condo offers the best of both worlds: easy access to the resort's golf, spas, and dining, along with all the peace, quiet, and cozy amenities of a private mountain getaway. When you are curled up by the wood-burning fireplace on a winter night or sipping your morning coffee in the patio's fresh mountain air, you'll know just what we mean.

Although cozy enough for just one couple or a small family getaway, the condo is also suitable for a larger group thanks to its flexible sleeping arrangements. Two of the three bedrooms each contain two sets of twin bunk beds, and the master bedroom offers both a luxurious queen bed and another set of twin bunks. There are two full bathrooms, making it comfortable for up to 8 guests!

The great room makes a wonderfully cozy pace for everyone in your group to gather, with a wood-burning fireplace, rustic touches like exposed timber beams, and plenty of comfortable seating (the sofa unfolds into a sleeper as well). The flat-screen TV offers cable and a DVD/Blu-Ray player, and two additional televisions in the bedrooms allow the kids to spread out if they can't agree on just one selection for movie night.

The fully-equipped kitchen has everything you need to prepare meals for your group. In addition to the usual refrigerator, oven, dishwasher, and microwave, you'll find cabinets fully stocked with plates, glassware, pots and pans, and cooking utensils, along with plenty of counter-top appliances to make cooking for a group easy (including a coffeemaker and grinder, blender, toaster, mixer, and slow cooker). The six-person table is positioned before a large picture window so you can enjoy the gorgeous views of the golf course and surrounding evergreens as you dine.

To get even closer to the great outdoors, head out the great room's sliding glass doors to the patio. There, you'll find a lovely four-person dining set and a gas grill for summer barbecues. You'll love breathing in the fresh mountain air and taking in the views, and there are even two extra loungers on the front patio for guests who like a little more peace and quiet as they curl up with a good book in the sunshine.

The condo is also well-suited for a working vacation or extended stay, with a washer/dryer and high-speed Internet access provided. Of course, all the amenities of Resort at the Mountain are just outside the Clear Hills complex; enjoy an early-morning tee time, then spend the afternoon at the resort spa, where your stay at the condo entitles you to a 20% discount. There are a few restaurants on-site, with a handful more in nearby Welches and dotted along Highway 26, and a very well-stocked Thriftway grocery store sits just around the corner.

In the winter, you'll find nearly endless skiing, snowboarding, snowshoeing, and cross-country skiing opportunities within thirty minutes of your front door (the closest ski resort being SkiBowl, just twenty minutes up the highway). At any time of year, the National Forest and wilderness areas offer amazing hikes, along with seasonal catch-and-release fishing on the Salmon River.

If you happening to be traveling with a larger group or would like even more space to spread out, consider booking this lovely getaway together with its neighbor, our Clear Creek Cabin!

