Mountain paradise with all the conveniences of home

This mountain paradise of a three bedroom Welches vacation rental is tucked away near the Mt. Hood National Forest. You'll enjoy a rustic elegance here - from the leather sofa with graphic design throw pillows to the immense brick fireplace and slated, wood-beamed ceiling. Everyone in your group will be charmed by the stylish decor and wowed by this vacation home's perfect wooded location.

Whether you finish the day in front of a roaring fire sipping mugs of hot cocoa or with a relaxing soak in the outdoor hot tub, this Mt. Hood cabin will make you feel right at home. In the living room, beneath the decorative iron chandelier, you can also settle back for a DVD on the flat screen TV (there's basic cable as well).

Although there are plenty of restaurants nearby, you won't mind eating in here at all! The cozy dining area sits in front of a charming cast iron wood stove and the kitchen is a well-laid out, stylish space with stainless steel appliances and a tiled counter. Skylights let in lots of natural light while you chop vegetables or stir sauces. And if you need extra seating, the counter doubles as an attractive breakfast bar.

This beautiful home has a lot of space to find a quiet spot. A small sitting room near the kitchen has another TV and some comfortable furniture. Perfect for an afternoon of reading and sipping an Oregon pinot noir. This room also has access to a loft - a great spot for kids to nap or play.

When it's time to turn in, three bedrooms feature gorgeous shabby-chic details like floral linens, chandeliers, and antique furniture. The master bedroom has a queen bed, and outdoor access through sliding doors with a picturesque view of the tree-filled yard. Another bedroom has a queen bed, and the final room has an elegant layout with a twin sized bed. Two bathrooms are located throughout the home for easy sharing. This beautiful mountain getaway will sleep up to seven gets comfortably, with a maximum occupancy of eight.

Out on the deck, aside from a gas grill and outdoor furniture, there's a hot tub for relaxing after a day on the slopes, and lots of room in the beautifully-landscaped yard for the kids and dog to play! Other great amenities at this Mt. Hood vacation rental include an outdoor fireplace, table tennis, a washer and dryer, and an iPod dock.

When you stay here, you'll want to bring your hiking boots or your snowshoes, depending on the time of year! Surrounded by the lush Mt. Hood National Forest, there are hiking and biking trails everywhere. After you pick up a trail map at the ZigZag Ranger Station, you'll see that there are endless possibilities. Other outdoor options include fishing in the Sandy River or an afternoon of golf at The Resort at the Mountain, which is practically right across the street.

In winter, make the short 17-mile drive to Timberline Lodge for a day of skiing, followed by a nice dinner out. Other area resorts include Mt. Hood Meadows and Mt. Hood Skibowl - both are less than a 30 minute drive away. The surrounding national forest lands are loaded with trails for snowshoeing, cross-country skiing, and even snowmobiling. And after a fun-packed winter day, return to Foxglove Falls retreat for cocktails in front of the fire, followed by a cozy soak in the hot tub.

This elegant and sleekly rustic Welches vacation home offers the best of both worlds - modern amenities with a charming cabin-in-the-woods aesthetic. Perfect for a family getaway or a ski trip with friends, come explore the Mt. Hood area in style.

**Unfortunately, Pets are no longer allowed at this home at the owners request.

