Located in the prime Government Camp area, this 2 bedroom with loft, 2.5 bath Chalet at Collins Lake on Mt Hood will have you hitting the slopes at all the major Mt. Hood ski resorts in no time. Skibowl is in walking distance, and Timberline and Mt Hood Meadows are just minutes away. When you're not skiing, you can relax at the Creekside Lodge where you'll find a indoor common space equipped with a massive wood burning hearth, sauna, year-round heated pool, hot tub, and another spring fed hot tub nestled creekside underneath the trees. Downtown Government Camp, full of restaurants and shops, and where you'll also find rental shops, a grocery store, post office, and museum, is just a short walk away. You can also commute to the slopes by shuttle bus from downtown.

On the main level, there's plenty of room for everyone to spread out in the living room in front of the large gas fireplace to watch television or a movie on the 50'' HDTV, listen to music on the stereo, read, or play games. The kitchen is fully equipped with stainless steel appliances including a gas range. The picnic style dining room table can seat up to 8 and there is additional bar stool seating across the kitchen counter. In the warmer months, you can enjoy a BBQ on the deck overlooking the woods.

On the upper floor, you will find two bedrooms, one loft and two full bathrooms. The master bedroom has a queen bed facing a window view of the woods, and a full private bath with tub. The second bedroom has a twin over full bunk bed and a large closet. The loft is adjacent to the second bedroom and has a twin over full bunk bed. There is a full bath located in the hall between the bedrooms.

The ground floor has a heated garage with room for two cars, a air hockey table, plus bikes to use during the warmer months. There's plenty of room for storing your equipment.

