This cozy Welches vacation rental is a fabulous, year-round recreational hot spot!

Although this rental sits right on the fairway, there is more than golf to enjoy when you make this getaway your home away from home on the mountain! In the winter, you'll be within half an hour of Skibowl, Mt. Hood Meadows, and Timberline Lodge for skiing, snowboarding, sledding, and more. The surrounding National Forest is full of trails for snowshoeing and hearty winter hikes, and your access to the Resort at the Mountain amenities allows you to warm up in the hot tub or sauna after a day in the snow!

For a golfer, Welches should be holy ground, considering it was the site of Oregon's very first golf course in 1928. And when you, your family, or group stay at this beautiful mountain home in the warmer months, the fairway is literally your backyard. Just grab your clubs, step off the back porch, and tee-up!

On a sunny day, the spacious living room is warm and inviting, bathed in light through the skylights and floor-to-ceiling windows. In summer, the same large windows beautifully display the vibrant greens of the golf course. In winter, as you sit in front of a crackling fire in the huge wood fireplace with rock facade, you just might feel like you're in the great hall of an old estate. But this lovely home is anything but old. Not only will you have cable TV, dual DVD/VHS player, a CD player, and a stereo, you'll be able to hop on the laptop as well with the free WIFI.

After a long day of skiing or snowboarding, soak away your cares in the jetted tub in the upstairs bathroom, then curl up on the couch in the cinema room with a bowl of popcorn and watch your favorite movie.

Finding an eating spot in Welches shouldn't be a problem. Step out for haute cuisine at the beautiful Altitude Restaurant (part of the Resort on the Mountain complex), or choose from one of 12 other restaurants around Welches with every type of fare from pizza to salmon.

If you feel like cooking, this home has everything you'll need. It's fully stocked. With an electric range, lots of counter space, a dishwasher and disposal, the designated chef will have no trouble - from prep to cleanup - whipping up something great. Gather 'round the oval table in the adjacent dining room with plenty of room for six. When it's warm, step out on the back deck and fire up the gas grill. There, you'll find a small and beautiful tree-lined yard. Watch the golfers playing just steps away.

Don't let the two bedrooms fool you; the Fairway Retreat sleeps 10 comfortably. The master king suite has a private attached bathroom with a shower/tub combination, double sinks, and a giant walk-in closet. The second bedroom, upstairs, has a wonderful queen bed and a dresser in the closet with lots of storage room.

But that's not all! After a challenging night of board games, pull out the queen sofa bed in the loft. The cinema room also has a pull-out queen sofa bed and the sectional in the living room has a full size pullout.

On the main floor is a half bath and a full laundry room with a washer and dryer and wash sink to make laundry day a swift and easy task.

Your stay at Fairway Retreat comes with two free passes to the Resort at the Mountain Community, your key to the wealth of activities available at the resort. Along with the 27-hole championship golf course and 18-hole putting course, you'll have access to the resort's full-service spa, fitness center, croquet and lawn bowling court, sand volleyball and badminton courts, children's playground, and outdoor pool (enclosed and heated seasonally).

And that's just the resort! Eagle Creek Golf Course is about a half-hour away and Springwater Golf Course, in Estacada, is about 45 minutes. Since Welches is right next to Mount Hood National Forest, you'll be close to all the hiking, biking, fishing, its sixty square miles of forested mountains, lakes, and streams. For skiers, the home is 20 minutes from Skibowl, and 30 minutes from Mt. Hood Meadows and Timberline Lodge, making it an ideal Mt. Hood vacation home anytime of year!

