We chose this house based on the proximity to the resort (everything is walking distance) and the fact that in photos the house looks less adorned than many others. With small children, less adored is a great feature. The house was a great size for us and felt safe, except for a large area rug that is curling at the edges which resulted in multiple trips by children and adults alike.

The description when we booked said there were 2 bedrooms plus 2 sofa beds and the house comfortably sleeps 8. When we received our check in instructions a week before our stay, the sofa beds were changed to air mattresses and our hope was that they were the high quality fairly comfortable ones. They were not. The house has 2 very comfortable beds in the bedrooms, and 2 air very basic air mattresses that you can use in extra rooms with big skylights overhead. Great for daytime, not good for kids if you want them to sleep past dawn or nap during the day.

There was a power outage at the resort during our stay. The home had one working battery-powered lantern (whew!) and one battery-less flashlight (boo). We lit a fire in the wood burning fireplace but had to put it out as the smoke backed up and came into the living room and quickly drifted upstairs to the bedrooms. The flue was open, so the chimney may be blocked and in need of a cleaning.

Still, this house was a good place for us to stay, but the fireplace needs attention and the air mattresses were disappointing.

We enjoyed several special days with our two grown children, their spouses, and our two new granddaughters.  The layout of the living room, adjacent eating area, and kitchen lend themselves to good conversation.  Instructions for check-in were easy to follow; we found everything clean and in good condition.  The kitchen is well equipped.  It was a real plus to be within walking distance to all of the activities at the Resort at the Mountain.  It was important to me when I selected this home that we would have access to the resort. This home provides you with a pass.  One suggestion:  put a bed in the second upstairs bedroom instead of using a pullout.

