Pet-friendly cabin in the woods with private hot tub!

With a private hot tub and warm, inviting atmosphere, this cozy Brightwood vacation rental is within an easy drive of ski slopes - and just across the street from beautiful hiking trails at the Wildwood Recreation Site!

The cabin is surrounded by fir, pine, and cedar trees, making the back porch a fragrant spot to sip your morning coffee in the fresh mountain air as you listen to the Sandy River rushing by. If it's chilly, skip the coffee and wake up with an invigorating dip in the hot tub instead!

Inside, you'll have all the comforts of home as well - a cozy gas fireplace, complimentary Internet, and a TV with DVD/VCR. (There's a well-stocked video store just down the road.) And, of course, a view of the forest is never far away through the wide windows.

Need a big breakfast before you head up the mountain to the ski slopes? This well-stocked kitchen has you covered: not only is there a new stove, microwave, and dishwasher, there's also a bagel toaster, coffee pot, waffle iron, and food processor! Serve it all up around the big wooden table with room for six (two more can cozy up to the bar on the comfortable, cushioned stools). If you feel like preparing dinner at home, head outside and barbecue on the gas grill. There's also a fire pit as well for late-night s'mores! All the groceries you might need are within easy reach too - Thriftway is just two miles up the highway, with restaurants for dining out even closer to home (wild boar tacos and a pitcher of margaritas at El Burro Loco, anyone?).

While the cabin technically only has one bedroom, it's been carefully furnished to make it comfortable for up to six guests to share! The first-floor bedroom has a queen bed, and the living room has a full-sized sofabed. Upstairs in the loft, you'll find a set of twin bunk beds and a full-sized futon. There's a full bathroom on the first floor, and a convenient half-bath up in the loft to make mornings run smoothly. The loft even has access to an upper-level deck where you can enjoy the views through the forest canopy (the perfect perch for birdwatchers!).

Your stay at Wildwood will put you close to all the activities, summer and winter, the Mt. Hood area has to offer. Of course, with the Sandy and Salmon Rivers nearby, you're going to need your rod and tackle box. Cyclists: There are no less than 17 bike trails of varying difficulty nearby. And since you're in Mount Hood National Forest, there's plenty of hiking trails, kayaking, canoeing, and horseback riding. Skiers: There are four ski resorts nearby where you can also ski cross country, snowboard, snowshoe, tube, snowmobile, or just relax on a sleigh-ride.

This Mt. Hood vacation rental is even dog-friendly, with a nightly pet fee. Please note that since the cabin is in a residential neighborhood with full-time neighbors, it does come with a strictly enforced six-person limit and noise ordinance... i.e., parties are not allowed.

For a relaxing getaway on the mountain, look no further than this comfortable, cozy Mt. Hood vacation rental!

