Ideal for weddings, retreats, reunions, and all sorts of large gatherings, this Sandy vacation rental is an enormous 26-acre property surrounded by lush forests, the beautiful Sandy River, and a gorgeous landscape that will make your event truly unforgettable. Plus, with space for 48 overnight guests and many more during daytime events, amenities such as a pool and hot tub, and ample outdoor spaces, this is an incredibly unique facility that has much to offer.

Located about two miles east of Sandy, along the banks of the lovely Sandy River, the Hull Park & Retreat is well known as a foundation for the blind but is also available to the public for one-of-a-kind events. Conveniently located just 40 minutes from both downtown Portland and the Portland International Airport, as well as 45 minutes from skiing at Timberline Lodge, it's within easy reach of many area attractions,while still enjoying a quiet and serene location just outside of charming Sandy.

This retreat offers a total of 24 dorm-style bedrooms  to house overnight guests. Twenty-two rooms each feature two twin-size beds,  and there is an additional one room with a  queen bed and another with a full-size bed.  Altogether, there will be comfortable sleeping spaces for a whopping 48 guests. This is a pet-friendly property, though please note that additional fees apply, including a $10 nightly, per-pet (with a $40 minimum per stay) charge.

A commercial kitchen is provided, as well as three smaller kitchens so you can hire a caterer or prepare food to feed all these hungry vacationers. Around the facility you will also enjoy WiFi access and entertainment including televisions and a game room with a foosball table, air hockey, and more. The Rainbow Lodge provides a large indoor space with a lounge, kitchen, and dining area. There is even an indoor swimming pool  and a 12-person hot tub, so don't forget your swimsuits!

The grounds of the Hull Park & Retreat are well-manicured and offer plenty of places for large gatherings and small, intimate groups alike. Here you will find playgrounds, riverfront trails, gardens, a picturesque gazebo, and plenty of areas for groups to congregate. There is a covered area with gas grills and picnic tables that can accommodate up to 200 people. Take a stroll around the aptly named Gardens of Enchantment, which showcase beautiful features that appeal to all five senses. At night, sit around the enormous firepit and roast marshmallows and tell stories.

Because this facility has so much space and areas that can accommodate groups of all sizes, it is a perfect place for large gatherings. Whether you're planning a family reunion, wedding, conference, church retreat, work gathering, or any other type of celebration or meeting, Hull Park & Retreat is well-equipped to accommodate large groups in style and comfort.

Please note that there is ample parking space for many vehicles, though groups with more than 25 cars will need to hire attendants to ensure safety. There is so much beauty around the property that you may be content to leave your cars parked and enjoy the peace and quiet of this forested area. Take a short drive up or downriver to an access point on the Sandy River, where you can find a shallow area to splash around, or even go fishing or kayaking in the river. Around the region are many fantastic hiking trails of various difficulty levels, and you can also find excellent trails for mountain biking.

With Mt. Hood towering to the east, you can take a scenic drive up the mountain, or even head up to Timberline Lodge for some wintertime skiing. Elsewhere in the area are lakes, streams, and nearly endless forested landscape to enjoy, so bring your camera! And, with the city of Sandy so close, you will have restaurants, grocery stores, shops, and other businesses available nearby.

If you're looking for a place for a large gathering, check out this enormous and amenity-packed facility near Sandy!

