This cozy ski studio condo boasts one of the best locations in Government Camp: the classic Thunderhead Lodge!

As one of ten units in the historic 1941 lodge (originally built as the terminal for a gondola between the town & Timberline), your stay includes access to community amenities like a heated geothermal year-round pool, a rec room with wood-burning fireplace, wet bar, pool table and foosball, coin-operated laundry facilities, and outstanding views of Mt. Hood and Ski Bowl from the wraparound decks.

Your own private getaway within the lodge is fully equipped with everything you might need to enjoy a ski getaway or mountain biking weekend for up to four guests. There is a comfortable queen bed and a sleeper sofa and a full bath, plus a cable TV with DVD player for relaxing movie nights. The free wi fi is available on the first floor of the complex only.

The kitchen has all the essentials: fridge, oven with stovetop, microwave, coffeemaker, and enough pots, pans, dishes, and utensils to whip up a hearty breakfast before a day on the mountain. Of course, if you don't feel like cooking, the brewpub and restaurants of Government Camp are just a short walk from your door.

You can walk to skiing at SkiBowl, or drive just a few miles further up the mountain to Timberline and Mt. Hood Meadows! In the summer, the area is surrounded by hiking and biking trails, alpine lakes, wildflower-filled meadows, and amazing scenic vistas of the mountain. Stay in the heart of it all here at the Thunderhead Lodge!

