Escape to a peaceful spot near Mt. Hood, right off the Sandy River and Hackett Creek, at this beautiful two bedroom Rhododendron vacation home. This home has a lot of character, including knotty pine accents and a slanted, wood beamed ceiling. You'll have charming creekside views, a private hot tub, and a great location near Timberline Ski Area, Mt. Hood Skibowl, and Mt. Hood Meadows!

The interior is rustically elegant with a cabin-in-the-woods motif. There are 20-foot tall ceilings and a wall of windows in the main living space that overlook Hackett Creek and the surrounding Mt. Hood National Forest. Decorative table lamps give this space a warm glow, as does the gas fireplace - perfect for both warmth and ambiance. Like a private mountain lodge, the walls are decorated with vintage snowshoes, skis, landscape paintings, and hunting memorabilia. On chilly evenings, you'll want to start a fire, settle back onto the red sofa, and watch a DVD on the flat screen TV - in addition, there's also a shelf full of books for borrowing.

A dining room in this large open space seats four and when it's time for meals, the full kitchen has everything you'll need, including a dishwasher! Put together a dish of vegetable lasagna, roast a rack of lamb, or just use the microwave to heat up leftovers. Since this area is also open to the living room, it's easy to socialize while making dinner.

Just out the door in the dining area, you'll find a delightful stone path that leads out to the hot tub and deck overlooking the Hackett Creek. After a day of skiing on the slopes or hiking a trail near the Sandy River, come back for a relaxing soak in the hot tub. Right outside the house, another deck - this one wraparound - has outdoor seating, a table for meals, and a fenced backyard area. This is a lovely spot to have morning coffee, afternoon tea, or even an after-dinner glass of port. There's also a gas grill for nice weather cookouts!

A large bedroom on the main level is light and airy, with a queen sized bed, more gorgeous knotty pine walls, ceiling beams, and a lovely wrought iron bed frame. Let the sun streaming through the windows wake you up each morning. There are bedside tables and lamps for extra convenience, so you'll always have a spot for your phone, glasses, or the book that you're reading.

Across from the main level bedroom, a small mudroom has a stackable washer and dryer, to keep everyone in clean and warm clothes during your Mt. Hood getaway. The bathroom is also located downstairs and has a tub and shower combination.

Upstairs in the loft, a second bedroom has an additional queen bed, slated, wood ceilings, and access to a deck overlooking the front yard. This room is cozy and outdoorsy in its theme, and in a hidden crawlspace, there's a futon for kids to play, nap, or spend a quiet afternoon reading. This mountain retreat will comfortably sleep up to four guests. Other amenities include a stereo, CD Player, and WiFi for checking email and staying in touch while away.

On the decks and in the backyard, you'll have beautiful views of mossy trees, the creek, and forest ferns. You'll find peace and tranquility here, as well as adventure out on the nearby trails. Depending on the time of year, there's hiking and biking paths, as well as snowshoeing and cross-country skiing trails. For a fun afternoon, challenge yourself with a hike to Ramona Falls. This seven mile loop trail heads though lush scenery, and scenic footbridges.

In winter, Timberline, Mt. Hood Meadows, Summit Ski Area, and Mt. Hood Skibowl are all within a 20-40 minute drive away from this creekside vacation home. Mt. Hood Meadows is only 28 miles east and has a variety of terrain, 85 runs, and 140 acres devoted to night skiing! And on the drive back, if you don't feel like preparing something at home, Highway 26 has a number of meal options. Try The Rendezvous in Welches for rib eye steaks and salmon fish and chips or Wrapitude, just down the road, for a quick, healthy snack.

This spotless and well cared for Rhododendron vacation rental makes a great home base for exploring the majestic Mt. Hood area. Whether you come to ski, hike, fish in the nearby rivers and streams, or just relax, this Hackett Creek Hideaway will thoroughly charm you with its mountain lodge style and cozy furnishings.

