With all the modern comforts of home, access to resort amenities, and delightfully rustic furnishings and decor, this attractive and comfortable two bedroom chalet offers something special for everyone in your group!

Curl up by the cozy gas fireplace while you enjoy a movie on the 46" flat-screen TV with DVD player; prepare a gourmet meal in the chef's kitchen; or head to the year-round heated swimming pool or hot tub to soothe your muscles after a long day on the slopes (did we mention that Skibowl is just a short walk away?). Maybe you'd rather stroll to Government Camp's brewery for a fresh IPA or oatmeal stout, or head to the local outfitters to rent snowshoes or sign up for snowboard camp. Like we said - something for everyone!

In the living room, sink into the comfortable sofa after your busy day exploring the mountain. The gas fireplace adds a bit of cozy mountain ambiance, even while you enjoy the top-notch cable package on the flat-screen TV: movie fans will find seven HBO channels, and sports lovers can enjoy ESPN & ESPN2. You won't miss one email with our high speed internet available throughout the property.

With updated stainless steel appliances and plenty of granite countertops, the kitchen makes cooking for a group a delight. The cabinets are fully stocked with all of the pots and pans, dinnerware, cooking utensils, and dishes you may need, along with a few select countertop appliances (such as a coffee grinder and blender). Of course, the dishwasher makes clean-up a breeze. Take your cooking out to our balcony with our fantastic gas grill and breathe in the fresh mountain air while grilling!

The well-appointed vacation rental condo sleeps six guests very comfortably. The master bedroom has a luxurious king-sized bed, complete with Tempur-Pedic memory foam mattress for a wonderful night's sleep. The second bedroom has both a queen-sized bed, also with memory foam, and a set of twin bunk beds, making it ideal for either kids or a second couple. This bedroom has its own 32" flat-screen TV, so no disagreements will arise on movie nights.

And, you don't have to leave your dog pals at home, but please note that there is an additional pet fee.

As part of the lovely Collins Lake community, this stylish vacation rental condo includes complimentary access to a heated swimming pool, hot tubs, sauna, and luxurious clubhouse. Trails wind throughout the 28-acre complex, perfect for snowshoeing in the winter or casual hikes in the summer.

Beyond the boundaries of Collins Lake, all the adventures of Mt. Hood await. The town of Government Camp is an easy walk from your front door, with plenty of dining and shopping; make sure to drive just a few miles further up the mountain to visit the historic Timberline Lodge.  This property also includes a heated two car garage with a washer and dryer to dry out those wet ski clothes.

In the warmer months, the Mt. Hood area is paradise for hikers, mountain bikers, fishermen, kayakers, and nature lovers of all kinds. Winter, of course, brings excellent snowfall for skiers (both downhill and cross-country), snowboarders and snowshoers, as well as ideal conditions for those who prefer hot-chocolate drinking and cozy book-reading by the fire. Remember, there is something special for everyone here at this wonderful Collins Lake getaway!

