Quintessential cabin. That's what you'll say when you feast your eyes on this quaint little two bedroom Rhododendron vacation rental. Though its charming exterior says "rustic," step inside and see how imaginative design, great amenities, and an unsparing taste for elegance has made this little place into the proverbial diamond in the rough.

Poised between Steel Creek to the east and the Zigzag River to the west, take the nearby footbridge over the Zigzag where you can cross into the tiny hamlet of Rhododendron, a burg popular with ornithologists and close to winter spots like Skibowl and Timberline Lodge.

This is a sweet remodel! With vaulted ceilings, track lighting and large windows that invite the sunlight, this otherwise small space is liberated, cheery, and classy, giving it the illusion of a much bigger home. Throw a log on the fire, snuggle up on the plush couch and slip one of your favorite DVDs into the player or pick one from the library. There's also a big flat-screen with cable. With the beautiful hardwood floors and unfinished paneling, you'll feel like you're in an upscale resort (without the crowds!). After a long hike or a day on the slopes, slide into the bubbly warmth of the private hot tub.

This Rhododendron vacation rental sleeps four comfortably. It has two bedrooms, one with a queen bed, the other a full. There's also a crib for the little tike, The bedrooms are tastefully decorated with comfy linens and pillows. It has two nicely decorated bathrooms, one of which is also paneled and has a walk-in shower.

Like the rest of this vacation rental cabin, the kitchen is a balance of space, efficiency and elegance. In addition to an up-to-date stove, fridge, and fixtures, there's a microwave, a waffle iron, and a coffee maker and grinder. Serve it up at the lovely, modern dining set with room for four. Out on the deck you'll find a gas grill for a barbeque. When the weather's warm, head out to the backyard fire pit and enjoy the fresh mountain air with your toasted marshmallows and s'mores!

Close to two of the official Oregon Cascades Birding Trails, Rhododendron is a go-to spot for ornithologists. Huckleberry Haven is just 15 minutes to skiing at Skibowl and historic Timberline Lodge in nearby Government Camp where you can experience the area's rich history. You'll be close to all the great sites and recreational activities you'll find in the Mount Hood area, including world-class fishing. With its proximity to three rivers,(the Sandy River is very close by) Rhododendron is a haven for fly-fishing, offering up steelhead and salmon as the prize. And since you'll be smack dab in Mount Hood National Forest, you'll enjoy the benefit of 60 square miles of forest, streams, and lakes which, of course, means plenty of places to hike, bike, kayak, and just savor the abundance and beauty of the Mount Hood area.

So come to this charming Rhododendron vacation rental cabin where your cabin experience comes with a dash of class and panache!

