Explore all the stunning sights around Mt. Hood when you stay at this pleasantly-decorated one bedroom Welches vacation rental. In a quiet neighborhood, you'll be right next door to The Resort at the Mountain's historic golf course and the peaceful serenity of the Mt. Hood National Forest. With its golf green views and modern amenities, this laid-back getaway has everything you'll need for a weekend (or more!) in the mountains.

After a day of hiking, return to this Fairway Estates for wine and snacks on the glass coffee table. Or, turn your attention to the flat screen TV for some cable and a DVD, while you warm yourself in front of the fireplace. There's also WiFi so you can stay connected, research restaurants, or get directions to the nearest ski resort.

The full kitchen has all the major appliances you'll require (including a dishwasher) and lots of counter space. Perfect whether you're putting together a quick breakfast before heading out on a hike or preparing a multi-course meal at the end of an adventure-filled day. And since this main living area is all one open space, you can still enjoy the fireplace while sitting down to a meal at the dining table.

When you head off to bed, everyone will have a spot to lay their head. There's a queen sized bed, as well as a twin in the bedroom (also a second TV for late night channel surfing), and the sofa in the living room pulls out to a bed. This Mt. Hood vacation rental will easily sleep up to four guests. And if you have pets, up to two dogs (under 30-pounds each) can come on vacation as well with a $10 per day, per pet fee($40 minimum per stay).

But that's not all - this condo has a few more amenities! Right in the complex, there's a small playground for the kids, and you'll have a washer and dryer right in the unit. There'll be no worrying about keeping your clothes clean while out exploring here! (Please note that while this home is located next to the Resort on the Mountain, it does not include access to amenities like the pool and spa.)

Area hikes are plentiful, so you'll definitely want to pack your trail shoes. Ride your bike along the Sandy Ridge Trail or take the dog for an after-dinner walk around the neighborhood. There's fishing in the nearby Sandy River and on nights you don't want to cook, you can walk to The Resort at the Mountain's restaurant Altitude or make the short drive to the main drag for pizza and beer at the colorful ZigZag Inn. And of course, there's always world-class golfing at The Courses.

Downhill skiing and snowboarding are close by at three area ski resorts - Timberline, Mt. Hood Meadows, and Mt. Hood Skibowl are all are within a 24 mile drive. There's also cross-country skiing, snowboarding, and snowmobiling right nearby.

This Welches vacation getaway is perfect for both your wallet and sense of adventure. Year-round there's much to do, and at the end of the day, you'll have a comfortable condo to call home.

