Step back in time with this peaceful three bedroom home, set along the historic Barlow Trail. Take a stroll on the footbridge that is set over the babbling stream (the path is about 150-feet from the driveway), relax by the warming fireplace, or prepare breakfast in the antique wood-burning stove. The Stove and Stream is the ultimate private getaway!

Hackett Creek along the front and a mountain stream running under the cabin create soothing sounds and mountain fresh water to drink. The water is filtered and tastes great!

The kitchen has a blend of old and new with a wood-burning South Bend Malleable Range  (please note that the antique wood stove is the only way to cook/bake in the kitchen), and an electric dishwasher. You can enjoy your meals in the kitchen or in the dining room. Both have seating for six with views of the meandering stream. Enjoy your morning coffee or evening wine watching the water go by, from your choice of the front or back deck.

The main level of the cabin has a cozy living room, making it the perfect place to tell stories, read a book or grab a game off the shelf to play with your family and friends. You will also find a bedroom and bathroom on the main level. The log staircase will lead you to the upper bedrooms. There you will have amazing views of the stream.

Looking for some adventure during your stay? The Sandy Ridge Trail System provides new recreation opportunities for mountain bikers and hikers to explore the foothills of the Cascade Range. As of July 2010, roughly 6.5 miles are open to public access. The trail head parking is only minutes away from the Stove & Stream Cabin. You have Ski Bowl and Timberline lodge approximately 20 minutes away for your sliding fun. Also a view point for the Sandy River is a short drive away.

Come, step back in time with the Stove & Stream Cabin. This is truly a vacationer's delight!

