Charming A-frame right near golf, close to Mt. Hood skiing!

This charming and classic Welches vacation rental is a mid-century A-frame nestled near the Mt. Hood National Forest, but still adjacent to the main road for easy exploring. With it's one bedroom and loft, you'll have a space for up to eight guests and you can even bring along the family pets!

With a location that is sure to appeal to golfers, skiers, and outdoor adventurers alike, you'll be right near the Resort at the Mountain (literally steps away), for golfing at The Courses or a nice meal out at Altitude or Mallards.  Mt. Hood SkiBowl is only 17 miles away and in summer, it's the same distance to Trillium Lake for kayaking!

Inside this well-designed cabin, you'll find a comfortable floor plan with a cozy living room for relaxing after a day of hiking or skiing. Settle back on one of the plaid sofas (one is a sleeper sofa) for a night of cable TV or pop some popcorn and watch a movie on DVD.

The full kitchen has everything you'll need (even a dishwasher), so you can plan a hearty family meal or a festive brunch or two during your vacation. And when it's time to enjoy your feast, the dining table has seats for six and in the kitchen, there's an additional table. No matter if you're sitting down to pancakes in the morning or an after-dinner poker game, there are spots for everyone!

Out on the deck, you can admire the surrounding trees while you prepare steaks on the grill. There's plenty of outdoor seating for an al fresco meal or to admire the blooming rhododendrons.

Downstairs, there is one bedroom with a queen bed and deck access, as well as a full bathroom. Upstairs in the loft, you'll have an addition queen bed and two twin beds (trundle-style). On this upper level, there is also a private balcony - perfect for some quiet reading or a morning cup of coffee. This home will comfortably sleep up to eight guests and dogs are welcome for an additional fee.

Other amenities at this comfortable, retro cabin in the woods include WiFi,  three TVs, a private washer and dryer, and a poker set for game nights. And for the history buffs in your group - once upon a time, this historic A-frame was the gift shop for the resort next door.

This ideal location is right in the middle of all the happenings at the popular Resort at the Mountain! Schedule a game of golf, get a facial at the spa, or plan a special meal out. You'll also be near great hiking - the Hunchback Trailhead, the start of one of Oregon's steepest hikes, is only a couple of miles from your door.

Also just down the road are neighboring mountain towns like Rhododendron and Government Camp. In winter, head to Mt. Hood SkiBowl, Mt. Hood Meadows, or Timberline for a day on the ski slopes - all are within a 24-mile drive.

Come to ski, to hike, or just to relax at this comfortable and cozy Mt. Hood vacation rental!

