This modern mountain lodge is a peaceful yet fun-filled spot to experience all the natural beauty and outdoors adventures Mt. Hood has to offer!

With exposed timber beams criss-crossing the vaulted ceilings, a spiral staircase leading up to a spacious loft, and a fireplace set into a wall of exposed brick, you know from the moment you enter that this lodge is something special. The living area is open and spacious, with windows overlooking the surrounding pine trees and a media center fully equipped for rainy days. Curl up on the sectional sofa by the fire with a movie on the TV, or power up the Wii for more interactive entertainment.

Behind the living area, the open floor plan continues to the dining area and roomy kitchen. The table for six sits near a potbelly stove for warm family dinners, with a few stools lining the breakfast bar in the kitchen. The chef in the family will appreciate the ample counterspace, perfect for making use of the cabinets' hearty supply of cooking gear and dinnerware. And yes, alert the dish-doer in the family that there is a dishwasher provided for easy clean-up! With the Thriftway in Welches only five miles away, you don't need to worry about packing in groceries (or even good beer!) for your trip to the mountain.

Through the living area's beautiful French doors is the master bedroom, with a queen bed, mirror-topped dressing table, and an attached bath. Up the spiral staircase is the spacious loft. There are two sleeping areas with another queen bed and a twin-over-full bunk, respectively, with a shared bathroom between them.

With an extra futon tucked away on the lower level, up to eight guests can share the space quite comfortably; the laundry room's washer/dryer make sharing the space easy and packing light! Wireless Internet is also provided for working vacations and those who like to stay connected.

While the house itself is beautiful and relaxing, the backyard may be the biggest draw! There is a covered hot tub with plenty of room for four adults.  The grounds are large and fully fenced, providing a safe place for youngsters to build forts and play in the snow on winter days or take a ride on the zip line. There's also a barbeque, outdoor eating area, and a fire pit for roasting marshmallows on summer evenings. As part of the Timberline Rim community, the house even includes access to a seasonal swimming pool, tennis and basketball courts, and easy access to trails along the Sandy River.

Of course, Mt. Hood itself is the ultimate playground! Just minutes from the home is the Sandy Ridge Trail System, providing epic recreation opportunities for mountain bikers and hikers to explore the foothills of the Cascade Range. The historic Timberline Lodge is approximately 20 minutes away for your skiing, snowboarding, or very scenic hot chocolate-sipping. For the fisherman at heart, the Sandy River is a hop, skip, and a jump away, offering you world-class salmon and steelhead fishing. This river has gained a reputation among fly fishing enthusiasts as a very demanding arena to test the best of skills.

Summer or winter, Mt. Hood has something special for everyone, and the same goes for the Mountain Meadow Lodge. Book your next Mt. Hood adventure today!

