Relax and retreat into the mountain life with this gorgeous Government Camp vacation rental! With three bedrooms, a private hot tub, and old-school interior, you'll fit right into the Mt. Hood life.

Sure, there are tons of things to do in Government Camp any time of year, but let's face it - it's mostly about the skiing and snowboarding! Ever since Peter Sickler started the first ski run on Multopor Mountain back in 1928, skiing has grown in Government Camp, and nowadays you can choose from world-class slopes at Timberline Lodge, SkiBowl, and Mt. Hood Meadows. This charming cabin, with room for six in the middle of Government Camp, has witnessed much of that growth. From its subtle gingerbread facade outside to the ski memorabilia throughout the interior - this is a place that's seen many skiers come and go, and it wants you to know it.

After a day on the slopes, tuck away the boots, the skis, and the down jackets and hang out in the living room on the comfy leather love seat and sofa. You can recount your downhill daring by the warmth of the propane wood stove in a lodge-like ambiance filled with wood-trussed ceilings, old mugs, and a roughhewn log support that holds up the decor more than the house. But it's not all about nostalgia, this place has some bells and whistles! You'll be able to watch your favorite flicks with the DVD player, shows on the TV with cable, or check your email or make a reservation using the WIFI.

With plenty of room in the fully stocked kitchen, your designated chef(s) will have no problem whipping up a meal for hungry vacationers anxious to hit the slopes, or tired from being on them all day. And when you gather around the wooden table to enjoy your meal, nostalgia looms large in the wonderful, wrap-around collage filled with images of skiing and skiers gone by.

This cozy 1,000 sq ft cabin sleeps six, and features three unique and creative bedrooms. The master bedroom is a large bedroom with bright walls, a queen-size bed and space to spread out all your warm winter wear.  The second bedroom has a classic ski cabin look and features a full bed that is great for a second couple. The third bedroom is a fun, sunlit room with cozy quilts that cover two twin beds - perfect for the kids. All three bedrooms are on the second floor of the home, and the two bathrooms are downstairs.

Government Camp is pretty cool in the summer too, so this cabin is a wonderful place to lounge all year round. There are historic sites like Barlow Trail and Timberline Lodge, and 25 trails around Government Camp for hiking, biking, or just strolling in a beautiful, alpine environment. The Sandy River is nearby, so you can indulge your love of fishing, rafting, kayaking...anything you can do in the summer! Check out one of the five great places to eat in Government Camp or visit some of the shops you'll also find there. Plus, the adorable town of Hood River is just 45 minutes away, so any shopping, dining or bar-hopping you're interested in can be easily done there!

When you stay at Wilcox Cabin, be prepared for fun and the feeling of an old-school cabin in the lovely Mt. Hood forest!

Note: The stairs are steep and the bedrooms are upstairs, bathrooms are on the main Level.

