This secluded, riverfront Parkdale vacation rental is the perfect place to stay while you enjoy the beauty and serenity of nature. With 1.3 acres of land that backs up to the spectacular Hood River, a pet-friendly attitude, and a private hot tub, you will surely have an amazing vacation here!

Located about two miles north of the small, charming town of Parkdale, this home is a quick drive away from small markets and a few restaurants, but you may want to spend all your time at the riverfront vacation house, surrounded by the great outdoors.

With three bedrooms (plus a loft) and two bathrooms, this home has plenty of space for eight guests to vacation here. You are even welcome to bring your dogs along with you! Though a $10 per-pet, nightly fee with a $40 minimum per stay does apply, your furry friends will love sniffing around the property, chasing squirrels, and splashing around in the shallows of the river.

Head inside to discover vaulted ceilings, wooden walls, and a warm, homey atmosphere. The spacious living area has plenty of seating arranged around the cozy river rock fireplace, as well as large windows that offer views of the forested surroundings. With a VHS player, DVD player, and Internet access, guests will have plenty of electronic entertainment in case you wind up needing a break from the quiet of nature!

Bring along groceries and enjoy home-cooked meals during your stay! The full kitchen has all the tools and equipment you may need to prepare food, as well as plenty of space so multiple chefs can maneuver easily. Sit down at the dining room table or the more casual breakfast bar and enjoy a nice meal together before heading out to wade in the river or explore the forest.

The master bedroom has a huge king-size bed where you will sleep soundly. A second bedroom has a soft queen-size bed, and the final bedroom has a twin trundle bed and a full-size bed. Upstairs in the loft area is an additional fold-out futon, so altogether eight guests will have comfortable and warm places to rest at night.

The loft also serves as a fun playroom: watch TV, play foosball, or bring some board games to spread out on the floor. This would be a fantastic area for any children to play while the adults chat in front of the fireplace downstairs. And, with a laundry room, you won't have to worry about anyone getting their clothes dirty while exploring the area.

Outside, the deck is a peaceful place to sit, soak in some sunshine, and enjoy the sound of the breeze rustling through the trees. If you're very still, you may even see a deer walk by! Use the gas grill to cook up a casual lunch of burgers, or step into the private hot tub and let all your troubles melt away in the bubbling water.

With the beautiful Hood River just past your doorstep, you and your guests will love to spend time on your private beach area enjoying the sunshine, wading in the shallower sections of water, and even fishing! You will also enjoy exploring the 1.3 acres of property and looking for wildlife, all while listening to the rippling river and birds singing nearby.

In Parkdale proper, you will have a few small markets to stock up on the basics and a handful of restaurants, including excellent house-made craft beer and pizza at Solera Brewery. For even more options, drive 15 minutes north to the city of Hood River, where you will find many eateries, shops, and activities. And, with Mt. Hood just 30 miles away, you could take a scenic summer drive or a winter trip to enjoy some skiing!

This secluded, peaceful, and spacious Hood River vacation rental is a great place to relax and enjoy your getaway while surrounded by the beauty of nature!

