Quintessential cabin in the woods with stunning views

Step back into a simpler era at this cozy 1920's Mt. Hood vacation rental cabin! Surrounded by cedars trees and just a short walk from the ZigZag River, you may find that time moves a little slower as you curl up by the fireplace here at Old Smokey Cabin.

The most peaceful mornings begin with a mug of hot coffee on the porch in the fresh mountain air. Spend your days strolling through the quiet wooded neighborhood, along the river, or head up to the ski slopes for an adventurous winter's day (Skibowl is only 15 minutes from your door, with Timberline and Mt. Hood Meadows just a bit further). In the evenings, wind down by the fireplace, surrounded by exposed timber beams and rustic decor in the exceptionally cozy living room.

Despite feeling delightfully slow-paced and relaxing, this charming vacation rental home does come equipped with many modern amenities. The kitchen has all the expected appliances, including a dishwasher for easy clean-up and plenty of countertop gadgets like a waffle iron and slow-cooker. A grocery store is less than two miles away in Welches, so you won't need to worry about hauling food up to the mountain. The dining table is tucked just off the kitchen for sit-down meals, and the patio has a gas grill for warm-weather barbecues.

When it comes to technology, you'll find two modest television sets with cable, along with a cabinet of DVDs for movie nights. Wireless Internet access is provided as well.

The lower level of this rustic vacation rental home has the living room with both a propane stove and wood-burning fireplace, the kitchen, and the dining area. There are also two bedrooms downstairs, both with queen beds, and the full bathroom. Upstairs, the loft has both a twin and full bed, and a sitting area that's perfect for kids to hang out, play board games, or watch their own movie selection.

This vacation rental home is perfect for a cozy winter retreat or ski weekend, but it's also fantastic in warmer weather. The surrounding area is full of hiking trails and fishing holes, and the pet-friendly cabin has a wonderful fenced backyard for the family dog. With the ZigZag River just a short walk away, your four-legged companion might think he's found paradise!

Indeed, after a few days of enjoying the simpler pace of life only found in a cozy mountain cabin like Old Smokey, your only problem may be convincing your family to leave!

