This two-bedroom Chef's Chalet vacation rental in scenic Government Camp has room for seven people and one dog, and offers the perfect retreat for the culinary artist in you.

Bring the skis, the snowboard, the fishing gear and your appetite to this beautiful three story chalet in the acclaimed condos at Collins Lake. Geared to the chef in you, this charming vacation rental not only has numerous cookbooks for your perusal and a fully equipped kitchen to make your recipes a reality, you'll enjoy TV with cable and Blu-ray, and access to Collins Lake amenities.

If you're not assisting the designated chef, just settle into one of the comfortable chairs in the living room and savor the aromas wafting from the kitchen. Click on the gas fireplace, turn on new 42 inch cable TV or slide a DVD or CD into the Blu-Ray player. Once you've got that pillow situated just right, put your feet up on the big leather ottoman and wait for the call to "come and get it." Or, step out on the balcony just off the living room and - seasonally relevant drink in hand - enjoy the sylvan scene in front of you. And if you decide to head out to dinner in Government Camp, you can browse restaurant reviews with the complimentary WiFi!

The kitchen has everything your chef will need. With stainless steel refrigerator, stove, and dishwasher, you'll have plenty of counter space and plenty of room to maneuver so you're not bumping into the sous chef. There's also a toaster oven, a full complement of knives easily accessible, and a veritable library of cookbooks from which to choose your next culinary challenge. Pass your steaming creation around the elegant dining table that seats six (a couple more can sit at the bar.) Bon appetit!

After dessert, a good movie, and it's time for bed, this chalet will accommodate seven. For those who need the drone of the TV to put them to sleep, no problem: you'll find a TV in each bedroom. The master suite has a private bath with jetted tub and a view of the adjoining forest. The second bedroom features a queen bed that is great for a second couple and the loft has a bunk bed with a full bed on the bottom and a twin on top for the kids. You're also welcome to bring one dog with you, though please be aware that if you want to bring your furry friend a $10 nightly fee with a $40 minimum per stay will apply.

As part of the resort, your stay comes with access to the amenities at the chalet clubhouse. Grab that novel you've sworn to finish and lounge in front of the grand, Cascadian stone fireplace. Slide into exquisitely hot waters of the two hot tubs, or dive into the year-long pool with heated decks.

When you're ready to venture out beyond the realm of the resort, Skibowl and Government Camp are within walking distance. Have a beer and a snack at Mount Hood Brewing Company. Enjoy a great meal at Charlie's or the Huckleberry Inn. Government Camp is within a half-hour of five different ski resorts. (Take advantage of Vacasa's offer at Mount Hood Meadows). In addition to all the hiking trails, fishing, rafting, available in the area, the resort has its own activities including everything from a half-mile alpine slide, tube hill and kiddy karts at the Mt. Hood Adventure Park, to kayaking, canoe, rafting and hiking tours you can arrange through Mt. Hood Adventure.

So bring your family or group, your well-behaved dog, your equipment, your cookbooks and your appetite and enjoy a stay at the colorful and fun-filled Collins Lake condos in Government Camp.

