Cozy loft tucked in the woods near Govy!

This unique one bedroom loft is a wonderfully romantic yet affordable getaway, close to all the shops and restaurants of Government Camp. Those who like a little more peace and quiet, though, will delight in the home's location on a large private lot with two streams running past.

The loft is located above the garage of an attached home, allowing you to enjoy your own little retreat.

The space has been brilliantly designed to accommodate up to four people, and feels larger than its 600 square feet! In the main living area, a comfy loveseat sits before a TV with DVD player for cozy movie nights.

On the opposite end of the space, the fully remodeled kitchen has all the essentials: full-sized fridge, oven, dishwasher, microwave, coffeemaker, blender, and all the pots and pans, dinnerware, and cooking utensils you might need to prepare meals. The four-person table is perfect for sharing meals or even using as a workspace (wireless Internet is also included in your stay!).

The spacious bedroom has a comfortable queen bed and a ladder leading up to the loft. Younger guests will love climbing up to their own private space each night, and two twin mattresses with fresh linens and warm blankets provide a cozy spot to sleep under the sloped wood-beam ceiling! It's almost like camping in a pup tent -- except, of course, for the nicely appointed bathroom with tub/shower combo. And if one of your extra guests prefers not to climb a ladder, the living area's love seat unfolds into a comfy sleeper sofa as well.

The loft is within easy walking distance of all the attractions in Government Camp, like freshly-brewed pints at the Ice Axe and gear rental at one of the shops in town. Skibowl, of course, is only a bit further across Highway 26, and Timberline is just a 20-minute drive away. The property also sits quite near the base of Mount Hood's historic Glade Trail for a little more out-of-the-ordinary exploration.

