From its pinball machines to the poker table, this beautiful Molalla vacation rental is truly furnished for fun - We have an especially festive offer in store for you!  When you stay at the Molalla River Lodge for five or more nights,you may be able to take advantage of the owner's season tickets to the Portland Trailblazers... Depending on schedule and availability, the pair of tickets includes free parking and great views from a second-level box, right above the Blazers bench! Contact our reservation line for more details and to check availability.

Anytime you stay at this wonderful home on 1 1/3 acres, you'll have a tough choice: "Do we stay in, or go out?" After all, there are two pinball machines, two arcade-style video games, a 60-inch flat panel with Dish TV and surround sound, a PlayStation, and a poker table inside. Then again, not only is the beautiful Molalla River right in your backyard, you can enjoy it either from the eight seat hot tub on the deck, or from the charming patio, complete with a huge brick fireplace. It's a cross between Vegas and a wooded vale, just 45 minutes from downtown Portland.

The living room is loaded with bells and whistles. The kids can test their dexterity on the "The Simpsons" and "The Family Guy" pinball machines, the PlayStation, or the arcade games ("Golden Tee" and "Extreme Hunter"). Settle into the big leather chairs and watch cable TV, your favorite movie on DVD, or just listen to music on CD or the iPod dock. Or, hook into the free WiFi and surf away! Weather permitting, head outside. Mingle on the big deck where you'll not only find a gas grill and a table, but a gorgeous tiled wet-bar that's great for entertaining and will make you feel like you're in a resort!

This lodge-style vacation rental has a big, fully stocked kitchen that includes a deep fryer, an array of spices, lots of counter space and a dishwasher for easy clean-up. The dining table, part of which has bench seating, seats up to 10 comfortably. There's also a picnic table and a patio table with four chairs, so you can enjoy meals inside or out. Firewood is provided. If you'd like to go out, Molalla has 15 places to eat serving everything from enchiladas to eggrolls.

There are three bedrooms in Molalla River Lodge, with one bed in each. The kids will like sleeping on the two air mattresses that are readily available. Along with direct access to the deck through sliding glass doors, the master bedroom has a great view, not to mention a Temperpedic Adjustable California king bed and a flat panel TV with Dish TV and a DVD player. The house is all on one level so it is easily accessible for anyone with mobility problems. There are two full bathrooms, one with a shower stall and one with a tub and shower set up.

If you've got doggie with you, there's a 20-foot dog run in the back. There's even a pen big enough for horses so you can ride on the many trails around the area. As you would expect, the Molalla River Corridor is loaded with river-related activities like rafting and fishing. But Molalla is also known for its famed "Buckeroo Rodeo" where cowboys and cowgirls can tighten their chaps and test their equestrian skills with varying events beginning in April and ending in September. But that's not all! There are five city parks in Molalla, one devoted to skateboarders. Did you ever want to try sky-diving? Well, you can do that in Molalla too. But you have to come here first. Call and reserve your spot at this great lodge today!

