Located right in the middle of Government Camp (and just a few hundred feet from the Summit Ski Area), this home is in an unbelievably perfect spot for lovers of snow sports. Timberline Lodge and its surrounding slopes are a 10-minute drive up the mountain, and Mt. Hood Meadows is just 15 minutes away by car.

This two-bedroom, two-bathroom home has a unique shape - long and thin, with a small but efficient floorplan. The lower level contains a nice, comfortable living room with space for guests to sit around the fun electric fireplace and talk. A full bathroom and a bedroom with a double-size bed are also nestled on the ground floor.

A full kitchen may seem too small at first glance, but when you look closer you will see that it is fully equipped with everything you may need to cook up delicious meals for you and your guests. A mini-fridge even provides a separate place to store extra soda or beer without taking up valuable space in the standard-size fridge.

Upstairs you will find a second living room with lots of seating, a flat screen TV equipped with cable and a DVD player, DVD selection, board games, and a stereo. This home also has WiFi and books to borrow, so you will have no trouble finding ways to keep entertained!

The upper floor also has its own full bathroom with a washer and dryer, which means you won't have to worry about getting your clothes wet or dirty while exploring the area. A second bedroom has a queen-size bed and a lovely balcony to admire the view.

The house sleeps 4 to 6 adults comfortably, but 10 guests may sleep in this home, spread out among the two bedrooms and five futons that fold out into sleeping spaces. The house is perfect for two families with sleeping spaces and bathrooms on each floor. It is also great for a romantic getaway or to head up with a house full of friends to enjoy all that mount hood as to offer. With all the activities beckoning you away from this home, you may not want to spend too much time inside! "

Government Camp is a great place to stay if you love the outdoors. Perched on the side of majestic Mt. Hood, this town has restaurants (including the fabulous Mt. Hood Brewing Company) and a general store, but most people visit to experience the world-class snow sports on Mt. Hood itself. During the colder months, this is a perfect place for skiing, snowboarding, and snowman-building.

In the summer, even though most of the snow has melted on the mountain, there are still many activities to keep busy. Miles of hiking and biking trails crisscross the forested wilderness, offering some of the best views of the region. Nearby lakes such as Timothy Lake (20 miles south) or Clear Lake (10 miles south) offer wonderful summertime swimming, boating, fishing, and picnicking opportunities.

If you crave the amenities of a larger town, take a drive on the beautiful, tree-lined highway west for 30 miles to reach Sandy, which has a huge variety of restaurants, stores, businesses, and an especially amazing donut shop.

While you're out experiencing everything this enchanting, adventure-filled area has to offer, stay at this comfortable and homey Mt. Hood vacation rental with everything you need to enjoy your getaway!

