The little community of Government Camp is not only a doorway to myriad outdoor activities like hiking, fishing, kayaking, biking and climbing, it's also a historic treasure. You can hike or snowshoe up Blossom Trail (one of the original roads) to Timblerline Lodge, the Depression Era building constructed by an army of WPA workers in the '30s. There's skiing up there too, just as there is in nearby Skiibowl and Timberline Ski Area. Mount Hood Meadows is a little farther, about 17 minutes away on the eastern side of Mount Hood.

Collins Lake is kid-friendly, offering attractions like kiddy karts, kiddy canoe, mini golf, and interpretive trail hikes. Birders: nearby Rhododendron is renowned for its feathered inhabitants and has 25 places to take your binoculars and...well, watch! Plenty of golfing over in Welches - the site of the first golf course in Oregon. They're waiting for you to come and tee up. And don't leave without that souvenir: The shops and boutiques in Government Camp are waiting for you too!

So reserve this vacation rental chalet in rugged and beautiful Government Camp and enjoy all the wonders, recreational activities, and rich history of the Mount Hood area.

