The cozy living area is equally suited for long conversations, relaxing in front of the stone-faced fireplace, or TV viewing. With cable and a DVD player, you'll have a lot of entertainment choices here, as well as WiFi. So throw another log on the fire and settle back on one of the leather sofas for a quiet night in.

When you want to fix a meal, the bright, spacious kitchen has all the appliances you'll need, including a dishwasher. There's even a coffee grinder for fresh beans in the morning. You can retreat to the sun room with your mug for a great view of the forest, or if it's nice outside, go out on the deck and the birds will provide a perfect soundtrack for the wonderful view.

The private deck also boasts a hot tub for leisurely soaks and a gas grill for outdoor summer barbecues. There's a picnic table right on the deck for al fresco dining, as well as a second deck right down by the river. Or head out to the outdoor fire pit after dinner for some late night s'mores.

The master bedroom is a rustic, lodge-like sanctuary with a pine log queen sized bed, plaid wallpaper, TV, and sliding glass doors leading out to the deck. A second bedroom has a lovely full sized four poster bed, wainscoting, and elegant decorative touches. And for the kids, a third bedroom with two sets of twin bunk beds means they can have a slumber party every night. This home will sleep up to six guests and has two full bathrooms.

When you want a quiet spot to relax, play games, or read a book, the lower level den is just the spot. You'll have patio access and a bar to enjoy a glass or two of wine, while playing a game of cards. There's also a stereo with a CD player for listening to music.

This Mt. Hood vacation rental is only a short drive from the Mt. Hood Scenic Byway and restaurants like The Rendezvous and the ZigZag Inn. So, even though you do have your own kitchen, dining out is definitely an option during your stay! Also right nearby is golf at The Resort at the Mountain, hiking and biking trails, and rock climbing. In the immediate area, you can even make an appointment for a spa treatment like a river rock massage. Plan an outdoor adventure or get pampered - it's up to you.

Ski season is a popular time to visit, with Timberline Lodge, Mt. Hood Meadows, and Mt. Hood Skibowl all within a 24 mile drive. While the snow is on the ground, you can explore Rhododendron on snowshoes, cross-country skis, or by snowmobile. However you sightsee through the surrounding National Forest, you'll love coming back for a soak in the hot tub. And don't worry about keeping your clothes clean and dry out on your adventure - there's a washer and dryer back at your Barlow Creekside Lodge.

A peaceful escape to the mountains is within reach when you stay at this gorgeous Mt. Hood cabin rental. Enjoy river views, a comfortable rustic design, and great amenities whether you stay for a fun-filled weekend or more.

