Built in 2009, this spacious Mt. Hood vacation home has plenty of room for family and friends, in an immaculate, well-designed space. Much of the beautiful natural pine wood in the home, from the ceiling beams to the window trim, was created from pine trees that originally stood right on the property. And with a great location in Welches, a hot tub, and beautiful outdoor entertaining area, this wonderful Mt. Hood retreat offers year-round adventure for your next group getaway!

A large open living area has tall, slanted ceilings, recessed lighting, and a gas fireplace to create a cozy environment that encourages conversation or an evening watching movies on the wall-mounted flat screen TV (there's both a DVD player and BluRay). The sectional sofa is plush and inviting - the perfect spot for a lazy afternoon reading a book and sipping tea. There are also plenty of board games to pick from for an after-dinner game, and a collection of children's movies for keeping the kids entertained.

Right nearby, the kitchen has lots of room for multiple chefs and is well-stocked. There are granite countertops, shiny stainless steel appliances, and specialty gadgets like an espresso maker, a slow cooker, and a hot air popcorn machine. The dining table seats eight, with extra seating at the breakfast bar and outside. For the smallest guests, there is even a plastic chair-top high chair.

Next to the dining room table, sliding glass doors leads to a lovely private backyard that borders a forested nature area. Guests can relax in the brand new seven person hot tub, sit around the fire pit roasting marshmallows and making s'mores, or have a glass of wine and conversation under the stars. There's also a gas grill for family cookouts on nice, sunny afternoons.

In all five bedrooms, comfortable mattresses await your slumber. The master bedroom has a beautiful wood beam King bed, fireplace, and access to the lovely back yard. Bring your espresso back to bed in the morning, or slide open the doors and sip your morning coffee outside. The attached master bathroom has double sinks, a large vanity, separate shower, and a jetted soaking tub.

Two other bedrooms also have queen sized beds and large walk-in closets. One has its own TV with VCR and a video tape movie library. Two other bedrooms are designed to accommodate children or teenagers, with two twin-over-twin bunk beds and one full-over-full bunk bed. There are also two futons, one in the open loft open to the living room, one in the Master Bedroom on the main floor. Also one extra twin-sized mattress, in one of the Queen upstairs Bedroom. Plus a Pack'n Play crib if needed. This home will a sleep a total 15 lucky guests, but please check to see if the bed configuration will fit your group's needs.

This palatial, modern mountain getaway is located in a quiet neighborhood, just perfect for an extended family vacation, friend getaway, or couples traveling together. There are several children's bicycles in the garage for the kids to tool around the neighborhood and explore. If anyone gets dirty while out having fun, no worries - a large laundry room with a full sized washer and dryer will keep everyone in clean socks throughout your stay!

Just a half mile away, there's a grocery store for picking up supplies, and a ski shop in the shopping center right along Hwy 26. In nice weather, the Resort at the Mountain's 27-hole golf course is open to the public and only a short two minute  drive away.

Looking for a ski getaway home base? Driving times to the three ski areas are minor - Mount Hood Ski Bowl, with its 34 fully lit runs, 65 runs total, and night skiing opportunities is only a 16 minute drive from the house. Iconic Timberline Lodge is only 27 minutes away and Mount Hood Meadows is a 30-40 minute drive.

In the summer, hiking and mountain biking trails abound, and views for landscape photography are plentiful. Mt. Hood Ski Bowl also has a summer Adventure Park for the whole family featuring bungee jumping, indy karts, mountain biking, horseback riding, a rock wall, and more! Spring, summer, fall, or winter, this Mt. Hood getaway will house your group in comfort while you discover the beautiful and scenic Mt. Hood area.

