This cozy Brightwood cabin is a classic Mt. Hood vacation rental: a laid-back getaway with a fireplace, exposed timber, and an amazing location right on the Salmon River!

The cabin itself is located just off Highway 26 for easy access at any time of year, but the sound of the Salmon River rushing past easily drowns out any traffic noise. Golf and groceries are found just five minutes up the road in Welches.

This getaway has all the essentials you'll need to enjoy a weekend on the mountain. Curl up by the fireplace on an overstuffed armchair with your morning coffee. There is a cable TV with DVD player for laid-back afternoons, plus a shelf stocked full of board games for more interactive entertainment. If you're working while away, you'll appreciate the wireless Internet access; if not, you can always browse reviews for the nearby restaurants and pubs while you relax by the fire.

Take advantage of the open kitchen with a 1950's flair to cook some homemade meals. Those bright blue cabinets hold some fun extras like a blender for smoothies and a coffee grinder for the perfect grind on your favorite brew. Dine inside or out - it's up to you!

Open up the curtains at the rear of the house and take in unbelievable views of the Salmon River rushing past, no matter what the weather may be outside. When the sun shines, step out to the patio overlooking the river. There is a charcoal grill for summer barbecues and a table and chairs so you can dine outdoors when the weather warms. The cabin is also dog-friendly, with an additional nightly pet fee.

This is a cozy one-bedroom, one-and-a-half bathroom home with an additional loft. Upstairs, the open sleeping loft has a queen bed and two twins. The downstairs sofa unfolds into a comfortable full-size sleeper, allowing up to six guests to share the space. There is one full bath downstairs, with an upstairs half bath to make sharing the space easier.

Come and enjoy the wonders of Mt. Hood! There are hiking trails and fishing holes galore, and of course the world-class skiing at four different resorts. Skibowl is the closest to this cabin, less than 15 miles away; is just a few miles further.

For a laid-back riverside retreat, you won't find much better than this cozy Oregon vacation cabin near Brightwood on Mt. Hood!

