Golfer's Villa at the Resort on the Mountain

Sure, you love to golf, and what better place to be than right here in this beautiful Welches vacation rental townhome on the fairway of world-class, Resort at the Mountain. But golfing isn't everything, is it? (Okay, maybe it is.)

But Welches is much more than the three golf courses right in the area. There's a great spa and restaurant right there in the resort, and surrounding Welches are the natural wonders of the Mount Hood area - rivers, mountains, forests - that call to you with hiking, fishing, rafting, and every manner of winter sport.

There's lots of room to stretch out in this big living room with vaulted ceilings. If you're just back from the slopes, throw a log on the wood fireplace and warm up your toes while you're waiting for dinner. You'll have plenty of entertainment options. Bring along some of your favorite DVDs and CDs to pop into the player. And make sure the iPod's loaded up - there's a doc for that too. For some serious relaxation, slide into the warm, swirling waters of the jetted tub in the master bathroom.

Golfers Villa has a big, well-stocked kitchen that's up to any chef's challenge. Lots of cupboards and counter space make preparing any meals easy. Serve it up at the dining table with room for four and a great view of - you guessed it - the golf course. (Diners can also cozy up to the bar on three stools.) If you've got a taste for barbeque, just fire up the gas grill on the deck. If you're heading out, there are some great eateries right in the resort where you can get everything from a steak to a "wee bite." Or, head into Welches where you'll find 12 different places to eat, serving just about every taste.

With three bedrooms and a loft, this townhome vacation rental sleeps up to 6. The master bedroom, on the main floor, has a queen bed and a bathroom with the jetted tub. There are queen beds in two of the other bedrooms upstairs, one of which has a bunk twin as well.

After you've played the final hole and you've settled into the comfy living room of this luxurious vacation rental, do yourself a favor: pull out the laptop and look up the beautiful Indian legend surrounding this area. Welches is right next to Mount Hood National Forest.

For skiers, Golfers Villa is 20 minutes from Skibowl and 30 minutes from Mt. Hood Meadows and Timberline Lodge. Just a few miles away is the popular Salmon Creek Trail. Hike one-way (2.6 miles) or round trip (5.2 miles). It's just one of 31 trails of varying difficulty around Mount Hood. And, there's rafting, fishing, kayaking, horse back riding - everything you'd expect from 60 square miles of wilderness area. Of course, there are lots of place to golf too. So call now and reserve this beautiful townhome for your next Mount Hood getaway.

