The Coyote: Lean; adaptable. As its namesake suggests, let this comfortable, reasonably priced cabin be the base camp for your year 'round, alpine experience. Just 1 hour and 15 minutes from Portland, Coyote House is three miles from Parkdale and a short trip from all the outdoor adventures awaiting you in the Upper Hood River Valley and Mt. Hood area. Let it be the place you lay your head after a day of skiing, hiking, or fishing. Or, grab your G.P.S. and try the latest high-tech game of hide and seek called "geocaching." (Look it up!)

Pack in your eats and fix a nice meal in the full kitchen, or, in the summer, fire up the barbie' around the back and enjoy a burger against a verdant mountain vista. Need milk or bread? No problem. Just hop in the car and visit one of three local groceries where you can also rent a DVD to enjoy after dinner. Grab a cup of coffee at a nearby coffee house or a cool craft brew from the local brew-pub. (Coyote has a TV but, sorry, no cable.)

Whether you're a group of two or a half-dozen, Coyote House can accommodate you. With a full kitchen, large dining area and living room, there's plenty of space to kick back. At bedtime, you'll find one bedroom with a queen bed, an additional queen bed in the loft (the ultimate bunk bed for the kids: access is by a ladder), and a comfortable queen size convertible couch in the living room. Also, plenty of secure space to stow your gear and room for two vehicles next to the cabin.

Coyote is just three short miles from Parkdale, a town whose roots are entangled with the Mount Hood Railroad whose directors decided, in 1910, that little Parkdale should be literally the end of the line. Parkdale is the final stop on the popular "Fruit Loop"  -  a tour of the many orchards in and around Hood River Valley. Coyote is close to many biking and hiking trails in Mount Hood National Forest such as Frog Creek Trail. There are 23 fishing spots in the Hood River Ranger District. Or, head over to Hood River on the majestic Columbia River, just 20 minutes north, where you'll find some of the best windsurfing in the world and restaurants to serve any taste. Skiers can take advantage of Vacasa's Mount Hood Meadows special (above). Mount Hood Meadows is 28 minutes south of Parkdale.

Coyote is an eco-friendly vacation destination. Organic cotton linens and towels, recycled paper products, and recycling are provided. Add the fact that Coyote's non-toxic cleaning products are used to clean house, and it's clear that Coyote House's environmental footprint is gentle and Green!

(The pooch and kitty are welcome too. Ask about conditions.)

