Tucked beneath the trees in the Mt. Hood National Forest, just an hour east of Portland beside the Zig Zag River, lays an intimate updated mountain cabin with room for seven. Not only will your group be ideally located just 20 minutes from the slopes of Mt. Hood Meadows, Mt. Hood SkiBowl, and Timberline, but this quaint Rhododendron vacation rental will keep you warm and cozy year 'round with its private hot tub and fire pit!

Wood-paneled walls and ceilings create a true cabin feel, while modern upgrades and a thoughtful design will have you living the mountain life in style.  A gas fireplace within a beautiful stone facade in the sitting room will keep your toes warm and the ambiance inviting as you settle in with a glass of wine and some good conversation. Just above the mantle you'll find a large flat screen TV with cable so you won't have to miss your favorite late night show. Tucked in the corner you'll find a bistro table and chairs - an ideal spot for playing card games, spreading out a trail map, or keeping up with email on your laptop through the WiFi provided.

Around the corner, the compact yet fully equipped kitchen is brand new and ready to take on your homemade meals. Along with the basic necessities ñ electric stovetop, oven, microwave, and refrigerator ñ you'll also have a dishwasher to make for easy clean-up, as well as extras perks like a coffee maker, tea kettle and a slow cooker for that braised pork recipe you've been wanting to try.  Serve up your specialty on the beautiful wooden table with handmade benches and room for all seven of you.

In the warmer months you may want to move the party outside and grill up some burgers on the gas grill while soaking up that fresh mountain air. Don't forget the s'more fixings! You'll have your own fire pit to roast marshmallows and swap stories around out here too.  To top off the night, feel free to relax and star-gaze from the comfort of your private hot tub as you let the cares of your day slip away.

Back indoors, you'll find two full bedrooms and a loft on the second floor. The loft acts as a great kids' space, with a twin-over-full bunk bed and another flat screen cable TV and DVD player for movie night sleepovers. To the left is a small queen bedroom, with a platform bed and flat screen TV, and across the hall you'll find the master bedroom. Along with a plush queen bed and ceiling fan, the master bedroom offers a unique layout, with an in-room sink, stand-up shower, and toilet area for privacy and convenience. Downstairs, you'll find the second full bath and a side laundry room to help keep up with adventure soaked clothes. We know your dog loves the outdoors as much as you do, so for $10 a night, your four-legged friend can accompany you on your mountain retreat (with a $40 minimum per stay).

Though you're nestled in the forest, you won't be too far secluded to experience some mountain culture. Stop by the Zig Zag Inn for some pizza and a milkshake, or head into Skyway Bar & Grill to catch some live music.  Coffee lovers will definitely want to stop by Mt. Hood Coffee Roasters (some of the best beans around!)

While a primary reason to visit will naturally be the epic skiing found at Mt. Hood Meadows, SkiBowl, or Timberline, there's plenty to do in and around the Mt. Hood National Forest as well. Golfers (and history buffs) will enjoy rounds at The Courses, Oregon's first golf course, right next door at the Resort at the Mountain in Welches. Hiking trails are numerous throughout the National Forest, and plenty of boating, rafting and fishing opportunities can be found at the Salmon and Zig Zag rivers, as well as Mirror Lake nearby. When the snow falls, snowshoers and cross-country skiers will be in their element with plenty of terrain to traverse within minutes from your cabin. And don't forget the binoculars bird lovers ñ Rhododendron is home to two of the official Oregon Cascades Birding Trails.

Pack the skis, hiking boots, and clubs, gather up the family and get a head start on your Oregon Cascades getaway. Book this Mt. Hood vacation rental and let nature set the pace for a rejuvenating and adventure-packed mountain escape.

