This serene Mount Hood vacation home is a pastoral refuge nestled on four, forested acres just ten minutes from Rhododendron, but with a wonderful sense of peace, quiet, and privacy. With room for eight, every detail of this lovely cabin evokes the lush woodland visible through all the big windows. And from the comfort of the wicker chair out on one of the decks, you'll also have a front row seat on the idyllic little pond in back.

After a day of floating on a kayak or teasing the rushing waters of the nearby Sandy River with the new lures you've tied, this living room is geared for relaxation! Dinner's not quite ready, so take off your shoes and take a load off on the sofa, love seat, or armchair, each with its own built-in recliner. Nights can be chilly on beautiful Mount Hood, but you'll be snug and warm after you bring that fresh log to a blaze in the oversized wood stove, perched on its own stone pedestal. Start a game of chess or one of the many games available in the cabinet. Internet is provided, but please note there is a daily limit on usage and it should not be depended on for extensive use.

Meals will be easy in this fully equipped kitchen, complete with gas stove, double fridge, and a dishwasher, so there's less time by the sink. It's a bright space, with sunlight from the window, a skylight, and overhead track lighting. And there's plenty of counter space to for prepping those veggies. When it's all done, sit down at the table for eight where you'll eat and imbibe from brightly colored stoneware and modern wine glasses. Weather permitting, bring some steaks, hot dogs or salmon to sizzling perfection on the gas grill, stoke the fire in the outdoor firepit, and enjoy your meal outside with s'mores for dessert!

Each of Red Relaxer's three bedrooms share one thing: green. Whether it's a green rug, curtain, or the length of pine branches strung along the bed canopy, the theme is "forest", and the art and rustic furniture underscore it. In addition to the queen bed and attached full bath in the master suite, there's a handsome roll-top desk, an easy chair, and a queen futon. There's a queen bed with rough-hewn log frame adorned with pine branches in the second bedroom, and, finally, two twins in the third bedroom. A second full bathroom is available to everyone. And, pack light: there's also a washer and dryer.

The mornings are especially peaceful here: at the Red Relaxer you will wake up to the sound of gently gurgling streams and the rustling of cedars - never the sound of traffic going by or ski boots tromping on stairs!

As one of the communities located along the Mount Hood Scenic Byway, little Rhododendron shares the natural beauty and wealth of recreational activities you'll find everywhere in the Mount Hood area. Rhododendron is located near five state parks and the enormous Mount Hood National Forest, so there are plenty of places to hike and bike. Not only is the Sandy River nearby, but the town is also minutes from the Salmon River and Steel Creek, so it's not surprising that Rhododendron is a fly-fishing mecca. If you're an amateur (or a professional!) ornithologist, you're in the right place! Two of the official Oregon Cascades Birding Trails are nearby. There's plenty of golfing in Welches, and, in winter, skiers and boarders will be close to five resorts, including Mount Hood Meadows, just a half-hour away.

So come to this beautiful cottage in the woods just minutes from Rhododendron. Enjoy the peace and quiet that comes with four secluded acres, the convenience of all the amenities you could ask for, and access to all the sites and recreational options waiting for you in the gorgeous Mount Hood region!

