You'll have a taste of Bavaria when you stay at this German-themed, chalet-sytle Government Camp vacation rental with room for six within walking distance of Skibowl Ski Resort and the shops, restaurants and activities in and around Government Camp. After a tiring but fun day on the slopes, come out of the snow, slip the car in the double-deep garage, stow the equipment, and gather 'round the fireplace with a mug of your favorite Lager.

Located in Collins Lake Resort, it's just an hour's drive from Portland. When you stay at this chalet with room for six, you'll enjoy Alpen ambiance in the shadow of Oregon's Mount Hood.

There is comfy new furniture in the living room and there is even a new 50" Plasma TV with cable, so you won't miss the latest episode of your favorite mini-series. Bring along a couple of your favorite DVDs, fill a bowl with some snacks, and enjoy a movie. Or, bring up the free internet and plan your next day's activities in the abundant, Mount Hood area. The owner has provided some DVDs, games and a guitar for your enjoyment as well.  If it's warm enough, head on out to the deck and savor the spectacular view as you fire up the gas grill for a barbeque.

Your designated chefs can make everything from spaetzle to spinach in the full kitchen with lots of counter space for prep work, and the chore of cooking might seem a little less tedious with each look out the kitchen window, where they'll have a great view of Mount Hood. Serve it up at the wooden table with three chairs and a bench. The collection of steins might just make you feel like you're in a Gasthaus in Munich.

This chalet has two bedrooms, both upstairs. In one, you'll find a queen bed, in the other, two twins. At bedtime the kids can scurry up to the loft and pull out the twin trundle bed for a night's sleep. There are two full bathrooms upstairs, and a half-bath downstairs.

The garage is set up with a ski waxing station and even has a fooseball table and a dart board for entertainment after you hit the slopes!

Government Camp isn't just for winter. Sure, there's Skibowl, Mount Hood Meadows, and plenty of other places to play in the white stuff. But any time of year you can get a little bit of history by trekking up to Timberline Lodge, an historic legacy of  Depression Era architecture. Learn even more about Mount Hood's colorful past at the Mount Hood Cultural Center, right in Government Camp. In summer, Mount Hood is a haven for hiking, rafting, cycling, fishing, and much more. Or, just hang out at the Creekside Lodge where you'll find two hot tubs, a year-round pool with heated decks, and a beautiful clubhouse where you can lounge in front of the great stone fireplace with a book or a laptop.

Whatever season, whatever your idea of fun, this charming, Collins Lake vacation rental can accommodate you.

