Offering both the peace and serenity of a private vacation getaway and high-end amenities like hot tubs, a club house, and heated swimming pool, this Collins Lake Condo is the idea spot for your next Mt. Hood ski (or summertime!) vacation. Right near Collins Lake and all the fun of Government Camp's restaurants and shops, you'll enjoy an ideal location and comfortable, stylish decor with designer touches throughout.

Upon entry, head up the stairs and you'll be greeted with an open floor plan - a connecting living room, dining room, and kitchen. Super comfortable leather couches provide lots of seating in the living room, and there's a gas fireplace for those chilly mountain evenings. There's also a flat screen TV and accompanying DVD player for movie nights and if you forget to bring your favorite films from home, don't worry - just pick one from the collection!

Throughout this stylish condo, the owner's metal art is displayed, giving the space an almost gallery-like feel. Landscape scenes from around the area also decorate the walls, so you'll always find something attractive to catch your eye. Near the fireplace, a door leads out onto the deck for a view of the trees and well-kept community grounds. There's a gas grill and table seating out here as well to enjoy dining al fresco-style.

Back inside, the kitchen and dining room are bright and welcoming, with shiny hardwood floors and a warm color on the walls. Six people can sit comfortably at the table for meals, and there are a few extra spots at the breakfast bar. The kitchen features granite countertops and all the major appliances you'll need for preparing memorable vacation meals. The cabinets are stocked with pots, pans, glasses, and dinnerware, and the dishwasher makes clean-up a breeze!

Upstairs, the master bedroom has a queen sized bed with Mission-style bed frame and a luxurious heated mattress pad to keep you delightfully toasty. There's also a flat screen TV in this room, a relaxing decor, a view of the forest out the window, and a convenient attached bathroom with a Jacuzzi tub.

The second bedroom also features a queen sized bed, bright, comfortable bedding, and its own eye-catching artwork, including handmade mountain landscape silhouette metal sconces. A bonus room has twin bunk beds, perfect for kids. A second full bathroom is also located in this hallway. This nicely updated condo will sleep six guests quite comfortably.

As part of the well-maintained Collins Lake community, this condo includes complimentary access to amenities like a heated swimming pool, two hot tubs, sauna, and an impressive clubhouse. The placement of this particular condo is quite nice, as it sits towards the back of the complex and quiet, away from pool noise. This 28-acre complex includes many trails, perfect for snowshoeing in the winter or fun, casual hikes in the summer.

Beyond the grounds of Collins Lake, Mt. Hood provides plenty of adventure for your group! The town of Government Camp is an easy walk from your front door, with an abundance of dining options and stores to browse. On nights you don't feel like cooking, make the short walk to Ice Axe Grill for pints of Mt. Hood Brewing Co.'s Hogsback Oatmeal Stout, sweet potato fries, and steelhead chowder.

In the winter, you'll be able to walk to the slopes at Mt. Hood Ski Bowl or make the drive a few short miles further up the mountain to visit the historic Timberline Lodge. You may even find that some of your most favorite vacation memories include being curled up on the red comfy chair back at the condo, reading a book, and enjoying the fireplace.

In the warm weather months, this region overflows with hiking, biking, and fishing activities. Nature lovers will find much to be taken with in this year-round outdoor playground. No matter the season, this Lake Collins Condo is a great choice for couples traveling together, a group of friends, or a family getaway to scenic Government Camp.

