Sitting just on the north end of town, this gorgeous three bedroom Mendocino vacation rental has a beautiful ocean view, stunning landscaped yard, redwood paneling, a cozy gas fireplace, and a full kitchen. Right from the deck, you'll have views of Agate Cove and the Headlands - the perfect scene for a relaxing afternoon glass of wine.

Inside this beautiful Mendocino vacation home, you'll be treated to a tiled entry way and spacious, open living room. Relax back on the brown leather sofa or maybe the easy chair, and enjoy the ambiance from the gas fireplace. Entertainment options here include a flat screen TV, cable, a DVD player, WiFi, and a stereo. There's even an iPod dock.

Aside from an ocean view, the full kitchen has a dishwasher, refrigerator, stovetop/oven - everything you'll need for some seafood pasta or a special weekend brunch, complete with a pitcher of mimosas! And if you pick up some fresh beans at Moody's Organic Coffee Bar in town, you even have a coffee grinder back at your cozy Headlands Cove retreat.

This Mendocino vacation home's bedrooms are located on opposite sides of the house, allowing for extra privacy for the master suite. This space boasts a unique Murphy-style queen sized bed, comfortable sitting area, and a private bathroom with a jetted tub and a separate walk-in shower.

The two additional bedrooms are located on the other side of the house, each with a queen bed. They share a stylish bathroom with vessel sinks, and a multi-head shower that includes a steam feature. This lovely ocean-view home will sleep up to six guests comfortably.

The landscaped grounds at this Headlands Cove getaway include colorful rhododendrons and a variety of coastal flowers, including beautiful white and yellow Matilija poppies. From both the front and back decks, you can relax and take in the ocean vistas while preparing dinner on the outdoor grill or having an al fresco style meal - there's even a hidden picnic table out between the rhododendrons in the yard for a special lunch.

Right from your door, walk along the this quiet neighborhood's streets to Mendocino Headlands State Park. From the cliff-side bluffs you'll have stunning panoramic views or take the steps down to the rocky beach. This convenient location is also on a 15 minute walk from the center of town! Walk or bike to lunch, the bookstore, and numerous galleries -  you're close to it all at this lovely Mendocino retreat.

Right near the heart of the village and only minutes to Fort Bragg or Jug Handle Beach, this Northern California Coast vacation rental offers a stylish interior, an ideal location, and all the comforts of home with stunning ocean views.

