The view of the ocean is spectacular and the property's strongest asset.

The short hike to the Cove is covered in blackberries - a nice treat!  The Cove is quiet and spectacular.  We enjoyed the company of a molting elephant seal while we were there.  Walking to the lighthouse along the cliffs is just gorgeous.

It was literally just a walk out the door and around the corner to go hike in Russian Gulch State Park--a beautiful, lush and interesting place where the Redwoods meet the water.

