Looking for the perfect family reunion spot? Look no further than Captain Phil's gorgeous five-bedroom Albion vacation rental offering ocean views, a gourmet kitchen, fireplace, and private hot tub!

The brand new vacation home is located just South of the village of Mendocino in a quaint coastal community. Nestled amongst the California Redwood Forest and the Little Salmon Creek, the home is the ideal spot to set back the clock and regain some peace and solitude. A five-minute drive will offer beautiful views of Albion River Bridge, a WWII era wooden trestle bridge, shopping, and oysters and artisan cheese plates at the Ledford House.

This sea-themed getaway has exposed wood ceilings, ornate driftwood carvings, soft leather touches, and a statue of the Captain Phil himself! The large social areas, including the living room, kitchen, and dining room are upstairs in this second-story vacation home. Feel instantly at ease in the open-concept living room, with its soft leather reclining loveseats and sofa. The loveseats are huddled around a unique carved wood coffee table base with a glass top, and frame the large rock fireplace and flatscreen TV.

The media center offers cable, a CD player, and a surround sound stereo system to create a theater-style movie night! You and guests will gaze into the fire or absorb the nearly panoramic views of the Pacific ocean thanks to floor to ceiling windows overlooking the expansive patio.

Just off the living room is an exquisite kitchen with custom wood cabinets, granite countertops, and stainless-steel appliances including a built-in microwave, oven, gas range grill top stove, dishwasher, refrigerator, toaster, coffeemaker and French press, double sink, and plenty of cutting boards and kitchen accessories to serve large meals. An expansive granite kitchen island will allow you to prep lunches for your ocean adventures, and a table top wine rack will store the bottles you brought for your special family vacation! Just off the kitchen is a formal dining room with a wood table for eight. At the heart of the table is a twisted carved wood centerpiece.

