At night, this spacious home offers five bedrooms, four full bathrooms and comfortably sleeps 10 people. Two master suits are upstairs, one with a king and the one with a queen-sized bed. Downstairs is three additional guest rooms with queen-sized beds, and a regal game room with an ornate claw-foot pool table with red felt, vintage signs, studded leather barstools, and a chainsaw carving of a bear. Don't forget to pack your gadgets!

Drive just 10 minutes for geocaching, fishing, and boating to where locals call “the redwood tunnel to the sea” at Navarro River Redwoods State Park. Make the 15-minute drive to Mendocino where you can go whale watching, board a charter fishing boat, browse book shops and galleries, or enjoy a pulled pork sandwich and local brew at Patterson's Pub.

