Perfect for a family reunion or friends getaway, this lovely Fort Bragg vacation rental brings all the necessities of home including a gourmet kitchen, newly remodeled bedrooms, and a basketball court! With four bedrooms and three bathrooms, up to eleven guests and two pets can enjoy the vacation of a lifetime here.

This home is nestled next door to the locally famous Purple Rose Mexican Restaurant, and just steps from the Ricochet Ranch Horseback riding stables for rides on the beach. Easily explore beautiful MacKerricher State Park as the entrance is just a few houses down.

This 1950s home beautifully blends antique decor with modern novelties. The redwood wainscoting and white oak floor bring a unique warmth to this home.

With elegant leather furnishings, the living room will quickly become a favorite spot for everyone in the group. Warm yourselves by the pellet stove on cooler days while playing endless board and card games with the family or simply chat and lounge with an evening glass of wine. Family movie nights on the large flatscreen TV are a must and with cable and Netflix streaming, you won't miss any of your favorite shows.

The chef of the group will be whipping up delicious creations in no time in this perfectly designed gourmet kitchen. Along with plenty of bakeware and dinnerware, this kitchen also comes equipped with an oven, stove-top, microwave, mixer, blender, dishwasher, toaster, waffle iron, and wine glasses. The gorgeous dining room table can seat up to nine guests for daily family meals.

With two master-suites, a third and fourth bedroom, as well as a sofabed in the living room, this home can sleep up to nine guests comfortably. But with a maximum occupancy of 11, you're welcome to bring extra bedding. One master bedroom has a king-size bed and the other has a queen-size bed. Both bedrooms have spectacular full bathroom attached with uniquely tiled walk-in showers.

The third bedroom includes a queen-sized bed. The fourth bedroom, ideal for the kids in the group has a bunk bed (full on bottom and twin on top) and a TV with an Xbox 360. Staying connected is made easy as WiFi is included and with a washer and dryer, you're set for a long and memorable vacation with the entire family and up to two of your furry friends ($10 per pet per day, $40 minimum pet fee required).

Spend the day at the beach located just 998 steps away or walk down to MacKerricher State Park and find the only freshwater lake in the area, Cleone Lake, which is great for kayaking, fishing, and nature watching. You can also enjoy use of the biking, walking, and horseback riding trails within MacKerricher State Park as well!

Start your unforgettable family or friends reunion off on the right foot at this beachfront Northern California vacation rental.

