Admire the ocean & warm up by the bonfire

You'll be California dreamin' in this newly remodeled three-bedroom Fort Bragg vacation rental, offering a bonfire pit, ocean views, a full kitchen, and plenty of room for up to eight guests!

The cozy abode is within short walking distance to exploring tide pools and seal watching at MacKerricher State Park, boating and horseback riding at Lake Cleone, and within a seven-minute drive to coastal village shopping and fine dining in Fort Bragg. Located just 150 miles north of San Francisco on the rugged Northern California Coast, this vacation home is the perfect romantic getaway or family vacation spot!

The 1,700 square-foot space is welcoming with a bright red front door, flowering bushes and shrubs, and hummingbird feeders. The open-concept living room is bright and cheery offering up a sofa, decorative throw pillows, and a wood table for six.

Pack your favorite family DVDs for movie night (you can also pick one from this home's DVD library), or watch a program on cable. The vacation rental offers wireless Internet, children's games, and a game room with a Ping-Pong table, so even on the rainiest of days you'll never get cabin fever!  In the garage, you'll also have an Xbox with games.

At the heart of the living area is a brown tile kitchen island and four barstools. It's the perfect space to entertain your guests, host a potluck, or veg out around snacks and good conversation. The fully-equipped kitchen offers a stove, oven, built-in microwave, refrigerator, dishwasher, and toaster.

The single-level home has three bedrooms and two full baths to comfortably sleep eight guests. The master suite has a king-sized bed, flat-screen TV, work desk, and calming ocean prints on the wall. A second guest room has a queen-sized bed, and the third bedroom has two twin-sized beds and pictures of the California coastline - perfect for younger guests. A queen-sized air mattress allows you to be flexible with extra guests and sleeping arrangements.

Outside, you'll roast the perfect s'mores on the unique iron bonfire pit that features cutouts of the moons and stars, and take in the salty breeze in laid-back Adirondack patio furniture. Enjoy a game of badminton, roast ears of corn on the gourmet gas grill, or simply watch the grass swirl in the breeze against the backdrop of California's untouched coast and overarching mountain ranges.

With elder and handicap access, and a private washer and dryer, this home is ideal for extended stays - and washing off the grit and sand from days well spent!

Go antiquing in Fort Bragg, located just seven minutes away, tour the meticulously-manicured Mendocino Botanical Gardens, or take a trip down the water slides at the Fort Bragg’s C.V. Starr Spath Aquatic Center. You'll enjoy whale watching at MacKerricher State Park during the winter and spring, and explore hundreds of miles along bluffs, dunes, forests and wetlands.

No matter how you choose to spend your getaway, this conveniently-located Northern California Coast vacation rental is cheery and the perfect retreat to tell ghost stores around the bonfire, collect sand dollars along the beach, and reconnect with the ones you love!

