This oceanfront three-bedroom, three bath Mendocino vacation rental home is the perfect setting for kicking back with friends and family, enjoying a glass of wine on the patio and watching the waves roll in. This home sets up on a bluff, which allows for a fantastic view.  Set back from the edge of the ocean so one can observe varied wildlife grazing with the Pacific sunset as a backdrop you and five other guests will love every minute spent at Sunset Point!

Centrally located, you'll be a short drive to either Fort Bragg or Mendocino Village. Take a quick walk to the Mendocino Coast Botanical Gardens for a truly floral experience and gorgeous ocean backdrop.

Ocean focused and single level, almost every room in this relaxed open floor-plan home is designed to maximize beach views. A large westward facing deck, living room windows and a telescope in the living room and sound dock allows for endless hours of whale watching, storm surveillance and sunset soirees.

The viewing room is a masterpiece, with oceanfront full windows, a large persian rug framed by an ocean-facing sofa and plush swivel chairs to choose whether to take in the ocean views or participate in what's happening indoors. Victorian inspired patterns and designs lead you into the second sitting area, again with full ocean views, two sofas in front of a TV with DVD player and a wood-burning stove.

Drift into the updated gourmet-sized kitchen for a casual lunch, or utilize the fully stocked appliances and equipment for a formal evening seating. Granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, light wooden cabinetry and an ocean view are sure to inspire a sincerely Pacific culinary creation!

Two king suites each have unique features - one has a luxurious, almost decadent ocean view bathroom with a Jacuzzi for two & a separate walk-in shower with dual showerheads; the other has sliding doors to a private deck with ocean views. The queen bedroom has views of the front garden. The family/entertainment room is a separate cozy room with a sleeper sofa; a great room for games, watching TV or using your laptop on the home's WIFI. Up to six people will find the varying room layout a perfect design for traveling couples, families and friends!

Fully embrace your settings with a few nights spent playing in the large backyard, or impress your group with fresh lobster barbecued on the gas grill, and finish off sipping a famous local wine while lounging in the patio furniture. Speaking of outdoor amenities, parking is a dream as this home features three spaces outside of the garage!

The Fort Bragg and Mendocino area offers a wide array of outdoor, nautical themed activities as well as classic Northern California culture. Spend the whole day under the sun visiting parks like the Otis Johnson Wilderness Park within city limits, Pomo Bluffs Park along the headlands overlooking the Noyo inlet, and MacKerricher State Park with miles of sandy beaches. Or take a trip to the amazing Glass Beach, world famous for its natural recycling and polishing process of dumped glass. Keep up the activity with a horseback ride down the beach, sea kayaking, or wild edible mushroom tour! Looking for a more leisurely experience? Take a ride on the acclaimed Skunk Train, schedule a wine tour through the array of local vineyards, or settle down for lunch at Laurel's Deli in the Depot shopping mall - known for it's yummy fresh-made desserts!

A wonderful home for adult couples, friends and families of up to six looking to leave the maddening bustle of the city behind! You will find all you were looking for and more with this Northern California oceanfront getaway.

