PHONE SERVICE- There is virtually NONE. There is no cell service (ATT and Verizon really dont work) and get this!,  NO house phone service either. This house requires a code to call out. YET- no one knows the code - The manual at the house gives NO explanation on what code to use and when we sent the issue via email to the rental agency they did not provide a solution either. We could not even CALL THE RENTAL agency - because you cant use the phone without the code. The listed details on the house (before you rent) does not warn you of this issue so it was a HUGE setback for us. Imagine you have to get in your car and drive to main highway to merely make a phone call to your home or office a mere 40 miles away. For $400+ a night most people would expect to be able to make a basic call out, OR be told HOW TO DO SO in the manual. No luck at this house.

OTHER ISSUES to be aware of. WIFI only works if you are really close to router and is super slow. Many window screens are missing so if you want to open a window- prepare for insects or worse. You cannot really hear the ocean from inside the house as this house is pretty far back from cliff.  Views are nice but windows are way dirty and many windows are blocked by hedges to fully see the ocean. Kitchen is not as advertised i.e. well stocked for cooking. Lids donâ€™t fit pans, very few pans etc. Most cupboards are empty.

