This newly remodeled Fort Bragg vacation rental boasts a private oceanfront parcel, as well and unique foliage and wildlife. It's the perfect getaway for anyone looking to be soothed by the beautiful sounds of the ocean - especially from the private hot tub on the deck!

Just north of the Mendocino Coast Botanical Gardens and near Digger Creek, this home's not far from the action. Downtown Fort Bragg is a stone's throw away, as are the other charming hamlets along the coast.

An all-redwood interior and numerous picture windows make this a highly desirable vacation residence; spend hours watching the waterfront panorama as you let your tensions melt away.

This large ranch abode is sure to delight. The vaulted ceilings and open floor plan make the already expansive space feel even more spacious. The living area features a cream carpet, two gray sofas, and wooden chairs. Red pillows add a splash of color. A gas fireplace is the focal point, and occupies a space near the flatscreen TV and a wall festooned with duck artwork.

The modern kitchen is a gourmand's delight with a massive island, dishwasher, black cupboards, fridge and matching electric range. There are plenty of kitchen accoutrements to whip up a chef-worthy repast in no time. Craft a delicious breakfast and serve it at the four-seat breakfast bar, or dine on a larger meal at the four-seat table overlooking the ocean.

The bedrooms are on the main floor, just steps away from the living area. The master features a king bed, small wooden dresser, and an ocean vista view. Another king bed occupies a smaller bedroom, and a third bedroom has a queen bedroom adorned with the same floral coverlet. The bright yellow bathroom offers a vista to the private backyard.

Head down the wooden steps to gaze at the beautiful Pacific Ocean. A new deck runs the length of the house, with a private hot tub that takes excellent advantage of the whitewater vistas. You'll be able to stay well-connected as this home comes with WiFi.

Once a collection of sleepy fishing villages, the Mendocino Coast now boasts myriad food and adventure activities. Enjoy touring the Victorian homes in historic Mendocino Village. Try your hand at kayaking via Liquid Fusion Kayaking in Fort Bragg, or spend a rainy day at the Triangle Tattoo and Museum, showcasing Maori tattoo art from the 1800s. The Mendo Bistro in Fort Bragg serves up barbecued splendor throughout the year, and craft beer aficionados will love the opportunity to sip a microbrew at North Coast Brewing Company.

Whatever your pleasure, a stay at this gorgeous, updated oceanfront Northern California vacation rental is sure to be a delight!

