Just 16 miles south of Mendocino and perched right on the ocean bluff, this majestic five-bedroom Elk vacation rental offers luxurious surroundings, all with a stunning ocean view. In addition, there's a private hot tub, WiFi, wood burning fireplace, and a kids' room - complete with six twin beds, pool table, and a flat screen TV. All of this and a half acre yard - it's heaven!

Inside this 4,000 square foot, oceanfront vacation home, you'll enjoy nights relaxing in the spacious living room with its 40-inch flat screen TV, cable, and DVD player. Or, you can retire to the fireplace room - start a fire and settle back on one of the sofas or the window seat and take in the amazing ocean view. No matter where you decide to relax, you'll be surround by comfort and classic design touches.

The full kitchen includes a refrigerator, Wolf Commercial-grade stovetop/oven, and a dishwasher. Unleash your gourmet skills in this gorgeous, functional space. From the dining area, you can have your dinner with stunning water views for an unforgettable vacation meal. You'll want to stay at the table talking, and finishing the last of the wine.

Five bedrooms (two downstairs and three upstairs including the "dorm") have three queen beds, a full bed, and there are six twin beds in the upstairs, kid-friendly game room space - room for up to 12 guests total. This game room also has a flat screen TV, pool table, comfortable furniture, and lots of room for playing, reading, or socializing. Three of the bedrooms have ocean views, including the downstairs master suite. There are also three and a half baths, a laundry room with washer and dryer, board games, and a stereo. Everything you'll need!

No matter how nice the interior of this Elk vacation home is, you will definitely be spending a lot of time outside. Lounge on the large deck, enjoying the views of the rocky California coast, soak in the hot tub after a long day of exploring, or grill some steaks out on the stainless steel gas grill. The edge of the property extends all the way to the bluff, allowing for spectacular views of the ocean. Bring a cup of coffee out in the morning for some quiet contemplation as you listen to the ocean's waves.

The Bella Mare vacation home in Elk is right along the main street, with plenty of options if you don't feel like making a meal at home. Bridget Dolan's Pub is practically next door for a nice dinner out and in the morning, walk down the road to Queenie's Roadhouse for a satisfying breakfast alongside the locals. The perfect fuel before a day of hiking or a game of golf at the Little River Golf Course, just 13 miles north. If you do want to explore the beach, there's a trail head right across the street from Queenie's that heads right to the shore.

Other area attractions include the charming community of Mendocino, just a 30 minute drive away for a day of gallery browsing, hiking, and pints of local beer at Patterson's Pub. But really, with its amazing view, you may just be content to leave your car in the driveway and spend your time walking around the charming village of Elk and enjoying the good life at your Mendocino-area vacation rental.

This Northern California Coast vacation rental is an oasis of stunning ocean views, deluxe amenities, and classic style. Visit this small, laid-back ocean bluff community of Elk for a relaxing vacation in the beautiful Northern California sunshine.

