Distant Shores, one of four cabins within the Mendocino Coast Dunes Retreat, may be rented together with the other cabins for large group gatherings, or separately for a private, relaxing, comfortable place to stay during your vacation. With wheelchair accessibility, a private hot tub, and pet-friendly attitude, you will feel right at home here!

Situated about seven miles north of Fort Bragg, this home is right next to the beautiful sand dunes. The beach is just past the dunes, about half a mile, though the walk is a bit of a hike - drive just south to MacKerricher State Park for easy beach access and amazing views of the ocean and dunes.

This two-bedroom, one-bathroom wheelchair-accessible home can accommodate up to six guests, and you are even welcome to bring your beloved pets with you, though a $10 per pet, per day, $40 minimum fee per stay does apply. With a queen-size bed in each bedroom and an additional sofabed, everyone will have a comfortable place to rest up for another day of vacationing!

In the living room you will find plenty of ways to keep entertained, whether you prefer watching cable TV or a DVD, playing a board game, using the Internet to stay connected, watching the flickering flames in the lovely gas fireplace, or simply gazing out the windows at the beautiful scenery. A full kitchen has all the tools and equipment you may need to cook meals during your visit, and a laundry area will come in handy during longer stays.

Outside, you will be pleased to find a nice deck with seating, a firepit, and a private hot tub! You and your guests will love using the firepit to cook up s'mores for dessert, or relaxing in the cozy warmth of the hot tub.

The Distant Shores would be a great place to enjoy a nice vacation with your family or a few close friends, though you could also rent it with the other three cabins in the complex and bring a large group to vacation together! With Fort Bragg just a few miles down the highway, take a quick trip into the city for a nice meal at a restaurant, some groceries, or to explore the town.

This comfortable, accessible, and amenity-filled home is ready to welcome everyone to their fabulous vacation!

