Located about seven miles north of Fort Bragg, this home is just over half a mile from the sparkling ocean, though if you want easy beach access you may want to drive to MacKerricher State Park, because the walk from the cabin over the dunes is a bit hilly.

Up to four people are may stay in this one-bedroom, one-bathroom home which features a full-size bed in the bedroom and a comfortable fold-out futon. Feel free to bring your dogs to enjoy the vacation with you, though a $10 per pet, nightly, $40 minimum fee per stay applies.

With a delightful nautical theme, you will feel very welcome in the living area, which comes complete with cable TV, a DVD player, Internet access, and a cozy gas fireplace. A kitchenette has a hot plate and a mini fridge so you can whip up a snack easily.

