Relax with the comforts of homes at this Fort Bragg vacation rental. This 2,700-square-foot abode boasts a private fenced yard, two living areas, a formal dining, and a hot tub and can be rented alone or with three other homes in the Mendocino Coast Dunes Retreat for family reunions and other events!

Situated near the dunes on the north side of MacKerricher State Park, this lovely house is about seven miles north of Fort Bragg. The ocean is a little more than half a mile to the west.

The Sandrahla boasts plenty of space for the whole family. The living room features a 50-inch flatscreenTV, equipped with cable and a DVD player, a plush brown sofabed, and a green recliner. Grab a board game and test your mettle against the rest of the family or tickle the ivories on the upright piano. Just around the corner lies a formal dining room with seating for eight as well as a great room with a large brown sectional couch.

The kitchen offers a four-seat breakfast bar for your morning noshes as well as plenty of counter space to whip up a hearty repast. You get a gas range, dishwasher, and a wealth of accoutrements to make the home chef happy. Outside, you will be delighted to find a large deck with a plethora of seating for al fresco dinners under the stars. Toast marshmallows in the firepit or relax after a hard day in the hot tub.

This home features four carpeted bedrooms and three baths, making it ideal for up to 10 people (12 people max). The master suite is spacious and luxurious. Sink into the satiny folds of the king bed or relax in the round jetted tub in the master bath. There's even a separate standalone shower in the bathroom as well as access to the outdoor deck via sliding glass doors.

The other bedrooms have a queen bed each and are decorated in a variety of themes, from Asian to Hawaiian to Southwestern. All feature wood furniture and plush coverlets. There are two additional full baths down the hall.

Guests get free WiFi as well as a private washer and dryer and plenty of land to roam. Feel free to bring up to two dogs with you on your holiday, for an additional fee. The Sandrahla is the perfect place to host a large group event such as a family reunion or work retreat.

Fort Bragg is only 10 minutes away and boasts a plethora of exciting activities. Enjoy a seaside nosh or a cup of joe at one of the eateries in town. Head to the Mendocino Coast Botanical Gardens or MacKerricher State Park for an easy day trip exploring the outdoors.

Book this spacious, comfortable, and amenity-filled Northern California Coast rental and experience for yourself everything the area has to offer!

