Settled on the ocean side of Navarro Ridge, Sky Song is a unique octagonal Albion vacation rental home perfect for up to six adults. Offering a panoramic ocean-view that reveals the Navarro River merging with the Pacific Ocean you'll be engulfed in an eclectic and romantic traveler's paradise! This home is ideal for writers, persons looking for a personal retreat or small intimate groups looking to mix work with pleasure in a beautiful location.

Close to the river and ocean, you'll be settled in the midst of an aquatic centered utopia. Kayaking, paddle boarding, fishing and scuba diving await! State parks and miles of sandy beach are a short drive away whether you're headed north or south. When looking to hit the town you'll be just a five-minute drive from the adorable village of Albion, and twenty minutes south of Mendocino.

The owners have combined an eclectic style of exotic wall hangings and furnishings from Asia - including Tibet, Nepal, India, Burma, Thailand, Bhutan, Cambodia, China and Japan - with contemporary furniture. Bright natural lighting, gorgeous wood paneling, two fireplaces, a wrap-around deck, and ocean view hot tub makes this an ultra-luxury retreat.

Heading into the living room you'll be greeted with expansive views of the river and ocean below, and are sure to be impressed by the wide array of carefully selected East Asian decor. Settle in for the evening with a cup of chai on one of the comfortable couches and enjoy a movie in front of the TV or a quiet night of reading by the wood-burning fireplace.

Guests will be thrilled with the open-concept kitchen, large enough for multiple cooking partners, drifting snackers, and culinary purveyors. Fully equipped with large appliances and household cooking utensils, your group will be set for a truly home-cooked meal while on vacation. Make sure not to miss out on the fantastic morning spread for coffee with a coffee grinder, coffee maker, and even an espresso maker! Gather round the six-person table for a caffeine filled day-planning meeting, or slow things down with a decaf espresso with dessert after a romantic dinner.

Perfect for traveling couples of any age, Two bedrooms of this home are located on the first floor. The first master suite has a king-size bed and en suite bathroom, while the second bedroom with a queen bed located just down the hall. There is a queen bedroom, gas fireplace and spacious conference/meeting space downstairs, accessible by a spiral staircase from the living room. The dynamic and multi layered design of this home makes it ideal for up to six adults traveling together!

Luxuriate in the convenience of amenities such as a washer/dryer, three parking spaces, and cable TV. In order to maintain the serene and unique atmosphere in this home, the owners do ask that guests take off their shoes at the front door.

While in Albion don't miss out on a gourmet three-course dinner at the Ledford House, featuring a rotating menu and nightly specials such as Fisherman's Stew or Steak Au Poivre. Go for a more casual feel and grab a quick breakfast or lunch at the Flats Cafe, locally beloved for their great carrot cake and fresh made pizzas! Let your wild side emerge with a trip to the B Bryan Preserve, just a 45 minute drive and whole world of an experience away!

Traveling groups looking to unlock the sophistication, uniqueness and enchanting qualities of Northern California will find it all in this three bedroom vacation rental. Fit for up to six adults, everyone is sure to find at least a few great highlights from their stay at the Sky Song.

