This is a classic Meadow House vacation home in Sunriver, a family-friendly resort community that boasts world-class golf courses, hiking and biking trails, and year-round activities. 17 Meadow House is the lower level of a duplex in the highly sought after Meadows area near golf courses, the SHARC aquatic center, and the fun-filled Village. Having had only one owner since it was built, this home has been very well maintained. Cozy and all on one level, it's the perfect place for a family or group of friends to get away from it all and have the ultimate Sunriver adventure!

The exterior boasts two private decks, one enclosed for privacy and one that views a lovely green area out the back. Spend lazy summer days out on the deck, just sitting back, relaxing, and enjoying the peace and quiet. Inside, it's just as serene, with vaulted wood ceilings, a large wood-burning fireplace, and comfortable furnishings that will thoroughly charm you and your group. Enjoy time with family and friends after an action-filled day of golfing, floating the river, or having fun at SHARC.

There's a large flatscreen TV with cable and a DVD player in the living room for movie nights and plenty of room for everyone to find their favorite spot. On chilly high desert evenings, a favorite activity may well be just hanging out together in front of a toasty fire, playing board games and talking about the day's adventures.

A full kitchen has everything needed to make meals and snacks. Whether it's coffee and biscuits and gravy in the morning or a giant spinach salad for a light dinner, you'll have it all covered. There's even a gas grill on the deck for barbecues on nice evenings. And with both and outdoor and indoor seating areas, you can dine indoors or al fresco style out on the deck.

There are two large bedrooms - one has a queen sized bed, flat screen TV, comfy reclining chair, and a door out to a deck. The second bedroom has two twin beds and large floor to ceiling windows for a nice view of the surrounding greenery. There is also a sleeper sofa in the main room, which allows up to six people plenty of room to stretch out and relax. This home is also dog friendly with a $10 per pet, per day fee ($40 minimum per stay) so you don't need to leave your furry friends behind!

With extra wide hallways, and two easily accessible full bathrooms, this home is also perfect for any individuals who just aren't as mobile as they used to be, or for little ones that haven't learned about stairs yet. There's also has a laundry room with a full sized washer and dryer for the convenience of always having clean clothes while on vacation!

Sunriver has over 33 miles of paved bike trails and plenty of shopping and dining options in the charming Village at Sunriver, so there's always something to do right outside your front door. If you're looking for even more outdoor fun, SHARC is only a 10 minute walk away. Sunriver's newest attraction, this facility has swimming pools, a lazy river, and hot tubs. Best of all, this home comes with six unlimited use SHARC passes, so you'll be able to enjoy it all as often as you want. In winter, Mt. Bachelor Ski Resort is less than a 30 minute drive away!

For a fun day trip any time of year, head to Bend, also only a 30 minute drive from Sunriver. Spend the afternoon browsing through galleries on Wall and Bond streets, walking around Drake Park, and then stopping at Deschutes Brewery Public House for pints of Mirror Pond Pale Ale and boar meatloaf sandwiches before returning home to your comfortable Meadows home.

This Sunriver getaway has it all - an exceptional location, great value, and a cozy, well-maintained atmosphere. You will definitely enjoy your time at 17 Meadow House!

