Get swept away in this charming five-bedroom Sunriver vacation rental with pet-friendly accommodations, brand new hot tub, a wood-burning fireplace, and a deck. It's ideal for up to 10 guests. The Art House is a historic lodge combining elegance and a rugged outdoor location. Plan your next mountain getaway or even corporate retreat today!

The Art House was the music and art building for the Old St. Francis School in the early 1920s. The school was restored by McMenamins and transformed into a bohemian hotel in downtown Bend. The Art House was moved into its current location, but has been preserved to reflect the art and history of the original building.

Rich in culture and surrounded by nature, thus fabulous home is within walking distance to the Deschutes River and the Village at Sunriver is only two miles away for restaurants and shopping. Ski at Mt. Bachelor just 19 miles away, trek through ferns 35 miles away at the Deschutes National Forest, or hike to waterfalls just eight miles away at the Trail to Benham Falls!

Inside, the home is warm and wrapped in windows, offering carved-wood furniture, immaculate floral decor, and original artwork. Curl up around the wood-burning fireplace in the living room or watch the snowfall on windowpanes outside. This historic home boasts modern media amenities including a Blu-ray DVD library, two cable TVs, and streaming Netflix. WiFi and even a sound dock are provided so you can remain plugged into work emails and your favorite playlist!

Beyond the living room is a cheery kitchen with old time charm like a vintage sink and floral painted cabinets and murals. Prepare a holiday feast with help from modern kitchen appliances, or enjoy comfort food like tomato soup and grilled cheese sandwiches on the rustic kitchen table for two. The formal dining room, which is currently being renovated, offers seating for 12 and dramatic French doors lead to the deck.

The Art House has five lovely bedrooms and two full baths providing space for 10 guests. You can bring two dogs here (please note an additional pet fee)!

The gorgeous bedrooms are sure to inspire sweet dreams and a fantastic night's sleep. Each of the five bedrooms offer a queen-size bed, and an eclectic sleeping porch offers a twin bed for more sleeping options.

A second living room provides extra space to stretch your legs. This inspiring room offers floor-to-ceiling windows, cozy upholstered furniture, and carved-wooden accent furniture. Unwind with a movie on the flatscreen TV, or choose a book from the library and let your mind wander among the art history!

Outside, this bright orange and teal trimmed home is surrounded by a one acre wooded lot in the process of a revitalization. Enjoy a cup of coffee on the front porch steps or lounge on the private back patio. Write the next great American novel out back or throw shrimp and asparagus on the gas grill for a spring barbeque. An outdoor firepit overlooks the meadow and creates an intimate space to sing songs around the ember glow!

You can plan a day trip sampling cheese and wine at Volcano Vineyards, and then gaze into the starry night sky at the Oregon Observatory at Sunriver. View artisan wares from more than 30 local artists at the Artists' Gallery, and tribal history at the Museum at Warm Springs. Drive just 19 miles to Bend for fine restaurants, boutiques, and breweries!

Plan your next great getaway whitewater rafting with Sun Count Tours, or mountain bike through waterfalls with the Paulina Plunge. Launch your boat or drop a fishing line at the Sunriver Marina, or ride horseback over 900 acres at the Brasada Ranch Equestrian Center. Top off your day with a soak in the hot tub.

Unhinge your imagination at this lovely Central Oregon vacation rental. The art-filled walls come alive with rich history and beauty of bygone times, so book your trip today and add to the fantastic storyline!

