Forest views with community pool, tennis, and more!

When you stay in this cozy two-bedroom Sunriver vacation rental, you might feel as though you're staying in a resort-within-a-resort. With its own seasonal tennis court, swimming pool, and hot tub, the Quelah community offers a bit of insulation from the weekend crowds while still keeping you in the heart of all the action of Sunriver.

Just 18 miles from Bend, and about 21 miles from Mt. Bachelor, this home is a great year-round destination.

This lovely retreat offers the perfect mix of rustic central Oregon charm along with all the modern comforts of home. For instance, in the great room, a cable TV with DVD player is set into the beautiful stone facade of the wood-burning fireplace. With sliding glass doors leading out to the patio, you can enjoy the lovely forest views even while watching the big game from the cozy sofa.

On the opposite side of the great room, the fully-equipped kitchen is stocked with pots and pans, dinnerware, cooking utensils, and the all-important dishwasher for easy cleanup. The kitchen overlooks the dining table and living area, so that the amateur chef in your group can still socialize with everyone while preparing meals.

If you'd like to enjoy the fresh air even while cooking dinner, head to the entrance courtyard where a gas grill awaits for summer barbecues! Out back, shady aspen trees make the rear deck and backyard feel wonderfully private, offering a perfect spot to sip your morning coffee and listen to the birds sing.

The condo has two bedrooms furnished with flexibility in mind. The master has a  king bed, private entrance to the back patio, and attached bath with lovely tiled accents. The second bedroom has two twin beds and its own bath, and the living room's sofa unfolds into a very comfortable full-sized bed. Up to six guests may share the space, making it equally well-suited for a romantic weekend, outdoors adventure with the kids, golf retreat, or girls' getaway. And you don't need to leave any member of the family behind: well-behaved dogs are welcome for an additional $10 per pet, per night fee ($40 minimum per stay).

With a washer/dryer and wireless Internet access provided, the condo is wonderful for longer stays or working vacations. In the winter months, skiers and snowboarders will find the slopes of Mt. Bachelor waiting only 20 minutes away, and the nearby Village at Sunriver offers a seasonal ice-skating rink in addition to its boutiques, restaurants, brewery, and outfitters.

While the Quelah community offers a wealth of amenities for its lucky guests, all the amenities of Sunriver will be at your fingertips in this centrally-located condo. Woodlands Golf Course lies just minutes to the north and Meadows to the south, with the Nature Center, Fort Rock Park, and the Village at Sunriver within easy reach. Your stay even includes six unlimited passes to SHARC, the brand-new aquatic center with year-round spas, saunas, swimming pools, and tubing hill. Almost 40 miles of paved bike paths criss-cross the resort, and of course the surrounding forests are full of trails for hiking and mountain biking.

Discover for yourself why this special community is considered one of Sunriver's best! And if you are traveling with a larger group, please inquire about booking this unit alongside one of our other professionally managed Quelah condos to make your Central Oregon vacation rental especially memorable.

