One of the newest homes in the original heart of Sunriver awaits your next golf getaway or ski weekend! With two master suites and a private outdoor hot tub, this well-appointed getaway offers well appointed amenities in a very comfortable and cozy family-friendly home. All the shopping and dining of the Village at Sunriver are just a short walk away, but the home feels very peaceful nestled in the evergreens quiet Jay Lane.

This lovely cabin in the woods is perfect for a few couples traveling together or even a dual-family vacation. In the airy great room, vaulted windows overlook the surrounding forest, and an open floor plan makes it easy for your whole group to spend time together. In the seating area, a plush sectional sofa sits before the handsomely tiled gas fireplace and a cable TV with DVD player. On chilly winter nights, there is no better spot for a movie night!

Just behind the living area, the open kitchen makes it easy for the chef in the group to socialize with other guest while making use of the updated appliances and well-stocked cabinets (all the pots and pans, dishes, cooking utensils, and dinnerware you might need is provided). Four stools line the breakfast bar for casual snacking or sipping on a glass of wine, and a six-person dining table sits before the towering windows so you can enjoy the forest views while you eat.

Of course, in warmer weather, you can head to the outdoor patio to soak up the sunshine and fresh mountain air. Plenty of seating is provided for outdoor dining or an afternoon game of cards, and the nearby hot tub is surrounded by a half-wall for extra privacy. After a day spent hiking, fishing, skiing, or simply window-shopping, nothing feels better than soaking under the stars!

The home has three bedrooms and three full baths, and has been thoughtfully designed to provide extra space for two couples or families vacationing together. The traditional master bedroom has a king bed, television set, and attached bath. The second master bedroom is in the beautifully refurbished garage, carefully transformed to provide a separate suite with queen bed, sitting area with cable TV/DVD player, private bath, and easy access to the hot tub and deck. The third bedroom has a comfortable queen-sized bed and its own television set.

Older guests or those with mobility issues will find the house quite accessible, with virtually no stairs and a walk-in shower. Those planning longer stays will certainly appreciate the on-site washer/dryer and wireless Internet access.

This special getaway has a fantastic location in the original heart of Sunriver, but is considerably newer and brighter than most of its neighboring homes. Few other vacation rentals offer the same combination of such a central location and modern amenities, making this house a unique find! One of Sunriver's 37 miles of paved bike paths passes right by the house, and within a mile of your front door are many of the town's most popular destinations: shopping and dining at the Village, indoor swimming pools and year-round tubing hill at SHARC, and golfing at the Meadows, which offers 18 lushly landscaped holes as well as an all-ages putting course.

At any time of year, Sunriver offers amazing access to the best outdoor activities in central Oregon, from rafting the Deschutes River, to hiking through the national forest, to world-class skiing at Mt. Bachelor (only 20 minutes away). Whether you are planning a girls' getaway, golfing retreat, romantic weekend, or just a good old-fashioned family vacation, this special Sunriver getaway will make you feel right at home in the heart of all the action!

