Classic and cozy Sunriver condo next to SHARC!

Come explore the Central Oregon's most popular, year-round resort community! This two-story, free standing condominium is just a stone's throw from the Village at Sunriver, the Sunriver Resort, and - best of all - less than a block from SHARC, Sunriver's amazing aquatic facility! The whole family will appreciate being close to all the area's outdoor fun like tennis, golf, and Deschutes River activities.

When you step inside, you'll feel right at home! With its rustic wood paneling, slanted ceilings, and comfortable leather furniture, this house has both coziness and a simple style. A gas fireplace adds to the ambiance and there's also a TV with cable. Snuggle down into the couch and use the WiFi to plan the next day's excursions, or just spend time in this room socializing with the group.

An open, full kitchen has all the appliances you'll need for fixing meals and snacks for the family. Plenty of counter space gives you room to work and create scrumptious breakfasts, lunches, and dinner. There's a separate dining area with a table, and extra spots at the breakfast bar for chips and salsa and cold beer anytime of day.

Out on the deck, you'll have a gas grill for outdoor cook-outs on nice evenings. And since this is sunny Central Oregon, most evenings are definitely nice!

The main floor has two large bedrooms with king-size beds. Each room has wood paneling, comfortable bedding, bedside tables, and reading lamps. There's also a full bathroom with a a walk-in shower.

Upstairs, a loft bedroom has two twin beds and is a great space for the kids. The room looks down over the main floor but is still secluded from the rest of the house. A perfect playroom! There's also a full bathroom upstairs with a shower/tub combo. This home will sleep six guests comfortably and also includes a washer and dryer for keeping everyone in clean socks.

This perfectly-situated vacation home is right in the middle of all that's happening in Sunriver! The nearby Village at Sunriver has plenty of spas, shopping, dining, and even a seasonal ice-skating rink. Your group will also have a blast at SHARC's pools, play areas, and year-round tubing hill. And best of all, this home comes with six free SHARC passes!

In winter, Mt. Bachelor is only 18 miles away for skiing and snowboarding, and cross country skiing and snowshoeing trails are abundant in the national forest lands right by the house. If you're considering a trip around the holidays, Sunriver Stables offers horse-pulled sleigh rides in Victorian-style sleighs between late November and February. So festive!

Anytime of year, a visit to the Sunriver Brewhouse will result in pints of Stargazer Black Ale and plates of delicious brewhouse tacos and grilled Columbia River steelhead sandwiches. Really, no matter when you choose to visit Sunriver, 14 Pole House is a fantastic home base for a memorable family getaway in Central Oregon's high desert!

