You'll really be able to get away from it all when you arrive at this lovely, two-bedroom La Pine vacation rental! And don't worry about pet sitters, this Sunriver region retreat is even pet-friendly, so you can bring along your furry family members.

Although right near Sunriver Resort, this secluded cabin is not a part of the resort and does not have access to its amenities. But, with a great location right near La Pine State Park and Fall River access, you'll have plenty to keep you occupied. There are gorgeous mountain views from the property's 40 acres, and if you need a little excitement, it's just 18 miles to Bend proper for gallery browsing, brewery hopping, and great shopping!

This modern log cabin is charming on the outside and just as delightful on the inside! You'll have tall, slanted ceilings, hardwood floors, and a wood-burning fireplace. Snuggle up in front of the fire on a cozy evening and read. While you won't have a TV here, you will have WiFi, so you can still keep in touch and entertained.

Have your meals at the rustic dining table, while the sun streams in or the colors from the sunset provide a lovely backdrop for dinner. There are also a couple of spots along the breakfast bar for a kids' table or for quick snacks before heading off on a hike.

The full kitchen has everything you'll need for meals including a dishwasher and plenty of counter space. Stop at the store in town and pick up some groceries for wonderful vacation meals. And if you do crave a meal out, all of Bend's eateries are just a 35-minute drive away.

At the end of your fun-filled days, two bedrooms provide space for up to six guests. The master has a king bed, while the second bedroom hosts a twin bunk bed set and a full bed, and out in the living room, there is a sofabed for even more sleeping options. If you do bring your dogs, it's just an additional nightly fee.

Other amenities at this relaxing getaway include a washer and dryer for clean clothes. You will also have two full bathrooms - one being the private bathroom just for the master bedroom.

While here, Oregon's vibrant high desert will be the location for a memorable family getaway or even a relaxing, stay-cation if you live in the area. Boasting a sense of serenity and privacy, 40-acres to explore, and even access to the Fall River (perfect for fly fishing!), this will be a one-of-a-kind retreat! Spend your days hiking and biking, or head to town for some big city excitement.

Sisters is about a 45-minute drive from here for the rodeo and you can be skiing at Mt. Bachelor in about 30 minutes.  And for a truly unique adventure, the Paulina Plunge is a Sunriver guided mountain bike tour that includes waterfalls and gorgeous natural rock water slides. But really, your favorite activity might just be lounging on the patio listening to the birds or cuddled around the fire with mugs of hot cocoa!

Come explore the popular La Pine area at this relaxing and private Central Oregon vacation rental!

