Located close enough to walk or bike to the Aquatic Center, Sunriver Village Mall, or the Lodge, this charming retreat is a great home base. While here, head out on some of Sunriver Resort's 40 miles of paved multi-use trails on foot or on two wheels. And at just 18 miles from Bend, you can be brewery-hopping, browsing galleries, or even spending a day in the Old Mill District after just a short and scenic car ride.

After a day of skiing at Mt. Bachelor or hiking around the resort, return to your cozy escape for an evening in front of the wood-burning stove for a some cable TV or a movie on the DVD player or VCR. You'll also find a collection of board games to spread out on the coffee table, so you can gather the whole family around for a game night. And on sunny days (the norm in Central Oregon!), you'll have plenty of skylights throughout this charming home to let in a lot of natural light!

The full kitchen has everything you'll need (even a dishwasher) for whipping up a meal whether you're planning on assembling everyone around the dining room table for a hearty stew or just planning a quick breakfast in the morning. There also WiFi, so getting online to find a recipe for dinner is no problem here.

