When you step inside, you'll feel the luxury and warmth of the log home with views from the kitchen, large dining table, great room, and both lower and upper bedrooms. The home includes two stone fireplaces and an outdoor fire pit, great for s'mores and relaxing under the stars. A hot tub awaits you on a massive patio and deck, with music speakers for entertainment. If adventurous, a cold dip in the Deschutes River is right outside the door - along with a second riverfront deck just above the bank!

The spacious living room boasts many comfortable spots to put your feet up and relax, as well as a large flatscreen TV to pass the time when you're not out exploring. In addition, all rooms have HDTV and a BluRay/DVD player. WiFi, Netflix, and Hulu are available in every room! There's also a PS3 game system along with a workout bike upstairs in a fun bedroom with its own microwave, sink, and refrigerator.

Whether you're making a multi-course, sit-down meal or just divvying up a take-out pizza, the full kitchen has got you covered. You'll have beautiful, high-end stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, and stylish wooden cabinetry. A kitchen island provides lots of extra work space for pulling together a summer soiree you won't soon forget. This spacious gourmet kitchen will also work well for outside caterers preparing food for a party or celebration.

When you do want to sit down to a meal, there are a couple of choices. The beautiful custom wood dining table seats up to 10 guests, with two more stools at the granite island. However, on nice sunny days, you might want to consider the picnic table down by the river or the deck, with its stunning river and mountain views. And don't forget about the hot tub! Spend chilly evenings surrounded by warmth, soaking while looking up at the stars.

The four bedroom plus loft home, which also includes four bathrooms, will assure that each of the 10 guests can find their own perfect spot for sleeping. There are two king beds, two queens, two cozy alcove twin beds, and an American Leather sleeper sofabed. Each room has a special name: Deschutes, Nez Perce, Bachelor, and Nicklaus, which are decorated or have amazing views to enhance their uniqueness. Upstairs, there is a great quiet office or crossword puzzle space with a cozy bench to sit and relax and see the views.

This Central Oregon vacation rental is right on Spring River Road, the main road to Mt. Bachelor, so a day of skiing and snowboarding is only a 25 minute drive away. Even closer is access to snowshoeing, cross-country skiing, and snowmobiling. Many of the Cascade Lakes and rivers are minutes away for amazing fishing, boating, or other water activities.

The driveway can accommodate a snowmobile trailer in winter and a boat trailer in summer. While kayaks and boats are not provided at the home due to insurance limitations, if you bring or rent your own, you can launch your kayak right from the dock or bank right at the house... or, start a little ways upstream and float down to the house! Outfitters like Good2Go Food & Fun in Sunriver can help you plan your activities, and have kayaks, canoes, stand-up paddle boards, tubes, rafts, floats, snowskates, sleds, snowshoes, and snowmobile rentals.

For the golfers of the group, some of Central Oregon's greatest golf courses or only minutes away: Crosswater, Sunriver Resort's Woodlands or Meadows courses, Widgi Creek, Lost Tracks, Pronghorn, and more!

A haven for outdoor enthusiasts, seasonally, you may be able to fish, canoe, or kayak in the Deschutes River right from the property. Nearby, there's also great hiking, biking, rock climbing, and whitewater rafting. And there's no need to stay clean while out having your adventure - back at the house you'll even have a mud room connected to a washer and dryer. The outside two-acre yard is great for the right approved pets, along with a large dog kennel connected to the house and direct access into the garage. Bikes are also available in the attached garage for use in the nearby 30  miles of trails in Sunriver.

