The condo offers all the comforts of home and has plenty of space for up to six guests. After a long day spent playing tennis, kayaking the Deschutes River, or simply shopping in the Village, everyone can gather in the living room for a movie night before the cable TV with DVD player.

Walk across the street to dine at one of the nearby restaurants, or prepare your own meals in the fully-equipped kitchen. You'll find all the pots and pans, dinnerware, and cooking utensils needed, plus the all-important dishwasher for easy clean-up. The dining table seats six, and there are two stools at the breakfast bar so guests can sip a glass of wine and chat with the chef. On warmer evenings, head out to the back deck for a barbecue around the gas grill or to dine at the patio table in the fresh air.

Each of the three bedrooms has a comfortable queen bed, and there is one full bath for smooth morning routines. There is a washer/dryer, which makes it easy to keep up with wet bathing suits and well-worn hiking clothes.

And you will want that bathing suit! Staying at the condo entitles you to six complimentary passes to SHARC, the brand-new aquatic center with swimming pools, lazy river, tennis courts, and hot tub less than a mile from your front door. The surrounding national forest is full of hiking trails, fishing holes, and kayaking runs; in the winter, Mt. Bachelor is just twenty minutes away for all your skiing and snowboarding needs. Of course, the resort and its surrounding area have a handful of excellent golf courses, with the Meadows being the closest to the condo.

More adventuresome types can book a guided fishing expedition or whitewater rafting trip at one of the trusted outfitters, while the young-at-heart will love playing a round of mini-golf or hopping in the bumper cars. In the winter, take a spin around the ice-skating rink, followed by a cappuccino at the Italian cafe. And when you're finally ready to leave all the activity behind, you only need to walk across the street to your private Central Oregon getaway.

