This charming, one-bedroom loft Sunriver vacation rental is stocked with everything you'll need for a restful and adventure-filled resort getaway! This cute and welcoming  retreat is filled with books, a wonderful wood-buring fireplace for toasty nights by the fire, and of course, access to all of Sunriver Resort's amenities like SHARC (the Sunriver Homeowners Aquatic & Recreation Center), miles of hiking and biking trails, horse stables, tennis courts, and more!

This location at Sunriver Resort is just over 15 miles from Bend, where you can spend the day exploring the shops and galleries along Wall and Bond streets, check out the local brewery scene, or spend an afternoon wandering through exhibits at the High Desert Museum. Sisters (38 miles north) is also an option for a  fun day trip, and in winter the drive to Mt. Bachelor only takes about 30 minutes. You can even catch a shuttle right from Sunriver Resort (a nominal fee applies).

Your woodland cabin is a pleasantly-updated, rustic getaway with exposed wood beams, wood paneling, and a warm and inviting interior throughout. Come back from skiing or hiking to a spread of appetizers out on the coffee table and a glass of wine in front of the fire. Entertainment options here include WiFi, cable TV, a DVD player, and a stereo - plenty of choices for when you're not out taking advantage of all of Sunriver's activities.

The compact but fully-stocked kitchen includes all major appliances (including a dishwasher), as well as gadgets like a coffee grinder and a toaster. Make a filling brunch before you head off on a nature hike or sleigh ride and at night, dinner can be at the large wooden dining table, if you want to stay in. Out on the deck, you'll also have a gas grill for sunny afternoon, outdoor feasts.

The bedroom and loft hold a king-size bed, a queen, and one twin, making this Sunriver getaway ideal for a maximum of six guests. With large beds for two couples, the sofa and twin bed can accommodate up to two kids. There is a half-bath in addition to the full bathroom for added convenience, and a stacked washer and dryer in case you need to do laundry during your vacation.

Set on over 3,000 acres in Oregon's high desert, Sunriver Resort is filled with activities for every member of your family! There are pools, hot tubs, and saunas at SHARC, four golf courses, including the award-winning Crosswater, 26 tennis courts, 40 miles of paved, multi-use trails, and the restaurants and shops of Sunriver Village Mall.

Mt. Bachelor is close enough to spend your days skiing and snowboarding, and if you just want to stay close to the resort, you can take a unique one-horse open sleigh ride, complete with a festive, Victorian sleigh and gorgeous views of the surrounding mountains and Sunriver Meadow. It's about an hour's drive to Fort Rock State Natural Area if you want to do some rock-climbing or just hike around this gorgeous natural area. But really, you may just spend all of your time at the resort - hiking, biking, and relaxing in your cozy cabin in the woods.

Plan an unforgettable Sunriver adventure with a stay at this Central Oregon vacation rental for fun in the sun, a skiing retreat, or just a family getaway to enjoy deluxe resort amenities.

