This unique contemporary Sunriver vacation home sits on a large corner lot, perfectly perched between the famous SHARC Aquatic (with passes included with your rental!) and Fort Rock Park. Miles of trails surround the home, stretching forever from the high desert to the rambling Deschutes River for fishing.

Guests to this special home especially love the great room, with its vaulted wood ceiling and two-story stone fireplace. Five expansive windows bring nature's views indoors, whether on snowy moonlight nights or on a crystal clear morning watching the deer pass through the yard. To get a little closer, step through the French doors to the large wraparound deck.

In the great room, relax by the flatscreen TV with a DVD player, or settle at the game table with ten board games. Enjoy your favorite music on the stereo system with CD player, or browse restaurant reviews on the free WiFi. Relax by the fireplace for a little romance, or gather around the handsome large dining table for quiet dinners or entertaining for many. The fully equipped kitchen is perfect for the gourmet chef, with granite countertops, updated appliances, and a dishwasher for easy clean-up. There is also a washer/dryer provided in the laundry room.

The main floor includes the master suite, with a queen bed and adjoining full bath. Then move to the loft-style second floor with two bedrooms. A queen bedroom is joined via a Jack and Jill bath to the third bedroom, which offers a double bed, twin bunk beds, and TV, all with views overlooking the great room and fireplace.

