Take your boat and dock it at this traditional riverfront Sunriver vacation rental. This one-story, spacious home has been recently renovated, from the carpet to the windows to bathrooms. It's the perfect spot for a guys' fishing getaway or a family or two that wants to be on the river.

You're right on the Deschutes River, just steps away from the water and quiet spots to contemplate life. Downtown Bend is only 22 miles away and the family-friendly slopes of Mt. Bachelor are only 25 miles from here.

This relaxing home boasts comfortable furnishings. The living room features new carpet as well as two traditional floral couches and a large flatscreen, cable-ready TV. There's also a stereo nearby to play your tunes so you'll be vacation ready in no time.

The kitchen is roomy and offers plentiful counter space to make your vacation meals. There's a large fridge, dishwasher, stove, and a two-seat stool set for quick breakfasts. An eight-seat dining room table awaits your formal dinners.

A family room sits off to the side with a lovely leather couch and cozy wood stove. But it's the gorgeous pool table that dominates the space. One wonders how many nights you'll be perfecting your game here. Sliding glass doors lead to a gorgeous deck with a firepit for marshmallow roasting and ghostly tale-telling.

The bedrooms and baths have been updated to reflect a comfortable but elegant decor. The master features a king bed in a large wood frame, sloped ceilings, a flatscreen TV, and a rocking chair. There's a large renovated bathroom nearby.

A second bedroom affords guests a queen bed in a wood frame under a striped coverlet and a third bedroom features a twin-over-full bunk bed, perfect for the younger members of your party. There's also another full bath down the hall. With the addition of the sofabed, this home can comfortably accommodate up to eight people!

Stay connected via the free WiFi and freshen your laundry at the provided washer and dryer. Games and books are available but you'll probably be spending most of your time on the water, either whiling away the hours or exploring the river. Guests are welcome to store their boats in the large circular driveway as well.

Oregon's high desert is the perfect place to relax and unwind. You can book fly fishing tours or ski lessons or perfect your kayaking technique. There are four golf courses nearby to improve your handicap or you can plan a special meal in any of the area towns nearby. It has something for everyone.

This updated traditional Central Oregon vacation rental offers the perfect escape from the everyday. Book it today!

