With a chef's kitchen, private hot tub, and wonderful location in the desirable Circle Four Cabin community, this elegant three-bedroom Sunriver vacation condo makes for a particularly luxurious Sunriver getaway! The space feels perfectly Oregonian with its mountain decor, but those beautiful hardwood furnishings and Western touches are anything but rustic. Recently remodeled, the condo offers all the modern comforts and conveniences of home.

The aquatic center is just one mile away from your cabin door, a very short bike ride along one of the many paved paths criss-crossing the resort. Also within easy reach are the Nature Center, Fort Rock Park's playing fields and tennis courts, the marina, horseback riding stables, and the Village at Sunriver. In this lively cluster of restaurants and shops, you can enjoy a freshly brewed beer or cup of coffee, book a guided expedition along the Deschutes River, and even enjoy a twirl around the seasonal ice skating rink in the winter months.

All the activity in the cabin will gravitate toward the spacious great room, which has vaulted ceilings and a beautiful river rock fireplace for chilly winter evenings. Curl up on the handsome sofa with a soft throw blanket and enjoy a cozy movie night or long conversation over a bottle of wine.

On the other end of the great room, the kitchen is both beautiful and functional. It was recently remodeled with brand-new stainless steel appliances, and the cabinets are well-stocked with all the pots and pans, dishes, dinnerware, cooking utensils, and glassware you need to prepare meals for a group.

You can dine at the six-person table near the fireplace, or head out the sliding glass doors to the private deck to enjoy the fresh mountain air as you eat. There is also a gas grill for summer barbecues, and of course the private hot tub that will soothe your sore muscles after a long hike or day of skiing.

The main floor has two bedrooms and a full bath with a tub/shower combo, making the condo appropriate for guests who would prefer to avoid climbing stairs. One of the downstairs bedrooms has a beautiful queen bed, and the second has two twin-sized beds; each has its own TV set. A laundry room sits between the two bedrooms, making it easy to keep up with hiking clothes and fishing gear.

The upper level is entirely devoted to the vaulted master suite. With its queen-sized bed, cozy window seat, flat-screen TV with DVD player, and private bath, the spacious suite makes a wonderful oasis within the home itself.

The cabin also includes complimentary wireless Internet access, a nice assortment of books and games, and five adult bicycles for your use!

The Circle Four community is one of the most popular in Sunriver, mostly because it offers the unique amenity of a private on-site pool. Of course, your stay in the cabin also includes the use of eight unlimited passes to SHARC, the brand-new aquatic center with indoor/outdoor swimming pools and year-round tubing hill.

Beyond the borders of Sunriver, year-round opportunities to enjoy the surrounding Deschutes National Forest await: skiing on Mt. Bachelor, fly fishing, hiking, mountain biking, snowboarding, kayaking, and much, much more.

Whether you are planning a romantic retreat for two, a ski weekend with friends, or just a good old-fashioned family vacation, this luxury Central Oregon vacation cabin in the heart of Sunriver won't disappoint!

