This two-bedroom, pet-friendly Bend vacation rental is located right near Sunriver Resort and is perfect for getting back to nature. It offers a beautiful mountain lodge-themed interior and pet-friendly accommodations in the heart of Central Oregon. During your stay, you'll also have a private hot tub, a sun-filled loft with an entertainment area, plenty of space in the driveway for various toys like boats and ATVs, and a great home base for skiing, rafting, golfing, and more!

Located about a 20-mile drive from bustling downtown Bend, this quiet and lovely retreat is surrounded by pine trees, fresh air, and trails. Sunriver Resort is four miles away, just across the Deschutes River, and close to Cascade Mountain Lakes. In winter, Mt. Bachelor is just 18 miles northwest.

This home's large driveway makes parking your dirt bikes, boat, snowmobiles, or jet skis easy. The private locked storage shed offers a safe place to put your bikes, skis, snowboards, fishing gear, and golf clubs.

Inside this cozy space, there are two levels and 1,500 square feet of living area. When you aren't out skiing or hiking, you'll have two TVs, as well as a Roku box,  which allows you to stream your personal Netflix and other online accounts, as well as a DVD player and a movie library. There's also a pellet stove to keep the living room all warm and toasty and colorful artwork on the walls.

The full kitchen has all major appliances, including a dishwasher, and gadgets like a slow cooker, toaster, and a microwave. Meals for everyone can be served around the four-seat dining table, with two spots also open at the breakfast bar.

Right off the back deck, you'll find the hot tub - perfect for after a day on the slopes. Outside, there's also a grill for preparing barbecue feasts.  You may even be able to spot white-tailed deer, rabbits, and other wildlife right from the half-acre fenced yard!

Back inside this mountain-themed chalet, the main level also has one bedroom with a comfortable queen bed, and a full bathroom.

Upstairs, the window-filled loft area has a game table, as well as the Netflix-capable TV and DVD player. There's also a futon for extra sleeping options and a game table. The second bedroom also has a queen bed and there's another bathroom with a shower on this level. Osprey Chalet can comfortably accommodate up to six guests. If you do bring your dogs (up to two), please note that there is an additional nightly fee.

Other amenities include a stereo with a iPod dock, a laundry room on the first floor, board games, and an outdoor firepit! After dinner, bring your s'mores supplies outside for a late night dessert under the stars. This home is also horse-friendly with prior approval.

When you are not soaking in the hot tub or watching movies in the loft, you can explore the nearby foothills of Mt. Bachelor and the surrounding, pristine alpine forests. Book a rafting trip on the Deschutes, go fly fishing, or make the short trip to Mt. Bachelor Resort for a day of skiing and snowboarding.

