Restored historic cottage near the Deschutes River with AC!

This historic and pet-friendly, four-bedroom Sunriver vacation rental offers a super fun, Central Oregon experience. This hip little cottage was originally part of the Old St. Francis McMenamins Hotel in Bend, Oregon. In the spirit of recycling, this home was moved to Sunriver where updates were made to accommodate a new Sunriver vacation experience.

When you stay here, you'll be near the Sunriver Resort and all its amenities. The popular Deschutes River launch point for float trips and the Sunriver Resort bike paths are only three blocks away. You can walk, run, bike, or drive to shopping, restaurants, golf, and activities.

The Trout House has an outdoorsy theme, with comfortable decor for a laid-back experience with the fun, funky charm McMenamins is known for. There are hand-painted designs throughout. A spacious living room has spots for everyone to relax and watch TV after a day of skiing, fishing, or hiking. Entertainment amenities include cable TV, a DVD Blu-ray player, iPod dock, a Wii gaming system, and WiFi.

Feel like whipping up a feast? The full kitchen has everything you'll need for vacation meals and while there's no dishwasher, you can always go on an after-dinner walk while the dishes soak.

Outside, your group has their own private sand volleyball court, firepit, and enclosed back yard. The backyard is especially nice for the kids and dogs to play (if you do bring your furry friends, there is an additional pet fee). There's plenty of seating for the whole group on the spacious deck with bright sun umbrellas and a gas grill.

At night four bedrooms include a king bed, two queens, a full-size bed, and four twins allowing up to 10 guests to comfortably stay here. There is also one full bathroom. Other amenities include a washer and dryer and central AC.

During your stay you will notice some very unique aspects to this home and property. Continuing with the recycling spirit, reclaimed redwood was used for decking and fence materials, creating a barn wood look and feel. There are also tongue and groove ceilings, kitchen tables, and benches milled from local Ponderosa pine distinct to Central Oregon.

Sunriver Village is a short mile-and-a-half drive away if you need to pick up supplies or want a bite to eat. You can also be in Bend after an 18-mile drive. Plan a day of gallery browsing and shopping, and of course in the winter you'll be near all the world-class skiing at Mt. Bachelor (18 miles)!

Water enthusiasts will be right near the Deschutes River, as well as South Twin Lake, North Twin Lake, Elk Lake, Sparks Lake, Todd Lake, Wickiup Reservoir, and Crane Prairie Reservoir. You may want to bring your boats and fishing gear or rent supplies locally for a day of fun on the water.

No matter what you choose to do in the area this Central Oregon vacation rental offers a one of a kind stay in the stunning Sunriver region!

