Sunriver Resort, nestled along the mighty Deschutes River at the base of the Cascade Mountains, is about 15 miles south of Bend. This particular home is located conveniently close (a short five-minute walk) to one of the main attractions in the community, SHARC, where you will find an enormous aquatic center that will keep you entertained no matter which season you visit.

Step inside this traditional-style home and you will immediately feel a sense of warmth from the gorgeous wood walls, cozy fireplace, and windows and skylights that let in plenty of sunlight. Have a seat on the soft couches and read a book in front of the lovely gas fireplace, or simply sit with a mug of cocoa or glass of wine and tell stories while the fire flickers gently.

Behind the living room you will find a full kitchen that is completely stocked with the tools and equipment you may need during your stay. Simply bring your own groceries, then enjoy preparing meals in this spacious, clean, and well-appointed kitchen. You will have no trouble whipping up anything, whether you envision a simple breakfast of eggs and bacon or a more elaborate Sunday brunch of mushroom quiche and French toast. Sit down at the eight-seat dining room table and enjoy a leisurely meal together to fuel up for a day of vacationing.

Upstairs in the loft area, a large sofa piled with pillows is the ideal place to lounge and watch some cable TV or use the DVD player to have a movie night. With WiFi access throughout the house you will have no trouble staying connected, and you could watch YouTube or stream music for an impromptu dance party!

This home has three bedrooms and a loft, and up to 10 guests will be perfectly comfortable spread out among the various sleeping places! You will also find three full bathrooms throughout the house, as well as a laundry room, so there's no need to worry about getting your clothes dirty while you're exploring the great outdoors.

The master bedroom, located on the ground floor, has a fabulous queen-size bed and a recently remodeled attached bathroom that will make you feel like you're in a spa. The two remaining bedrooms both have lovely queen-size beds outfitted with warm and soft linens. Upstairs, part of the loft area serves as an additional bedroom, and would be a perfect place for kids to sleep because it has two sets of twin bunks, a large flatscreen TV, and even a foosball table!

The inside of this home is fantastically warm and welcoming, but don't overlook the outside! A tree-lined yard area is the perfect place to let any children run around. This home allows you to bring along one dog (with a $10 nightly pet fee and a $40 minimum per stay), so your furry friend will love to sniff around the pine cones.

A patio area is an ideal place to sit and breathe in the fresh air, or you could take advantage of the nice weather to use the gas grill to cook up a casual barbecue for everyone. You will be delighted to find a private hot tub, just for you and your guests! Relax in the luxuriously warm, bubbling water and let all your troubles melt away.

Within the community of Sunriver, you will have access to a plethora of fun activities. Head down to the SHARC to use the shared pools, hot tubs, picnic area, playground, and sports courts. If you love to golf, be sure to check out the four golf courses throughout the resort, or you could play tennis at one of the 26 tennis courts, visit a park, or walk or bike around the 40 miles of pathways that crisscross the resort!

You could also book a horseback riding tour, get a massage at the spa, or visit the fitness center. For even more options, venture out of Sunriver; the Deschutes River is a fantastic place to go rafting, skiing at Mt. Bachelor is just a 30-minute drive away, and lakes such as Wikiup Reservoir are within a scenic hour drive.

Just a mile away from your rental home is The Village, a cluster of restaurants and shops, where you can grab a bite to eat or stock up on basics at the market. Be sure to visit the larger city of Bend, just 25 minutes up the highway and explore its many famous breweries, grab a bite to eat (try the Portuguese chicken stew at Mediterranean restaurant Cafe Sintra), and walk around the beautiful parks that line the Deschutes River.

However you choose to spend your visit, come stay at this inviting, warm, and cozy Central Oregon vacation rental and be rested and ready to have a fun-filled trip!

