44 Tennis Village will be your perfect home-away-from-home while attending your Sunriver Conference!  You are just a short walk to the Main Sunriver Lodge as well as Sage Springs Spa. You are also less than a mile from shopping at Sunriver Village Mall, the links at Sunriver Meadows Golf Course, and about three miles from Fort Rock Park where you can have a picnic and a game of tennis or horseshoes. There's fun in the water, too, at SHARC, the nearby aquatic center, with swimming pools and hot tubs. This home comes with unlimited use of 6 SHARC Passes.

Spacious and comfortable, the flood of sunlight through the floor to ceiling windows and the lovely contrast of rough-hewn woods against the white walls gives the place a warmth and intimacy belying its ample, 1400 sq. ft. of space. When it's chilly, throw a log on the gorgeous lava rock fireplace and catch your favorite show on the 42 inch flat-screen TV, watch a DVD, or dig into that magazine article you've been wanting to read. If you've got some business to do, head up to the loft, where you'll find a mini office with a desk, phone and free wireless high-speed Internet.

If you're looking to dine out, check out one of the seven restaurants in Sunriver. For many more options, make the half-hour trip to Bend. Otherwise, you'll do just fine with this fully equipped modern kitchen. Its white appliances and stone-tiled floor blends nicely with the rest of the home's decor. Your chef will be able to cook just about anything in this kitchen, complete with microwave and dishwasher. When dinner is served, sit down at the rough-hewn dining set with room for six that looks like it's been taken right out of a fairy tale!

44 Tennis Village will accommodate 6 people comfortably. The master suite is on the main floor. You'll not only have plenty of room in its big king bed, you'll also appreciate the adjoining full bath and another TV for late-night viewing. There are two queen beds, another bathroom, and yet another TV in the bedroom on the upper level. Up in the loft, there's also a day bed with a trundle.

Sunriver is flanked by the Deschutes River to the west. Throw a line in the river, ride the rapids, or take a leisurely kayak ride through the river's meandering beauty. Cyclists, bring your bikes! There are 33 miles of paved bike path leading to both pastoral beauty and shopping and dining in the Village. Deschutes National Forest is less than 10 miles to the east. That, of course, means plenty of places to hike, rock climb, or just enjoy scenic vistas. Closer to home is the SHARC aquatic center with its outdoor and indoor pools, water slides, tot pool, lazy river, and year-round tubing park. Come winter, skiers will find world class skiing at Mt. Bachelor, about a half-hour to the north. There are also sleigh rides, snowmobiling, snowshoeing, ice skating, and bonfires in the snow!

So make your next trip to Sunriver  comfortable and memorable. Stay in this beautiful condo close to all the activities and sites in the Sunriver/Bend area.

