Condo on golf course near SHARC with shared hot tub!

With two outdoor decks, a jetted soaking tub, and an unbeatable location right on the twelfth fairway of the Meadows Golf Course, this pet-friendly, two-bedroom Sunriver vacation condo offers something special for every member of the family! Within a few minutes, you can walk to shopping, dining, and galleries at the Village of Sunriver, or stroll over to SHARC to use your 6 complimentary passes to the new aquatic center, with its indoor and outdoor pools, spa, and tubing hill. And, of course, world-class golf is right outside your door.

With its central location near all the activity of Sunriver, there are plenty of ways to spend the day (whether you are a golf enthusiast or not!). Visit one of the Village's spas or browse the boutiques; head to the Deschutes River on a kayak or with a fishing pole; or rent a bicycle and explore the nearly 40 miles of paved bike paths spread throughout this forested resort destination. Of course, once the snow begins to fall, Mt. Bachelor's ski slopes are only twenty minutes away, while the ice-skating rink at the Village is just outside your front door.

The two-story condominium is part of a lovely shingle-sided duplex that makes a wonderful retreat at any time of year. In the summer, step out onto the log-hewn decks to enjoy your morning coffee in the fresh mountain air, or spend the afternoon watching the golfers on the course below. When chilly winter air blows in, curl up by one of the wood-burning fireplaces (that's right, there's two) and enjoy a cozy night in with the family.

The condo's great room and main living spaces are on the second floor, with plenty of windows allowing the sunlight to flow in and exposed timber beams for a delightfully rustic atmosphere. At one end, a cozy sofa and loveseat sit before the wood-burning fireplace, with the nearby cable TV with DVD player for movie nights.

Just past the inviting living area, a full kitchen offers everything you could need to prepare meals, including a dishwasher for easy clean-up. Choose from a perch at the breakfast bar, or gather the family around the six-person dining table for a home-cooked meal. On warmer evenings, head out to the deck with its gas grill for a barbecue!

The lower level of the house contains two bedrooms, one of which is a beautifully appointed master suite. A king-sized beds sits before a romantic wood-burning fireplace, with sliding glass doors leading to the spacious deck. The master bath has a relaxing soaking tub, the perfect spot to soothe sore muscles after a day spent whitewater rafting or swooshing down the slopes of Mt. Bachelor.

The second bedroom has two twin-sized beds and a futon, although the living room's sofa doubles as a sleeper if extra guests prefer to have a little more space. The closets are stocked with plenty of fresh linens and towels, and a washer/dryer is available for your use, as well. The house offers wireless Internet for working vacations or browsing restaurant reviews, and you can even bring the family dog along for the trip (a $10 per pet, per night fee does apply along with a $40 minimum per stay).

When you stay here at Central Oregon vacation rental, your only problem will be choosing the day's adventure!

