This luxurious home is one of the finest  Sunriver vacation rentals - perfect for families or corporate gatherings. With giant timber framing, a two-story stone fireplace and distressed hardwood throughout, it feels like you're staying in a classic mountain lodge.

The house, which overlooks the second fairway at Woodlands Golf Course, sleeps 14 and features amenities for all generations. You can enjoy a game of ping pong, play on the fabulous pool table trimmed with rustic logs, or check out the touch screen for entertainment controls. Use this screen to access thousands of songs - and to adjust the heat and air conditioning as well!

This home is great for entertaining, with a gourmet kitchen featuring two dishwashers and two sinks. It has a full serving buffet and a custom granite table that seats 14, with four more chairs at the kitchen island. You can also enjoy eating on the patio right next to the golf course. After the meal, stay outside and soak in the new eight-person hot tub, or head to the stunning living room to watch a movie or gather around the fireplace.

When you're ready to venture farther afield, you can use the seven adult bicycles to ride the miles of bike trails crisscrossing Sunriver. You can also take a short walk to the Deschutes River for fishing, floating or other fun. As another plus, the home comes with 12 free passes to SHARC, the incredible new aquatic center. You and your guests will have a blast at SHARC's pools, play areas and year-round tubing hill.

Back at Vine Maple, you'll find five bedrooms, five full baths and two half baths. Three of the bedrooms are master suites that include king beds, TVs, DVD players and mood lighting. The downstairs master suite features heated floors, a jetted tub and a touch screen for music. A queen bedroom and a bunk room with six twin beds round out the sleeping accommodations.

Vine Maple is in north Sunriver, a beautiful area that features easy access to Highway 97. The home is near a major tennis facility, a quiet pool area, and The Marketplace, which sells everything from groceries and liquor to souvenirs.

Guests who stay in this luxurious Central Oregon vacation rental lodge rave about its gorgeous design and amazing amenities, and they call it the best place to enjoy a family vacation. Why not give your family and friends a treat and find out for yourself?

