This lovely three-bedroom Sunriver vacation home is tucked away among the pine trees on a quiet cul-de-sac, yet still close to all the action of Sunriver! Walk to Fort Rock Park or to use your complimentary passes at SHARC (the brand new aquatic center with year-round facilities), take the provided bicycles out to explore the 37 miles of paved paths, then return to your Conifer Lane retreat to soak in your private outdoor hot tub.

This shingle-sided vacation home feels very laid-back and relaxing, yet offers plenty of amenities to make your stay extra-special. In the open living area, a wood-burning fireplace is built into an exposed brick hearth to make movie nights especially cozy on winter nights. Settle into the overstuffed sofa, loveseat, or armchair, each with an excellent view of the flat-screen television with cable and DVD player; or, gather the family around a board game at the coffee table.

Just beyond the living area, a dining table sits near the tall windows so you can enjoy the peaceful forest views as you share meals together. The adjacent kitchen is fully stocked with all the pots and pans, dinnerware, cooking utensils, and dishes you need to cook for a larger group, and there is even a gas grill on the spacious outdoor patio for summer barbecues.

The house has three bedrooms and two full baths, with the spacious master suite on the ground floor. Here, a king bed sits below windows overlooking the pines, and an attached bath has a walk-in shower, making the house comfortable for guests who may have mobility issues or want to avoid stairs.

Upstairs, the second bedroom has a comfortable queen bed for a second couple, and the third bedroom has two extra-long twin beds. Down in the living room, the sofa unfolds into a queen-size sleeper to accommodate extra guests, with plenty of fresh linens and fluffy towels for up to eight guests.

When your group is ready to head out and explore Sunriver, the house comes equipped with a few extra amenities to get you started! You'll find eight unlimited passes to SHARC, the resort's brand-new aquatic center with year-round facilities, and a collection of bicycles for adults and children (please bring along your own helmets) to explore the labyrinth of trails snaking through the resort. You can pedal to the Village at Sunriver, with its coffee shops, restaurants, brewery, boutiques, and galleries; each of the four Sunriver golf courses; and any number of grassy parks. The closest, Fort Rock Park, has a baseball diamond, picnic tables, and playgrounds, and lies just a few minutes' walk from your front door.

Sunriver's summer activities are well-known and nearly endless (hiking, mountain biking, golf, whitewater rafting, fly fishing, and more); but in the winter, the resort becomes an excellent playground for skiers and snowboarders. Mt. Bachelor's powdery slopes lie just twenty minutes away, and the surrounding areas are full of sledding hills, cross-country trails, and the beautiful Sunriver ice skating rink even closer to your home away from home, with plenty of hot chocolate to please the less active guests. Although, with a fire crackling in the hearth and that private hot tub waiting just inside this Central Oregon vacation rental, a quiet night in may prove irresistible!

