Huge home w/private hot tub and sauna, space for 12, pets ok

With five bedrooms and over 2,200 square feet, there's room for the whole family (including the furry, four-legged ones) to relax and enjoy a Central Oregon retreat here! This Sunriver vacation home is located on the first fairway of the Woodlands Golf Course, offering great views and numerous resort amenities.

The large and open downstairs is bright thanks to lots of large picture windows, and nicely decorated with colorful throw rugs, comfortable leather furniture, a slanted wood ceiling, and a wood burning fireplace for keeping warm on chilly, snowy evenings. Read a book while sitting on the cozy window seat or set out snacks for everyone on the coffee table, after a long afternoon hike. There's a wall-mounted, flat screen TV with cable for watching movies or the game, a surround sound stereo system, and WiFi for researching restaurants or checking email.

This open space includes a large dining room table that seats eight and extra seating right at the breakfast bar. In the kitchen you'll find everything from a refrigerator, stove/oven, and dishwasher, to a coffee grinder, a mixer, and a toaster. As easy as it'll be to go out for meals at one of the resort's six restaurants, you can just as easily prepare as many vacation meals as you'd like, right in your own kitchen - be it toast and granola to start the day or a make-your-own taco party for dinner!

Right off the living room and dining areas is a large deck overlooking the golf course. Settle back in one of the comfy Adirondack chairs and watch the action on the fairway, sip some ice tea, or enjoy a glass of wine after dinner, while enjoying the cool breeze. For an extra dose of relaxation, there's an outdoor hot tub on the deck as well. Let the water soothe your muscles while you gaze up at the stars after a full day cycling or snowshoeing on the trails at Sunriver. On nice evenings, fire up the gas grill for a steak and vegetable skewer dinner.

Two of the bedrooms are equipped with twin-over-full bunk beds, each with bright bedding and comfortable accessories. The other three bedrooms each have a king sized bed,  providing a snuggly space for everyone in your group. All of these bedrooms have stylish details and two of the king rooms even have their own have deck or balcony access. This home will comfortably sleep 12 guests, including two dogs with a $10 per day, per pet fee ($40 minimum per stay).

Additionally, there are three full bathrooms, including a Jacuzzi tub and a private sauna. Other amenities include a laundry room with a full sized washer and dryer, and a VCR, as well as a ping pong and foosball table. Everyone in your group will find something to entertainment them here, whether it's a family ping pong tournament, spending afternoons walking on the trails near the house, relaxing in the hot tub, swimming in one of the many pools, or just staying up late each night reading in bed. Also Vacasa provides 12 complimentary SHARC recreational passes, as well as North Pool passes for the maximum occupancy of this home.

Sunriver is a family friendly resort community located in the stunning Oregon high desert. With amenities like horseback riding, swimming pools, miles of paved trails, and world-class golf courses, it's no wonder that the resort is such a popular family destination!

While this home is right on the Woodlands Golf Course, the resort boasts three others - Meadows, Crosswater and Caldera Links, all offering challenging play against a scenic, high desert backdrop. Additional activities include horseback riding and sleigh rides around the holidays, miles of paved trails for biking, hiking, cross-country skiing in winter, or just walking the dogs, and the Sunriver Homeowners Aquatic & Recreation Center (SHARC), with its outdoor and indoor pools, a lazy river, two water slides, shared hot tubs, and more.

Just off the resort grounds, Sunriver is near a number of outdoor adventures, including guided outdoor tours of caves and volcanos, whitewater rafting, waterfall mountain bike tours, paintball, rock climbing, skiing at Mt. Bachelor, and fly fishing on one of the many scenic lakes and rivers in the area.

For a memorable family vacation or a getaway with friends, this comfortable five bedroom Sunriver home has it all! A great location within the resort, amazing amenities, and it has an easy commute to skiing, shopping in nearby Bend, or just exploring beautiful Central Oregon.

