when we arrived at the house, we realized the microwave was not working and the living room had popcorn kernels all over the furniture and floor. We have toddlers, so we had to pick these up so that no one choked on them. i called the property about the broken microwave and they told me someone would be by the next day. Later that day we were not able to get any hot water out of the bath tub, for my toddler's bath. the property suggested we turn up the water heater. After we turned up the water heater, the water was warmer in the house, however, there was nothing in the instructions for the house stating that we needed to turn it up to begin with. the pots and pans in the kitchen all need replacing, they are old and there was only 1 large frying pan, which makes cooking for 10 people difficult. all of the frying pans have the teflon peeling off them. the oven had a temperature probe sticking down in it, that was so low, it was almost touching any tray we put in the oven. the gas grill outside only had one tank of propane, but since the kitchen was in such poor shape, this was how we cooked most of our food. after day 2 at the house, no one had come to see the microwave so i called the property again. it was later that day when a guy came out and after looking at the microwave, he determined it was broken. he came back with another microwave shortly and left the broken microwave in the garage. the curtains or blinds in the whole house need some attention, one of the bedrooms the curtain wouldn't go down all the way and all of them didn't work so great.

list of complaints:

-popcorn kernals on floor upon arrival

-broken microwave

-oven had probe that hung down low in food and was not well vented

-stove top took a very long time to heat any pots of water, etc

-pots and pans were very old, most had teflon chipped and there was only 1 large frying pan available

