Only two blocks away, beautiful Fort Rock Park has a children's playground, tennis courts, and softball, sand volleyball, and basketball facilities. Guests have six unlimited passes to the SHARC facility with indoor/outdoor swimming pools, water slides, and lazy river is just over a mile from your door, and you can take advantage of six unlimited passes that are included with your reservation! Within two miles of your front door, you can play a round of golf and access all the dining and shopping of the Village at Sunriver.

With an open floor plan and a set of double doors leading to the sunroom and outdoor deck beyond, the main living areas of the home are always bathed in natural light.

The warm and cozy living area has an old-fashioned wood stove set into a romantic stone hearth, and tall shelves stacked with books and games. Select a title and settle into the sofa for a quiet afternoon, or grab a board game to spread out on the coffee table with the whole family. There's also a TV with satellite cable for laid-back movie nights.

Through the living room, a warm hardwood-covered solarium offers a nice break between the indoors and outdoors, with an expansive deck just beyond the ample picture windows and sliding glass doors.

The kitchen overlooks the living area, and is fully equipped with all the appliances and supplies you could need to prepare meals (including a dishwasher for easy clean-up). The six-person dining table sits beneath a lovely stained glass lamp, and there are a few additional stools at the breakfast bar.

The lower level of the home has one bedroom, furnished with one queen and one twin-sized bed. The adjacent bathroom has a door to the bedroom and the living area, for both privacy and convenience.

A staircase leads up to the spacious loft, where the second bedroom has a queen bed and private bath. While the house comfortably sleeps five adults, two to three children could easily bring along sleeping bags and bunk in the solarium's loft.

This spacious vacation rental is ideally located in the geographic center of the Sunriver Resort, allowing for plenty of peace and quiet right around you, but still close to all of the resort amenities. You can spend your days biking the nearby trails, splashing in the resort swimming pool, or hiking in the surrounding national forest; in the evening, return to all the comforts of home in your own private retreat, quietly nestled among the trees in the heart of the Sunriver resort.

If you prefer not to drive at all during your stay, you'll be able to reach everything on the resort by foot, or hop on one of the bicycles furnished for your use (including five for adults, one tandem, three children's bikes, and a bike trailer) on the resort's nearly forty miles of paved trails.

In the winter months, Sunriver is less crowded but just as lovely to visit! Of course, Mt. Bachelor is only twenty minutes away, with world-class skiing and snowboarding (not to mention some truly impressive sledding hills).

The Village at Sunriver has a seasonal ice-skating rink for magical winter nights, and you can top it all off with a hot chocolate or glass of wine in front of a crackling fire at your own Central Oregon vacation getaway.

