The spacious four bedroom vacation rental sits on an over-sized wooded lot tucked away on a quiet cul-de-sac, so you can enjoy a considerable amount of privacy and solitude while still being in the heart of the Sunriver resort. In the summer months, the most popular spot to kick back and relax in your new home-away-from-home will certainly be the expansive outdoor deck. Gather around the patio set with umbrella for a game of cards or to enjoy dinner in the fresh air.

When the air grows chilly, the beautiful great room offers a warm and cozy place for everyone in your group to gather together. Sink into the plush sofa or recliner, put a movie or the big game on the 50" flat-screen with cable and DVD player, and build a toasty fire in the handsome wood-burning fireplace. With one wall of floor-to-ceiling windows overlooking the pine trees, you can still feel as though you're in the great outdoors even while cuddled up by the hearth.

On the other end of the great room, a dining area and fully-equipped kitchen make it easy to prepare and serve meals, even for a large group. The kitchen is nicely stocked with all the pots and pans, dishes, cooking utensils, and dinnerware you might need, as well as a dishwasher for easy clean-up. The table, perfectly positioned by the sunny windows, seats six to eight guests, and there are three extra spots at the breakfast bar.

With four bedrooms and four full baths, the house has been designed to share with multiple families or several couples traveling together. Younger guests will make a beeline for the brightly-painted kids' room with a bunk bed, additional twin bed, and plenty of toys and games. The lower level also has a comfortable queen bedroom, and the living room's sofa unfolds into a sleeper for extra guests.

On the upper level, a laid-back family room separates the two master suites, each with its own king bed and private bath. Sharing the space is even easier with a washer/dryer, and each bedroom has its own TV to avoid disagreements on which movie to watch at night. There is plenty of space for up to twelve guests, with room for everyone to spread out and do their own thing, or gather together for a board game marathon or hearty breakfast.

And you'll need that breakfast! Sunriver and the surrounding area are famous for outdoor recreation of all kinds. From your front door, it's a quick walk to Fort Rock Park's playground, basketball court, or baseball diamond; meanwhile, golfers will find four courses to choose from. The resort has miles upon miles of trails for bicycling or walking, with many more challenging hikes in the surrounding national forest. Kayakers, rafters, and fishermen will love the proximity to the Deschutes River, and skiers will be in heaven with Mt. Bachelor only 18 miles away.

Less outdoorsy types can enjoy a leisurely stroll to the Village Mall for a relaxing day of browsing boutiques and art galleries (just over a mile and a half from the home) and there are two grocery stores close by for those last-minute items. And of course, kids will adore spending the afternoon at SHARC, with its indoor/outdoor pools, lazy river, and water slides.

