The house was actually better than I expected. The separation of the bedrooms, plus 4 baths, was a huge plus and provided sound sleeping for 8 people (5 adults, 3 kids). The layout would be hard to beat. The immediate environment was also great, providing a nice woodsy feel.

Although it is not next to any of the popular sunriver locations, it is close enough to not be a problem. Furnishings were nice, and the rooms are all a nice size. Extras included numerous books and maps, games, videos, TVs in every bedroom, plus family room and loft. Overall the condition was good. Unexpected extras included fishing poles and golf clubs (not tested for functionality). The spa was nice as well, the patio furniture was very comfortable. Excellent washer and dryer.

The negatives were:

No wifi. This was a serious issue for three of us, so I made numerous trips to Fort Rock park to use the public wifi. I knew it didn't have wifi, but still found it more of a problem than I expected.

Condition of the bikes. My son is able to fix almost any bike, but we were hard-pressed to get any of them functional for our use, and ended up borrowing two adult bikes from friends, and renting two bikes for the 8 and 11-year olds. Bike issues included shredded tires, wobbly axles, and many dangerously worn brake pads. Maybe others would find them useful, but we didn't. I'd suggest either fixing those that can be repaired or locking them up to avoid potential accidents.

Finally, the kitchen: silverware was of poor quality and the biggest problem was no sharp knives for cutting. We found no knives that were useful for cutting.

Regardless, we greatly enjoyed our stay and would not hesitate to rent again, especially if the wifi was added. Having the Sharc and tennis passes was a big plus, and the area offers endless opportunities for enjoyment.

We enjoyed our stay. With a few fixes identified in the property condition section of the review, this place would be very desirable. Although I knew from the description that internet access is not provided, that would be a plus if added.

