If you're looking for a cozy Sunriver retreat in a great location, 13 Juniper is the vacation home for you.

This fun house is close to all the action in town. Bring your own bicycles - or rent some - and within minutes you can pedal along a bike path to The Village for dining and shopping - or even ice skating in winter. You can even bring along your pets, though please note that a $10 nightly, per-pet fee (with a $40 minimum per stay) will apply.

You're also a stone's throw from SHARC, the amazing new aquatic center. You get eight free unlimited passes to SHARC's pools, play areas, year-round tubing hill and so much more!

The home is decorated with country touches and offers your family a comfortable place to relax and enjoy. The living room features a vaulted ceiling and a nice wood-burning fireplace where everyone can gather. As as you sit around the fire, you can even hear the quiet rumble of the train like it used to in the early days in Central Oregon.

The convenient kitchen is downstairs, too, and so is the dining area. Step out onto the deck to enjoy the mountain air, have a barbecue or soak in the hot tub.

You'll find a bedroom with a bath in the hall on the ground floor, so guests with limited mobility don't have to maneuver stairs. On the second floor, there are two bedrooms: One has a queen, and the other features a queen and a bunk bed with a double below and a twin above. There's also an extra queen tucked under the eaves.

This cozy home is perfect for a family vacation on a budget. You get all the fun of Sunriver without breaking the bank!

**Please note, this home is by the active railroad tracks**

