This attractive mountain home is a vacation treat, both inside and out. The interior features vaulted ceilings and a wood-burning fireplace, and recent updates have added handsome new flooring, kitchen appliances and granite vanities. Outdoors, there's a wonderful wraparound deck where you can enjoy the forest setting.

17 Diamond Peak is great for a family or a group of friends on a mountain retreat. It's close to shopping, dining and recreation of all kinds, including golf, tennis, biking and water sports. You're also minutes away from SHARC, Sunriver's fantastic new aquatic center. When you stay here, you receive 8 passes to SHARC's pools, play areas, lazy river, tubing hill and so much more.

The inviting home includes an open kitchen and dining area. If you prefer to eat al fresco, cook dinner on the barbecue and sit around the patio table. Afterward, a soak in the hot tub is a heavenly way to end your day.

The floor plan offers plenty of privacy and accommodates any guests with limited mobility. Downstairs, you'll find the master suite with a king bed , a walk-in shower and access to the hot tub. The upstairs has another bath, a bedroom with a queen and a fun loft with another queen bed. All the bedrooms include lovely quilts with a rustic feel.

When you come back from a day of recreation, make yourself comfortable in the living room, gathering around the fire or watching a DVD on the flat screen TV. With its wonderful location, well appointed furnishings and woodsy surroundings, 17 Diamond Peak is a fabulous spot to spend your Sunriver vacation.

