A plush brown sectional sofa is the perfect place to relax after a day of biking, hiking, or swimming at the Sunriver Homeowners Aquatic and Recreation Center (SHARC). Gather everyone around for a platter of snacks on the leather ottoman/coffee table and pop in a movie - there's a flat screen TV with cable as well as a DVD player here, a Wii game console plus games and a library of movies for you to enjoy.

The kitchen and dining room share this open space so it's easy to carry on conversations whether you're at the dining room table using the WiFi to check email, watching TV in the living room, or chopping up some vegetables in the kitchen. When you do want to prepare a meal, you'll have a stainless steel refrigerator, stove-top/oven, and dishwasher at your disposal. And on nights you don't feel like cooking, there are six restaurants right at the resort to choose from and even more options when you include the nearby towns of Bend and Sisters.

Outside on the deck, you'll have access to a gas grill for cooking up some burgers or chicken, and patio furniture if you want to stay outside and make your meal an outdoor occasion. This outdoor space is also a nice way to pass the time on a lazy sunny afternoon - just grab a book and catch up on your reading while you sip a glass of wine.

When it's time to turn in, one bedroom is a nicely-decorated with a queen sized bed, TV cabinet, and new wood furniture. You'll want to sleep in late here! For the kids, the other bedroom has twin-over-full bunk beds, as well as a trundle. They'll be room for up to six guests as this comfortably, well-laid out home!

There's one full bathroom, as well as a stackable washer and dryer in the bright laundry room - there's even a counter for folding clothes. This home also includes a CD player for listening to your favorite music, and a Wii console with games for the rare rainy day. When the sun shines, you'll find thoughtful outdoor amenities included in the home, like tennis rackets and tennis balls, sleds, and an outdoor croquet game. There's so much to do before you even consider leaving the house!

But once you do, at Sunriver Resort you'll have 35 miles of paved biking and hiking trails. The Benham Falls Loop is a short eight mile loop around the Deschutes River, or if you're feeling up to it, pedal around Sparks and Lava Lakes - an exhaustive 10 mile trail that will reward you with stunning mountain views. Golfers can choose between the Crosswater, Meadows, and Woodlands Courses, as well as the family-friendly, nine-hole Caldera Links.

In winter, borrow the sled and speed down some hills, or just make your way to SHARC for some indoor swimming. Mt. Bachelor is only a 30 minute drive away, and right from the Sunriver Lodge, you can pick up a shuttle that will take you right there (and bring you back) for $20. Year-round, use your SHARC passes to enjoy the heated indoor pool, outdoor pools, hot tubs, lazy river, tubing hill, and more.

This Sunriver vacation rental is perfect for the whole family! Plan a getaway to the Oregon high desert for fun in the sun with hiking and golfing, or a ski retreat to remember - Sunriver Resort offers it all!

