Make yourself right at home in beautiful Sunriver and settle into this cozy, family friendly vacation house. Tucked away in a wooded area near the golf course and bike path, there are two decks to enjoy, as well as a hot tub, a classic and stylish interior, and a newly renovated kitchen.

The cleanly designed living room will make you feel like you are truly in your own mountain cabin oasis. Settle down into the cushions of the comfy red sofa and talk about the day's adventures or on chilly nights, curl up with a good book and a glass of wine next to the gas fireplace. There's cable TV so you can even spend the evenings watching your favorite shows with a big bowl of popcorn. Glass patio doors let in a lot of natural light and provide easy access to a lovely outdoor deck.

After a day of fun in the sun, the newly renovated kitchen with its sleek granite counter tops and shiny stainless steel appliances will make preparing food a pleasure. It's well stocked with all of the pots, pans, and cooking utensils you need to make a tasty meal and the dishwasher will have it all cleaned up in no time.

On sunny afternoons, you can fire up the gas grill out on the deck and have an outdoor barbecue. There's a picnic table and extra seating available right on the deck, as well as a table in the dining room, with another set of glass doors right there for easy passage between inside and out. Aside from a nice al fresco dinner, this deck is the perfect place to enjoy the morning sun with a cup of coffee or just lounge about in the early evenings.

Downstairs, there are also two large comfortable bedrooms. Both have cloud-like queen sized beds, dressers, bedside tables, reading lamps, and pleasing, comfortable amenities. But best of all, the house's second, more secluded deck is accessed through sliding glass doors in both of these bedrooms. This deck is private and enclosed, with a wonderful hot tub! It's just the thing for relaxation after a day hiking or biking around Sunriver.

Moving upstairs, this floor provides its own picturesque views of the neighborhood. Great for kids, there's a large bedroom with two sets of bunk beds and a second full bathroom. Let the younger guests enjoy and take over the upstairs! There's a small loft equipped with large screen TV, perfect for movie nights. The grownups can enjoy some quality time by the fireplace downstairs or evening drinks out on the deck, while the younger guests are having their own fun upstairs.

With its three bedrooms and two full baths, up to eight guests will be very comfortable here. This home is also pet friendly and allows your furry canine family members to join in the fun with a $40 minimum fee ($10 per pet, per day).

Sunriver is a family-friendly resort community that boasts world-class golf courses, over 33 miles of paved bike trails, and plenty of shopping and dining options in the charming Village at Sunriver. There's even a seasonal ice-skating rink. And at this house, you are right in the middle of it all!

Looking for even more outdoor fun? SHARC is only a 10 minute bike ride away. Sunriver's newest attraction, this is a a fully outfitted aquatic center with swimming pools, a lazy river, and hot tubs. This home comes with eight unlimited use SHARC passes, so you'll be able to enjoy it all as often as you want.

For geology buffs, the Lava River Caves is open May thorough September and located only five miles from Sunriver, This geologic site offers self-guided explorations of a mile long lava tube, formed by flowing ancient molten lava.

A fun day trip filled with shopping, galleries, restaurants and even more entertainment options can be found in Bend, only a 30 minute drive away. Spend the afternoon browsing through galleries on Wall and Bond streets, walk around Drake Park, and hit the Deschutes Brewery Public House for pints of Black Butte Porter and juicy Elk Burgers before returning home to your mountain oasis.

This Sunriver home has it all -- a great location, cozy atmosphere, and fun for the kids and adults alike! It's the perfect place to spend your next family vacation.

