You'll feel right at home in this comfortable space. The master bedroom holds a queen-size bed, and the bedroom and large loft upstairs are furnished with two more queen beds, allowing up to six guests to easily share the home. This cottage is complete with multiple outdoor decks for unwinding and breathing in the crisp mountain air; the decks are great for just relaxing with a glass of wine or spotting deer in the yard.

A newly remodeled kitchen with new stove, microwave, oven, and dishwasher will make preparing meals enjoyable whether it's a quick breakfast snack before heading out to the river or a full sit-down dinner after a long day on the slopes. This home also welcomes pets, so you can go ahead and bring your beloved dogs with you, though please note there is a $10 nightly, per-pet fee (with a $40 minimum per stay).

