Sunriver Resort is located just about 15 miles south of Bend and, like most of Oregon's high desert, enjoys over 300 days of sunshine per year. The perfect setting for a family vacation or getaway with friends, this popular Central Oregon destination has something for everyone in your group. And from here, gallery browsing and brewery hopping in Bend is just a short drive away, as is rock climbing in Smith Rock State Park (42 miles), or exploring the western-themed town of Sisters (39 miles). And in winter, there's skiing at Mt. Bachelor Resort, only about a 30-minute drive away.

Stepping inside this Sunriver vacation home, you'll be greeted by bright, white walls and comfortable, inviting furniture. Enjoy cozy nights in, snuggled up in front of the fireplace while you watch cable or a DVD on the large flat screen TV. There's also WiFi so you can keep in touch and let everyone know how much fun you're having during your Central Oregon getaway.

From both the living and dining room at 20 Topflite, there's access to the spacious deck, where you can sit out and read under the shade umbrella or use the gas grill to whip up some steaks for dinner. Form the back of the home, there's an additional deck with your private hot tub and even more outdoor furniture. You'll definitely be able to take advantage of all of the sun here -- you may even see deer and other wildlife right from the yard!

The full kitchen shares an open space with the dining room, with tall, slanted ceilings and all major appliances (including a dishwasher). Plan meals from fancy to simple and when it is time to sit down and eat, there's a small bistro table off the living room, stools at the kitchen counter bar, and a large dining room table. You'll have seats for everyone!

