Other amenities at this Sunriver getaway include a washer and dryer, so you can do laundry during your stay, a stereo with a CD player, and a collection of board games. It's the perfect family retreat for fun, sun, skiing, and Central Oregon adventure.

While here, you'll be right between the Woodlands Golf Course and the scenic, rushing Deschutes River. Rent bikes at the resort's Bike Barn and work your way through over 35 miles of pine tree-lined paved bike paths. Other popular trails for two-wheels include the Benham Falls Loop, Newbury Crater Rim Loop, Todd Lake, and the Swede Ridge Loop. This Sunriver home also comes with 10 SHARC passes, and you'll also have access to the Lodge pool and Sage Springs pool.

In winter, take a holiday sleigh ride through the resort, do some sledding or tubing at Wanoga or Edison Sno-Parks, cross-country ski or snowshoe, or ice skate at the Sunriver Village Mall! Right from the Sunriver Lodge, you can even take a shuttle to popular Mt. Bachelor Resort for a day of downhill and cross-country skiing and snowboarding (a nominal charge applies for the round-trip).

