This delightful three-bedroom Sunriver vacation home with a bonus sleeping nook has great architectural features like tall slanted ceilings and lots of windows for natural light, as well as a fully stocked kitchen, and all the amenities that Sunriver Resort has to offer - including eight SHARC passes! Spend some time here year-round, reconnecting on a family vacation that you'll always remember!

This comfortable, cozy interior will make everyone feel right at home whether you're gathered around the wall-mounted flat screen TV to watch a DVD, or playing a board game on the wooden coffee table. And on snowy evenings, there's no better place than snuggled up in front of the toasty warm gas fireplace, mugs of hot cocoa in hand.

In the large game room, you can play a game of pool, watch TV or pop a video into the VCR. There are a number of chairs for guests to relax or await their turn at the table. And on nice days, everyone can head out to the deck for a barbecue using the gas grill, enjoy a soak in the private hot tub, or just to socialize in the big, fully fenced yard. And since this home is dog friendly for one pet (with a $10 daily fee along with a $40 minimum per stay), your furry family member will have someplace safe to play and run around!

When it's time for meals, this Central Oregon vacation rental boasts a large, sunny kitchen, with a large dining table and stools at the breakfast bar. In the mornings, use the blender to make fruit smoothies for everyone, toast some toast, and grind some fresh beans for coffee. There's even a dishwasher to help you get cleaned up quickly, so that you can go back to having fun. And because the living room and kitchen share an open floor plan, no one will miss out on conversations while preparing meals or cleaning up!

The three bedrooms here are each decorated with an eye towards relaxation. In the master bedroom, you'll have a king sized bed, colorful striped bedding, an attached bath, and access to the deck - there's nothing like a soak in the hot tub before bed! The other two bedrooms have a queen bed and a set of twin-over-full bunk beds. The game room also has a sleeping nook with two twin beds, functioning almost like an extra bedroom that's perfect for kids! Altogether, up to eight guests can sleep comfortably here.

Other in-home amenities include a washer and dryer, stereo, and CD player. And if you need to keep in touch with work or just want to post your vacation pics so your friends will be jealous, this home also has WiFi.

This family friendly, high desert resort has everything you'll need for a relaxing, memorable family getaway! Visit the Sunriver Stables for a horseback tour of beautiful Central Oregon or a Victorian sleigh ride during the holidays, bring your skis and head to Mt. Bachelor Ski Area (for $20 roundtrip, there's a shuttle that leaves right from the Sunriver Lodge if you don't want to make the 30 minute drive yourself), or spend a snowy day snowshoeing on the resort's trails.

Sunriver also has a number of dining options right on site if you don't feel like cooking, and there's even more choices if you figure in The Village at Sunriver. There's Cafe Sintra for breakfast and lunch, Hot Lava Baking Co. for morning snacks and coffee, and Good 2 Go will even prepare a packed lunch for an afternoon hike or bike ride on one of the resort's 30 miles of paved trails. And for swimming in indoor and outdoor pools, more hot tubs, water slides, a tubing hill and more, don't forget to stop by the Sunriver Homeowners Aquatic & Recreation Center (SHARC) for family fun in the water!

This Sunriver vacation rental is just waiting to create memories for your adventure-packed Central Oregon getaway!

