The main floor is a gorgeous mix of tall, slanted wood-beamed ceilings, skylights, large picture windows that bring the outside in, and comfortable furnishings. After a full day of hiking or skiing, come back to your Sunriver retreat for a little family time in front of the wood burning fireplace. Kids and adults alike can enjoy a DVD on the flat screen TV. There's even a VCR if you want to bring some of your favorite videotapes from home!

The dining area shares this open, main space. You'll find seating for eight around the large wooden table with additional seats at the breakfast bar. On sunny days, open the door to the deck and let the fresh, Central Oregon air in or, better yet, take your plates outside and enjoy a meal surrounded by tall trees and the high desert breeze.

The full kitchen has everything the chef in your group will need to prepare meals, snacks, or even a round of afternoon cocktails. A center island holds a stovetop, and there are even extra stools for a kitchen helper or two. Bonus kitchen gadgets include a waffle iron, coffee grinder, blender, slow cooker, and a mixer. You'll be able to create everything from a batch of cookies to fruit smoothies here!

