This four bedroom riverfront vacation home offers the best kind of Oregon getaway: modern luxury (chef's kitchen & TVs in every bedroom), rustic mountain ambiance (exposed timber beams and romantic fireplace) and easy access to a wealth of outdoor recreation (fly fishing, boating, mountain biking, and skiing, to name a few).

The home is tucked away on a private lane just a few miles south of the popular Sunriver Resort, close enough for a morning round of golf or evening at the brewery but far enough to enjoy plenty of peace and quiet at your own riverfront retreat with private dock.

At any time of year, you'll feel instantly at ease in the welcoming great room. Cathedral ceilings, warm hardwoods, and lush Oriental rugs provide the perfect setting for a cozy night by the fire or festive evening cooking dinner with friends. The living area has handsome leather sofas arranged before the wood-burning fireplace with convenient gas starter and the 42" flatscreen with DishTV cable and DVD player.

Just behind the cozy living area, the open kitchen with a barstool-lined island and elegant walnut dining table offer the perfect spot to prepare and share meals together. The kitchen has abundant granite countertops and professional-grade appliances, including a gas range, custom refrigerator, and all-important dishwasher for easy cleanup. In addition to all the basic dinnerware and cooking utensils, the gourmet in your group will appreciate the collection of quality All-Clad cookware and chef's knives.

Through the French doors, the covered wraparound deck has a gas grill so you can enjoy a barbecue even on less-than-sunny days. We suggest starting your mornings here with a mug of freshly brewed coffee, keeping your eyes peeled for the neighborhood wildlife that might wander past.

The home has been thoughtfully furnished to accommodate two families especially well, with a sleeper sofa-equipped family room and master suite downstairs, as well as two additional bedrooms upstairs. While the adults gather around the fireplace, younger guests can retire to the family room with its 36" flat screen television, and plenty of board games. The master suite has a king bed dressed in luxurious linens, attached bath with sunken jetted tub and his-and-her sinks, walk-in closet, and a private entrance to the outdoor deck.

Upstairs, the second bedroom is quite romantic in its own right with a queen bed and balcony overlooking the river. The third bedroom has two twin beds, and a large bath with tub/shower combo sits at the end of the hall. With a washer/dryer provided to keep up with laundry and a well-stocked linen closet, the home is very comfortable to share with up to eight guests. Wireless Internet access makes it easy to plan a working vacation or extended stays.

This part of Central Oregon is meant for adventure. Bring your boat: a ramp sits just a quarter mile downriver. Bring your rods & reels: the nearby Fall River is world-famous for fly fishing. Bring your clubs as your golf options are plentiful! But don't bring the canoes. This home has 2 canoes for guest use! And if you forget your mountain bikes, hiking maps, canoes, kayaks, or even horses, you'll be able to rent practically anything in nearby Sunriver. Wintertime, of course, brings skiing, snowshoeing and snowboarding galore at Mt. Bachelor (18 miles away) and any time of year is a great time to visit Bend (21 miles north) with its breweries, restaurants, shopping, and concerts. Bring your snowmobiles and enjoy them right from your backdoor.

Of course, if you find yourself spending all your time curled up by the fire with a good book from the homes collection, or kicking back on the sun-drenched deck with a glass of your favorite Oregon beverage, we won't tell. However you choose to spend your Central Oregon vacation, you'll love staying in laid-back luxury here on the Big Deschutes River.

