It's a large and beautiful house, and it feels well separated from the neighbors even though it's in a development. So, it's a good space. But in lots of little ways, the house didn't live up to expectations:

- Some rooms receive lots of heat, while others receive very little (including the main area and the master bath -- brrrr!).

- Despite the picture, you can't really see or hear the river from the house.

- The river is very low in the fall and winter, so the dock is sitting on a mud flat about 20 feet from the water.

- The hot tub isn't under a roof, so it isn't usable in all weather. And it *really* didn't look very appealing anyway.

- The fireplace hadn't been cleaned in too long, and the blower didn't circulate any heat.

- There were some repairs that hadn't been made (like a cabinet door missing) and the wi-fi didn't work. Entries in the guest book listed a lot of those kinds of little problems over time.

Maybe for a large family or group of friends, it would be an okay place to stay.

But for us, high nightly rate + high cleaning fee + hot tub fee (?!) = not worth it.

We've stayed in lots of rental houses over the years, including others near Bend -- there are better options out there.

