This contemporary four-bedroom Sunriver vacation rental is the perfect mix of family-friendly and classic style, with ample entertainment amenities, as well as a gourmet-inspired kitchen, private hot tub, and a cabin in the woods charm. Spend afternoons on the back deck, taking in the tree-lined view with a glass of wine or head to SHARC for an afternoon of swimming and other water activities. No mater what you do, this 8 Cedar Lane home has an ideal Sunriver Resort location!

Inside, a large living area is outfitted with comfortable leather couches, slanted wood-beamed ceilings, a beautiful wood-burning stove, and a great entertainment center. Sit back and watch a DVD on the flat screen cable TV, turn on some Netflix streaming, or get on the WiFi. There are board games for an after-dinner tournament around the coffee table and plenty of space for everyone to find a spot for some quiet reading.

The outdoor deck has seating for all, so if it's a nice evening, you may even want to bring a mug of hot cocoa or a glass of after-dinner port outside. On summer evenings, fire up the gas grill for a burger feast or follow the pathway around to the private hot tub for a late evening soak. On clear nights, you can even do a little stargazing.

Back inside, you'll find the amazing updated kitchen is a dream for meal preparation. With slate tile floors, the stainless steel appliances, and granite countertops, the chef in your group will have fun whipping up breakfasts, lunches, and dinners. And don't forget a bowl of popcorn to go with movie night! There's even a dishwasher to make clean-up a snap. Meals can be eaten in the sunny dining room or out on the deck.

This lovely Sunriver getaway has four bedrooms, one with a king sized bed and the other three each with a queen. All have comfortable bedding, large windows looking out at the trees, and accessories like bedside tables and reading lamps. In addition, there are two futons for extra sleeping spots and two and a half bathrooms. This home will comfortably accommodate up to eight guests, as well as two dogs with a $10 per day, per pet fee ($40 minimum per stay).

The upstairs loft has a second TV, as well as one of the futons - perfect for some afternoon reading or as a quiet space to check your email. And if you need to do a load of laundry, you'll find a washer and dryer in the laundry room.

After dinner, you can head out to the garage for a game of pool or some foosball. There are also four adult bikes for exploring the 35 miles of paved bike paths at the resort. And if you need kids' bikes, just stop by the Bike Barn and rent whatever you need (including helmets, locks, and even a bike map).

Just 15 miles south of Bend, Sunriver Resort has something for everyone! Great for families and adventure-seekers alike, you'll be able to enjoy golf (there are four courses), biking, hiking, and more all against the backdrop of the majestic Cascade Mountain Range. The Sunriver Homeowners Aquatic and Recreation Center (SHARC) is home to outdoor and indoor pools, hot tubs, a lazy river, and water slides - and when you stay at this vacation home, you'll have passes to enjoy all of it.

In winter, you're only a short 20 minute drive from Mt. Bachelor or you can just hop on the shuttle at the Sunriver Lodge (for a nominal fee) and not have to worry about driving in the snow or parking. There are also sleigh rides right at Sunriver, as well as tubing, cross-country skiing, and snowshoeing at a number of nearby sno-parks.

Summer or winter, make the most of your Sunriver retreat at this charming and fun-filled Central Oregon vacation rental! Aside from all the attractions at the resort, you'll have a private hot tub, games, and pool table for an unforgettable family vacation to Oregon's high desert.

