The open kitchen has a good sized eating bar with two chairs so your friends can converse with the chef while they are working, or set the six-person dining table for a more formal meal.

With three bedrooms and two full baths, up to six guests can very comfortably share the space. The main floor master suite has a king size bed, a door to the deck and a private bath with tub/shower combination and double sinks. The second bedroom has a queen size bed and shares the hall bath with its walk-in shower. The third bedroom has two twin beds, and each bedroom offer ample closet space and dressers so you can unpack and relax. With warm wood accent walls, each space feels delightfully cozy with just a touch of rustic style.

The home offers access to all of the Black Butte Ranch recreation facilities! You'll enjoy the four pools, two golf courses, tennis, stables, biking and walking trails, state of the art spa and wonderful restaurants. The views from the main lodge are unmatched, looking out to the Cascade Mountain Range and over the lake, where you can even rent a canoe for an afternoon paddle! Complimentary WiFi is offered at the lodge and recreation facilities if you must stay connected to the office or check your email periodically.

The charming town of Sisters is just twenty minutes away, and the picturesque Metolius River and town of Camp Sherman are just across from the ranch entrance. A visit to the Camp Sherman store and fish hatchery is always a fun trip, as is a hike up to the ranger station on top of Black Butte.

Whether you are here to relax by the pool or to explore the great outdoors, you will love to call this Central Oregon vacation rental your home away from home!

*In order to access the recreational facilities, there is a fee of $6 per day for every guest above 8 years old. Please be aware that this fee will be collected by the resort at check-in. Also, please note that motorcycles are not permitted within the ranch or on any of the Black Butte properties.*

