A trip to Bend in Central Oregon will have you enjoying the authentic charm of this Old Mill vacation home, perched above the Old Mill District with mountain views. You'll be within easy walking distance to all the shops, restaurants, and theaters in the Old Mill district and downtown Bend is less than two miles away by car or bike.

This comfortable home offers a state-of-the-art sound system, as well as high speed WiFi throughout. The TV offers cable channels, but it's a new smart TV that allows you to access Amazon Prime for videos or Pandora accounts, too.

In the living room, sit back on the stylish, bright turquoise sofas while you watch a movie or your favorite TV shows. And if you get chilly, the gas fireplace with blower warms the living room, adjoining kitchen and dining area easily.

When it's time to prepare meals, the kitchen is equipped with everything including the basic spices to prepare a simple breakfast or a gourmet dinner. If you're walking around downtown Bend, pick up some beans at one of our many outstanding local roasters to come back and grind at the house.

When it's time for bed, you'll have your choice of four well-appointed bedrooms. Two of the bedrooms each have a queen bed, and there's a beautiful master suite with a king sized bed and a sofa trundle for extra seating or sleeping. A nearby den has two sets of twin bunk beds to sleep the extra little ones. The home also has a lovely tuned piano for added entertainment. This home will comfortably sleep ten guests (twelve if you use the sofa trundle in the master.)

In the evenings, step out to the large landscaped yard. It's a wonderful place to enjoy an evening mug of tea or glass of wine on the patio.

Although the home backs Bend's new parkway, you'd never know that once you're inside. The private cul-de-sac location is ideally situated to conveniently explore all that the greater Bend area has to offer. Additionally, there is a new wheelchair ramp to the front door if needed (and although a wonderful asset for those in need, it's not to ADA standards due to the slope and lack of a few feet in distance.) Other amenities include a stereo, CD player, and a washer and dryer for guest use.

When you're ready to explore the area, you'll find outdoor adventures left and right. There's white water rafting on the Deschutes River and great hiking in the nearby national forest lands, as well as mountain biking and rock climbing opportunities nearby.

In winter, Mt. Bachelor is only a 30 minute drive away for skiing, snow boarding, and snowshoeing. Year-round, the shops of the Old Mill District are only a 10 minute stroll away. A quick ride into downtown will reveal even more shopping and dining opportunities, include a number of local breweries for a fun afternoon of beer tasting.

For a great Central Oregon vacation, Bend has a lot to offer and everyone will enjoy staying at this wonderful and charming vacation home!

