Come enjoy the Central Oregon high desert at this beautiful and contemporary three-bedroom Black Butte Ranch vacation rental. With a traditional Northwest style and a prime Glaze Meadow location, your whole family will enjoy a getaway to this beautiful and laid-back vacation resort near the Cascade Mountains.

Located 32 miles outside of Bend, and 52 miles away from Mt. Bachelor, this resort community offers plenty of recreational opportunities like golf, swimming, and bike paths.

Nestled among the Ponderosa pines, this vacation home offers a comfortable, modern decor complete with a tall, slanted ceilings, a wood burning fireplace, a wall of windows looking out at the trees, and plenty of seats in the living room for everyone to relax. Kick back on the sofa with a good book or turn your attention to the flat screen TV for some cable or a DVD. Family movie nights will be a popular pastime here! You'll also find WiFi, a washer and dryer, a ping pong table, and a stereo: all of the comforts of home so you can get online or do a load of laundry during your stay. And if you're feeling lucky, stage an after-dinner ping pong tournament - winner gets an extra dessert.

This main living area also has a dining room table easily set for six, and a full kitchen for preparing vacation meals (also featuring a breakfast bar with extra seats). Making dinner is easy here with all of the standard major appliances, ample counter space, and all the pots and pans you'll need for any culinary project. After a day of fun activities like horseback riding or golf, assemble everyone around for a platter of fried chicken and three bean salad. And if the urge strikes, head out to the deck and the gas grill for some late afternoon barbecue.

There are three bedrooms, each with a queen bed, as well as two twin beds in the loft area. These rooms all feature wood accents, tall ceilings, and colorful bedding. One bed is on the lower level, while the others are all upstairs. This charming home will sleep up to eight guests (with a maximum of six adults).

With over 300 days of sun a year, Black Butte Ranch offers a wealth of outdoor activities on its popular 1800 acre resort. There are two championship golf courses, swimming pools, tennis courts, a stable with horses, and 18 miles of hiking and biking trails.

If you're in the mood to be pampered, the Spa at Black Butte Ranch is just the thing after an adventure-filled day. Schedule a massage, body treatment - there are even hair and makeup services. The spa is located inside the Glaze Meadow Recreation Center, where you'll have access to hydro-fit classes and lap swimming, exercise equipment, yoga, and zumba classes. And in the Family Recreation Area, pick from basketball, pickle ball, and bocci ball courts.

During your stay, you should try to plan at least one meal out at the Lodge Restaurant, where you'll enjoy a stunning view and farm-to-table cuisine. Other onsite dining options include Robert's Pub, Aspen Lounge, and the Lodge Espresso Shop. In summer, stop by the seasonal Lakeside Bistro, right near the lodge pool, for a take and bake pizza to enjoy back at your Black Butte Ranch vacation home.

With so much to do, it's no wonder that Black Butte Ranch has been a favorite Central Oregon destination for over 40 years! Come see why families love staying at this resort and enjoy the comfort of your own Central Oregon vacation home.

*In order to access the recreational facilities, there is a fee of $6 per day for every guest above 8 years old. Please be aware that this fee will be collected by the resort at check-in. Also, please note that motorcycles are not permitted within the ranch or on any of the Black Butte properties.*

