Experience all the reasons to visit Black Butte Ranch on one gorgeous acre when you stay at this amazing tri-level Black Butte Ranch vacation home with a private hot tub, unique two-sided fireplace, and gorgeous outdoor deck! Surrounded by trees and offering views out towards the nearby Glaze Meadows Golf Course, this home boasts an excellent location on a private cul de sac near all the facilities and astounding natural beauty that come with your visit to Black Butte Ranch Resort.

Make the trip over to nearby Sisters for some shopping, dining, and - if your timing's right  -  some great music. Skiers and boarders will be in their element with a trip to Hoodoo Resort, about 20 minutes away. Bend, with its bustling brewpubs and Central Oregon shopping, is just 30 minutes further.

On a chilly Cascade morning, make your way to the family room before breakfast and throw a log on the fire in the grand, stone fireplace. Sink into the plush furniture, the beautiful hardwood floors and wood ceilings gleaming in the mountain sunlight, bring up the laptop, and check the weather forecast for the day's destinations on the free WiFi.

At mealtime, turn your cook loose in this bright, fully-equipped kitchen with earth-tone tile floor, track lighting, recessed stove and piggy back oven and microwave, providing extra counter space for prep and lots of cabinets for supplies. When the dinner bell rings, lay out the meal on the big dining set with room for six. If it's cold, you'll be nice and warm, seated on the kitchen side of the two-sided fireplace that also opens to the living area. There's also room for four more hungry guests on the stools at the bar. Weather permitting, throw some salmon on the gas grill out on the back deck, barbecue your meal, and feast among the beautifully landscaped backyard and towering pines.

After a good soak in the hot tub out back, it's time for bed. With two bedrooms on the main floor and a master upstairs in the loft, this spacious home will accommodate eight. The first lower-level bedroom has a queen bed, and the other with two twins. Both are tastefully decorated in a country decor with comfortable linens, and share the first floor's full bathroom. Luxurious and large, the upper-level master bedroom echoes the living room's decor, with the same gorgeous hardwood floor and vaulted wood ceiling, along with its own full bathroom.

Up in the loft, you can watch the morning headlines on cable TV or enjoy a DVD before bed. There's a sleeper sofa for two additional guests, and the home also has an additional half-bath for everyone's convenience. You can definitely pack light: there's a washer and dryer in the home, too.

Along with all the wonderful amenities that come with this home, for a small fee* you'll also have access to the Black Butte Ranch facilities: the Glaze Meadow Recreation Center featuring indoor and outdoor swimming pools, hot tub, children's wading pool, steam room, workout facilities, a sports shop, equipment rental shop and spa. Take the bikes out on the 18 miles of paved bike paths or take some fly-fishing lessons over at Phalarope Lake. And since you'll be enjoying views of the Glaze Meadow Golf Course throughout your stay, you should probably bring your clubs along!

Come stay in this lovely home in Oregon's Cascade Mountains and experience all that beautiful Central Oregon vacation home has to offer!

*When you arrive at the Black Butte Ranch resort, you will need to register at the Welcome Center. Please be aware that there is a $6 daily fee for every guest above 8 years old for access to the recreational facilities and that this fee will be collected by the resort at the time of check-in. Unfortunately, no motorcycles are permitted within the ranch or on any of the Black Butte properties.*

