A glass door leads out to the large deck overlooks the natural spring and provides tranquil sounds of water below, with Black Butte's meadow stretching out into the distance. The gas barbecue is all ready for your cook-outs and al fresco dining. In the afternoon, it's also the perfect spot to put your feet up and get into a good book.

The main level has a lovely master bedroom - with a queen bed and en suite bathroom with a jetted tub and separate shower, it's quite a peaceful and relaxing spot. The lucky recipient of this room will also be treated to amazing views right off the deck. This level has a second bedroom with a queen bed.

Upstairs, there is another queen bedroom, a reading room with cozy, overstuffed chairs, and an adjoining sitting room with a twin bed. The upstairs is ideal for family members or a couple with small children that want to share a more private area of the house. The views out to the Butte and over the meadow are spectacular. With its three bedrooms and loft, this home will sleep seven guests comfortably; the provided washer/dryer make it easy to keep packing light.

Outside, there's a wonderful yard to discover, a free-standing porch swing, and lots of space for the kids to play.

Beyond the yard, Black Butte Ranch offers outdoor adventures for everyone in your group. In the winter, you can make the short 20 minute drive to Sisters and Hoodoo Ski area for downhill sporting at its best. The surrounding National Forest land has many trails for both cross-country skiing, snowshoeing, and snowmobiling in the winter, as well as hiking and biking in the summer.

A couple of white water rafting outfitters have pick-up and drop off service at the Rec Barn at Black Butte Ranch. Plan a family adventure they won't soon forget with a fun-filled half day McKenzie or Deschutes River trip. Black Butte Resort also has two golf courses, tennis courts, horseback riding, and five swimming pools. You will definitely have no problem finding something to do here!

On days that you don't feel like cooking, you can head to the Lodge Restaurant for fine dining, or to Robert's Pub for casual plates. For even more options, visit the cute western-style shops and cafes in Sisters, and Bend's popular breweries and restaurants are a mere 45 minutes from your door.

Come to Black Butte Ranch and enjoy this Central Oregon vacation home's bright spaces, shiny hardwood floors, and fabulous deck for entertaining and enjoy all that this resort community offers in style.

*In order to access the recreational facilities, there is a fee of $6 per day for every guest above 8 years old. Please be aware that this fee will be collected by the resort at check-in. Unfortunately, no motorcycles are permitted within the ranch or on any of the Black Butte properties.*

