Come enjoy one of Central Oregon's most desirable and family-friendly destination resorts, and discover all that this three-bedroom Black Butte Ranch vacation rental has to offer! One of the original resort cabins, you'll love the comfortable, open floor plan, rustic charm, and authentic Western art throughout the house!

The multi-use trail is practically right outside your door and ready to take you to all that the ranch offers. At the Black Butte Ranch recreation facilities, you and your family can enjoy four pools, two golf courses, tennis courts and stables, in addition to the biking and walking trails throughout the resort. A state of the art spa is also included, as are four restaurant options - the Lodge Restaurant for fine dining, Robert's Pub for more casual meals, the Aspen Lounge for cocktails and light meals, and the Lodge Espresso Shop for all your coffee needs.

Step inside to a large, open floor plan. A wonderful wood-burning fireplace warms the living room and adjoining dining area, and the tall, slanted ceilings give the room a very spacious feel. The whole room has a very homey feel, and you'll have no trouble finding a cozy spot to relax and read a book or just enjoy the views of Black Butte out the large windows. For entertainment, there is a new flat screen TV with cable and a DVD player. Fix some snacks, get the drinks and enjoy family movie nights in comfort.

For the chef in the group, there is an adjoining kitchen right near the eight person dining room table. It'll be easy to keep conversations going while meals are being prepared, or you can just move the party into the kitchen. There's lots of room for helpers around the shiny granite countertops. You'll also find all the appliances needed for creating great vacation meals - everything from blueberry pancakes to roast chicken and vegetables.

Sliding glass doors lead out to the deck outfitted with Adirondack chairs, table seating, and a gas grill for barbecues. As Black Butte Ranch boasts over 300 days of sunshine a year, grilling is essentially a year-round practice! In the yard, you'll also find a hammock that's just perfect for lazy, sunny afternoon book reading or rejuvenating naps after dinner.

There is a nicely decorated bedroom on the main floor with a king sized bed and TV. The full bathroom on this level has been beautifully remodeled with granite counters and decorative accents. There is also a laundry room for guest use, so getting dirty while out exploring the area is no problem at all!

Heading upstairs, there are two more spacious bedrooms. Both have tall, slanted ceilings and comfortable beds. One room has a large, king sized bed and stylish wall art, while the other has a queen and two twin beds, and a more western look. The upstairs bath has also been remodeled with more of those gorgeous granite countertops, as well as a walk-in shower. This home will sleep eight guests quite comfortably.

The lodge also boasts spectacular views of the Cascade Mountain Range and Phalarope Lake. In addition to swimming in the pools, there's also canoeing, kayaking and paddle boarding on the lake to consider. Complimentary WiFi is offered at the lodge and recreation facilities to stay connected to the office, update your status, or check email periodically.

Easy day trips include the nearby town of Sisters, at only a nine mile drive away. There you'll discover many galleries, restaurants, and shops. Outdoor enthusiasts may want to check out the crystal clear Metolius River for fly fishing opportunities to catch and release native rainbow trout, Kokonee salmon, and bull trout.

In winter, like a lot of areas in Central Oregon, Black Butte Ranch is close to skiing, snowboarding, and snowshoeing adventures, with the Hoodoo Ski Area a mere 15 miles away.

Whether you are at Black Butte Ranch to ski, swim, relax by the pool, or explore the great outdoors, you'll love your stay this comfortable, western-themed Central Oregon vacation rental.

