Meals will be easy to prepare here in your well-stocked full kitchen. Bright and spacious, you'll have all the major appliances you'll need on the evenings you don't head out to one of Eagle Crest's restaurants (there are three, as well as the resort's unique poolside eatery). And if you want to take advantage of Central Oregon's 300 average days of sun per year, the back deck is complete with a gas grill and outdoor furniture.

This Eagle Crest retreat's two bedrooms are both upstairs and will easily accommodate up to four guests. The master boasts a beautiful four-poster king-sized bed, a wall-mounted TV, shelves full of books, and access to a balcony overlooking trees and high-desert scrub. In the mornings, you can wander down to the kitchen for a cup of coffee, come back upstairs, and sip it out on your own private balcony. The adjoining bathroom has a luxurious, jetted soaking tub and a separate walk-in shower (there is also a second full bathroom). The other bedroom has two twin beds, and is ideal for two younger guests to share.

An amazing year-round destination, Eagle Crest Resort is home to two championship golf courses, including The Ridge Course which is open throughout the winter too! In addition, you'll have three Sports Centers to choose from, miles of paved and off-road trails for hiking and biking, lovely views of the Deschutes River, and even horse stables for equestrian tours, pony rides, and even horseback riding lessons. This home comes with six passes to the resort's recreation centers, and additional passes can be purchased. No matter what you do, you don't even have to worry about keeping your clothes clean because your Eagle Crest getaway has its own washer and dryer.

In winter, Eagle Crest Resort is less than an hour from Mt. Bachelor Ski Resort for 70 runs of powder-packed fun, snowshoe tours, cross-country trails, and even dog sled rides. Closer to Eagle Crest, you can take a snowmobile tour or ice skate at the Redmond outdoor rink - just a few minutes away. And any time of year, The Spa at Eagle Crest is available for pampering, massages, and even relaxing in the outdoor hot tubs.

One thing is sure: this Central Oregon vacation rental offers it all! Activities and amenities for the whole family await you at this comfortable and modern Eagle Crest vacation townhome on the desirable Golden Pheasant Drive!

