Good location but that's about it. Thin walls and can hear neighbors walking up and down the stairs. A/C was set to 72 which kept the downstairs cool but the upstairs was a sweat box. The master bedroom is right over the deck of the neighbors so be prepared to hear every word if they are outside and you open the windows.  The lighting inside is poor and has a cave-like feel because of it. I would not stay in this type of unit again

My husband was running in the Smith Ascent race at Smith Rock and this location was exactly what we needed. We chose to go with a VRBO b/c we had his mother in town and we wanted to make sure he slept well prior to the race (unlike some hotels which can be noisy), and we are glad we did!

The master bed and bath were great! Two sinks, large bath, separate toilet. Large, comfy bed. Easy to operate TV. Perfect. The guest room had 2 twins which I wasn't expecting (but would have known had I read the details more carefully). His mom said she slept great though!

The location was perfect. About 20 minutes from Bend, and about 25 minutes from Smith Rock.

